\h Deuteronomy
\toc1 Deuteronomy
\toc2 Deuteronomy
\toc3 Deu.
\mt1 Deuteronomy
\is1 Introduction
\ip The Greek word вҖҳDeuteronomyвҖҷ means вҖҳSecond lawвҖҷ, because some aspects of God's instructions in the previous accounts are repeated again in this one, noticeably the Ten Commandments. Hebrew readers call this document вҖҳDevДҒrimвҖҷ which is the second word in the Hebrew text and means вҖҳWordsвҖҷ or вҖҳThingsвҖҷ. Some European and other translations call it вҖҳThe fifth book of Mosheh/MosesвҖҷ.
\ip This document contains a series of addresses that Mosheh (commonly known in English as Moses) made to the descendants of Yisrael/Israel while they were in the Moav region on the eastern side of the Yarden/Jordan river. They had stopped there for quite a long time after their travelling through the wilderness, and it would soon be time for them to cross the river and enter the вҖҳpromised landвҖҷ of Kanaan/Canaan.
\ip Some of the more important points made in this document include: 1. Mosheh's summary of the history of the Israelis over the previous forty year, and how he requested them to remain loyal and obedient to Yahweh. 2. Mosheh's retelling of the вҖҳTen commandsвҖҷ and his explanation of the first commands, ensuring that Yisrael's descendants knew that it was vital to continue serving Yahweh. This also includes the various rules to be obey in Kanaan. 3. Mosheh's interpretation of the peoples agreement with Yahweh is retold here, and his encouragement to the people to continue to obey that agreement. 4. The selection of Yehoshua/Joshua as the new leader for God's chosen people group, Mosheh's song about the joy of serving Yahweh and the blessings for those who obey. Mosheh's death in Moav is also retold here.
\ip The best known segment of this document is Yahweh's blessing and cursing of his chosen people depending on the path that they decide to take. If the Israelis would chose to follow Yahweh's instructions, there was a large blessing to be receive, but equally a terrifying curse should they fail to acknowledge what God had done for them.
\ip The most important verses here are 6:4-6, quoted by Yeshua as being the greatest of all commands: You should love your god Yahweh with your whole mind, your entire being, and all your strength.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 Mosheh's first address \ior 1:1вҖ“4:49\ior*
\io1 Mosheh's second address \ior 5:1вҖ“26:19\ior*
\io2 a. The ten commands \ior 5:1вҖ“10:22\ior*
\io2 b. Instructions, rules, and warnings \ior 11:1вҖ“26:19\ior*
\io1 Instructions before entering Kanaan/Canaan \ior 27:1вҖ“28:68\ior*
\io1 The renewal of the agreement \ior 29:1вҖ“30:20\ior*
\io1 Mosheh's final speech \ior 31:1вҖ“33:29\ior*
\io1 Mosheh's death \ior 34:1-12\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Mosheh's first set of instructions
\rem /s1 The Command to Leave Horeb; Moses' first discourse; Introduction; Events at Horeb Recalled; The Command to Leave Sinai
\p
\v 1 TheseВҰ81372 are the messagesВҰ81373 thatВҰ81374 MoshehВҰ81376 \add (MosesВҰ81376)\add* spokeВҰ81375 to YisraelВҰ81381 \add (IsraelВҰ81381)\add* \add back when they were\add* in the wildernessВҰ81384 \add on the easternВҰ81382 side\add* of the Yarden \add (Jordan) river\add*, in the desertВҰ81385 plainВҰ81385 oppositeВҰ81386 SufВҰ81387 between ParanВҰ81390 and TofelВҰ81393, Lavan, Hatserot, and Di-Zahav.
\v 2 (It takes eleven days \add to walk\add* from Horev \add (Mt. Sinai)\add* to KadeshВҰ81408-BarneaВҰ81409 via Mt. SeirВҰ81406.)
\v 3 Forty years \add after the IsraelisВҰ81424 had left Egypt\add* MoshehВҰ81421 \add вүҲpassed on\add* to \add *them\add* everything that YahwehВҰ81429 had instructedВҰ81428 him
\v 4 after he'd defeatedВҰ81434 the AmoriteВҰ81438 King SihonВҰ81436 who lived at HeshbonВҰ81441, andВҰ81442 BashanВҰ81445 King OgВҰ81443 who lived at AshtarotВҰ81449 in EdreiВҰ81450.\x + \xo 1:4: \xt Num 21:21-35.\x*
\v 5 On the easternВҰ81452 side of the Yarden \add river\add* in the Moav \add (MoabВҰ81455)\add* region, MoshehВҰ81457 \add began\add* explaining those instructions, saying,
\s2 The removal of Yisrael's descendants from Sinai
\p
\v 6 вҖңOur GodВҰ81466 YahwehВҰ81465 spokeВҰ81467 to us at Horev, saying: You've \add вүҲcamped\add* here \add вүҲlong enoughВҰ81471\add* at this mountainВҰ81475.
\v 7 \add Now,\add* \add вүҲpack up\add* and travel to the AmoriteВҰ81484 hill country and \add вүҲthe surrounding areas\add* and the river plain, the lowlands and the southern wilderness, the coastalВҰ81494 plain, all of Canaan, and LebanonВҰ81498 as far \add north-east\add* as the EuphratesВҰ81505 river.
\v 8 Listen, that \add area of\add* land \add вүҲahead of you\add*, I've given to you. Go \add ahead\add* and takeВҰ81514 possessionВҰ81514 that land that YahwehВҰ81520 promised to your ancestorsВҰ81521 Avraham \add (AbrahamВҰ81522)\add*, Yitshak \add (IsaacВҰ81523)\add*, and Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*. \add вүЎHe promised\add* to giveВҰ81525 it to them and to theirВҰ81527 descendantsВҰ81527.вҖқ
\s2 Mosheh appoints leaders
\rem /s1 Appointment of Tribal Leaders; Moses Appoints Leaders from Each Tribe; The Appointment of Leaders; Moses Appoints Judges
\r (Exo. 18:13-27)
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ81530 Mosheh saidВҰ81530, вҖңI told you at that timeВҰ81532 that I wasn't able to \add вүҲgovern\add* all of you by myself
\v 10 \add because\add* your godВҰ81543 YahwehВҰ81542 has multiplied you, andВҰ81546 wowВҰ81546, \add вүҲnow\add* you're as numerous as the starsВҰ81548 in the sky.
\v 11 May your ancestors' godВҰ81553 YahwehВҰ81552 increase you all a thousandВҰ81558 timesВҰ81559 \add more\add* and blessВҰ81560 you all as he's promised
\v 12 \add but\add* how could IВҰ81567 \add possibly\add* bear all your loads and burdensВҰ81570 and disputesВҰ81571 by myselfВҰ81568?
\v 13 \add So\add* nominate some men from your tribesВҰ81579 who I can appointВҰ81580 as your leadersВҰ81581вҖ”\add вүЎmen\add* who are sensible and wise, and respectedВҰ81578 \add >by the people\add*,
\v 14 andВҰ81585 \add @your parents\add* \add вүҲagreed with thatВҰ81589 suggestion\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ81594\add* I took those wise, respectedВҰ81601 men and appointed them to be your leadersвҖ”leaders of thousandsВҰ81607, of hundredsВҰ81609, of fiftiesВҰ81611, and of tens. \add вүЎI also appointed some\add* as your tribal officialsВҰ81614.
\v 16 ThenВҰ81617 I instructed your \add new\add* leaders telling them to \add вүҲlistenВҰ81624 carefully\add* to \add both sides of\add* \add вүҲdisputes\add* and \add вүҲmake fair and honest judgementsВҰ81620\add* \add in conflicts involving\add* \add вүҲeither Israelis or\add* foreigners.
\v 17 \add вүҲDon't show partiality when you're making a judgementвҖ”treat important people just the same as the others\add*. \add вүҲDon't worry about what people will think because fair judgement is a godly activity\add*. And if any matter is too difficult, bringВҰ81660 it to me \add вүҲfor a decision\add*.
\v 18 I also gave you all other instructions at thatВҰ81672 timeВҰ81666.
\s2 The spies
\rem /s1 Scouts Explore the Land; Spies Sent Out; Israel's Refusal to Enter the Land; The Spies Are Sent Out from Kadesh Barnea
\r (Num. 13:1-33)
\p
\v 19 вҖңThenВҰ81675 we left Horev \add (Mt. Sinai)\add* and wentВҰ81677 through that wide and dangerous wildernessВҰ81681 that you sawВҰ81686 on the wayВҰ81687 to the AmoriteВҰ81689 hill countryВҰ81688 as ourВҰ81693 godВҰ81693 YahwehВҰ81692 had instructedВҰ81691 us, \add eventually\add* arriving at KadeshВҰ81697-BarneaВҰ81698.
\v 20 ThenВҰ81700 I told you all, вҖҳYou've all comeВҰ81702 to the AmoriteВҰ81706 hill countryВҰ81705, whichВҰ81707 ourВҰ81710 godВҰ81710 YahwehВҰ81709 is giving us.
\v 21 Look, your god Yahweh has given you\f + \fr 1:21 \ft The you\+bd (pl)\+bd* in the previous verse has switched to you\+bd (sg)\+bd* here.\f* the land \add вүҲthat's in front of you\add*, \add so\add* go ahead and take possessionВҰ81723 of it as Yahweh, your ancestors' god has told you. Don't be afraidВҰ81732 and don'tВҰ81730 be discouraged.вҖҷ
\v 22 ThenВҰ81737 you all approachedВҰ81737 me and \add вүҲsuggested\add*, вҖҳ\add вүҲWe shouldВҰ81741 sendВҰ81741 some menВҰ81742 aheadВҰ81743 of us to scout out the place\add*, and they can return and tell us the \add вүҲbest way to get inside those\add* citiesВҰ81761.вҖҷ
\v 23 \add вүҲThat sounded goodВҰ81766 to me, so I took one manВҰ81774 from each of the twelve tribesВҰ81776\add*
\v 24 and theyВҰ81781 wentВҰ81779 up into the hill countryВҰ81780 as far as the EshkolВҰ81785 valley, and the scouted it \add out\add*.
\v 25 They \add вүҲpicked\add* some fruitВҰ81791 from \add *there\add* and brought it \add back\add* to us, and \add вүҲreported\add* that the land that our godВҰ81804 YahwehВҰ81803 is giving us was \add very\add* good.
\rem /s1 Israel Rebels against the Lord; Rebellion Against the Lord
\p
\v 26 вҖңButВҰ81808 \add @your parents\add* were unwilling to \add вүҲproceed\add* andВҰ81811 rebelledВҰ81811 againstВҰ81811 your godВҰ81816 Yahweh'sВҰ81815 \add вүҲcommand\add*.\x + \xo 1:26: \xt Deu 9:23; Heb 3:16.\x*
\v 27 SoВҰ81818 you all grumbledВҰ81818 in your tentsВҰ81819, saying that it was because YahwehВҰ81822 hated us that he broughtВҰ81824 us out of EgyptВҰ81826 to hand us over to the AmoritesВҰ81830 to be destroyedВҰ81831.
\v 28 \add вүЎYou said\add* that you all didn't want to enter because the peopleВҰ81843 \add вүҲwere so tall and strong\add* and their citiesВҰ81847 were \add вүҲfortifiedВҰ81849 and powerful\add* with very high walls around them.
\p
\v 29 вҖңThenВҰ81858 I told \add вүҲyour parents\add*, вҖҳDon't be terrifiedВҰ81862 or afraid of them.
\v 30 Your godВҰ81869 YahwehВҰ81868 \add вүҲwho goesВҰ81870 ahead of you\add*, he'll fightВҰ81873 for you just like everything \add вүҲyou saw\add* him do in EgyptВҰ81879
\v 31 andВҰ81882 in the wildernessВҰ81882, whereВҰ81883 you sawВҰ81884 how your godВҰ81888 YahwehВҰ81887 carried you like a \add вүҲfather\add* carries his sonвҖ”getting you through \add thatВҰ81900 difficult region\add* untilВҰ81902 you all \add eventually\add* arrived here.вҖҷ\x + \xo 1:31: \xt Acts 13:18.\x*
\v 32 \add вүҲHowever,\add* you all didn'tВҰ81912 believe your godВҰ81915 Yahweh\x + \xo 1:32: \xt Heb 3:19.\x*
\v 33 \add вүҲwho had gone aheadВҰ81918\add* of you to find a \add good\add* placeВҰ81922 for you all to make your campвҖ”using fireВҰ81924 at nightВҰ81926 to show you all the way, and cloudВҰ81933 in the daytime.
\s2 Yisrael's punishment
\rem /s1 The Penalty for Israel's Rebellion; The Lord Punishes Israel
\r (Num. 14:20-45)
\p
\v 34 вҖңYahwehВҰ81937 heard \add вүҲthose complaints\add* and got angryВҰ81942 and made this promise,\x + \xo 1:34-35: \xt Heb 3:18.\x*
\v 35 вҖҳNone of the menВҰ81950 of this evilВҰ81953 generationВҰ81952 will \add вүҲget to enter\add* the goodВҰ81957 land thatВҰ81958 I promised to giveВҰ81960 to your ancestorsВҰ81961
\v 36 apart from Yefunneh'sВҰ81967 son Kalev \add (CalebВҰ81964)\add*вҖ”he \add вүҲcan enter\add* it and I'll giveВҰ81972 him and his sons the land \add вүҲthatВҰ81976 he scouted out\add* becauseВҰ81981 he \add вүҲfollowed YahwehВҰ81985 whole-heartedly\add*.вҖҷ
\v 37 YahwehВҰ81991 was \add also\add* angryВҰ81990 at me becauseВҰ81992 of you all, \add and\add* told me that I also wouldn't \add вүҲbe able to enter\add*,
\v 38 but that Nun'sВҰ82007 son Yehoshua who was standing thereВҰ82012 in front of me, \add вүҲwould be the one to lead\add* YisraelВҰ82021 to possess the land.
\p
\v 39 вҖңYour children that you \add вүҲthought would be taken captive\add*, and your young sonsВҰ82028 who don'tВҰ82030 \add yet\add* knowВҰ82032 right from wrong, they'll \add be the ones to\add* enter \add @the land\add*, and I'll giveВҰ82040 it to them, and \add вүҲit'll becomeВҰ82027 theirs\add*.
\v 40 \add вүҲBut\add* you yourselves need to turnВҰ82048 around and go back into the wildernessВҰ82051 \add вүҲin the direction of\add* the Red Sea.
\p
\v 41 вҖң\add вүҲbut they\add* all answeredВҰ82057 and \add вүҲadmitted\add*, вҖҳ\add Yes,\add* we've sinnedВҰ82061 against Yahweh, \add but now we'll fix that by\add* going in to fightВҰ82065 and do everything that ourВҰ82071 godВҰ82071 Yahweh has commandedВҰ82069 us.вҖҷ \add вүҲSoВҰ82057\add* every man strapped on his weaponsВҰ82076вҖ”\add вүҲnow thinking it would be easy to take over\add* the hill countryВҰ82080.
\p
\v 42 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ82082\add* YahwehВҰ82083 told me to \add вүҲwarn\add* them not to goВҰ82088 ahead and fightВҰ82091 because he wouldn't help them, and \add so\add* they'd \add end up\add* being defeatedВҰ82096 by their enemiesВҰ82098 if they proceeded.
\v 43 \add вүҲSoВҰ82100\add* I told \add вүҲyour parents\add* that, but they wouldn't listenВҰ82103вҖ”they rebelledВҰ82104 againstВҰ82104 YahwehВҰ82108 andВҰ82100 arrogantly \add marched\add* up into the hill countryВҰ82111
\v 44 \add вүҲwhere\add* the AmoritesВҰ82114 who livedВҰ82115 there came out against them, and chasedВҰ82119 them like bees and made \add @the warriors\add* scatter in SeirВҰ82126 as far as HaremahВҰ82129.
\v 45 \add вүҲSoВҰ82131 your parents\add* returnedВҰ82131 andВҰ82131 wept \add вүҲin frontВҰ82133\add* of YahwehВҰ82134, but he didn'tВҰ82135 \add вүҲpay any attention to them\add*.
\rem /s1 The Years in the Desert; The Desert Years
\v 46 \add вүҲSoВҰ82144 that's why we\add* stayedВҰ82144 at KadeshВҰ82145-Barnea \add вүҲfor as long as we all did\add*.
\c 2
\s1 Yisrael's wanderings in the wilderness
\rem /s1 Remembering Israel's Wanderings; Wanderings in the Desert
\p
\v 1 вҖңThenВҰ82152 we turnedВҰ82152 and went \add back\add* into the wildernessВҰ82154 towards the Red Sea as YahwehВҰ82161 had told us to do, and we \add вүҲspent a long time wandering\add* aroundВҰ82163 Mt. SeirВҰ82168.\x + \xo 2:1: \xt Num 21:4.\x*
\p
\v 2 вҖңThen YahwehВҰ82174 told me,
\v 3 вҖҳYou've all been wandering around this hilly area for long enoughВҰ82178вҖ”\add now\add* turnВҰ82186 and go towards the northВҰ82188
\v 4 andВҰ82190 tell the peopleВҰ82192, вҖңYou'll all be crossing the border into SeirВҰ82203 where your relatives, Esau'sВҰ82201 descendantsВҰ82199, liveВҰ82202. They'll be afraidВҰ82204 of you \add вүҲbut you'll all need to stay very alert\add*.\x + \xo 2:4: \xt Gen 36:8.\x*
\v 5 \add вүҲDon't attack\add* them because I won'tВҰ82209 giveВҰ82216 you any of their landвҖ”\add вүҲnot even a footprint size piece\add* because I've givenВҰ82228 Mt. SeirВҰ82232 to EsauВҰ82227 as \add &their\add* inheritance.
\v 6 \add вүҲAny food or drinkВҰ82245 you get from them must be paid for with cash\add*
\v 7 because your god Yahweh has blessedВҰ82250 all of your labourвҖ”he's \add always\add* \add вүҲbeen aware of your travel\add* through that vast wildernessВҰ82258. Your god Yahweh has \add вүҲhelped\add* you for those fortyВҰ82263 years \add so\add* you've all \add вүҲhad everything you need\add*.вҖқ вҖҷ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ82272\add* we passedВҰ82272 by ourВҰ82274 relatives, Esau'sВҰ82277 descendantsВҰ82275 who liveВҰ82278 in SeirВҰ82279. We travelledВҰ82287 along the Yarden valley plainВҰ82281 from Eilat andВҰ82272 Estyon-Gever, thenВҰ82272 \add north\add* through the Moav wildernessВҰ82289.
\v 9 ThenВҰ82292 YahwehВҰ82293 told me, вҖҳ\add вүҲDon't aggravate\add* Moav, andВҰ82292 \add вүҲdon'tВҰ82302 attack\add* them, because I won'tВҰ82302 giveВҰ82310 youВҰ82297 \add вүҲany of theirВҰ82312 land\add* because I've givenВҰ82318 ArВҰ82321 to the sons of LotВҰ82317, as a possession.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 2:9: \xt Gen 19:37.\x*
\s1 The tribes near Kanaan
\p
\v 10 (The Emites had lived their previouslyвҖ”there were many of them, and theyВҰ82326 were tall and strong like the AnakitesВҰ82332.
\v 11 \add вүҲPeople also call both\add* the Emites andВҰ82340 the AnakitesВҰ82339, Refa'ites but the people of Moav call them Emites.
\v 12 The HoritesВҰ82347 had previously livedВҰ82354 in Seir, \add вүҲbut\add* Esau'sВҰ82350 descendants \add вүҲhad killed them andВҰ82345 taken over\add* their land, just like the Israelis did \add later\add* in the land thatВҰ82361 YahwehВҰ82364 had given them to possessВҰ82360.)
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add вүҲThen we crossedВҰ82369 the ZeredВҰ82374 brook as Yahweh had told us to do\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲIt had been\add* thirty-eight years since we first left Kadesh-Barnea until we cross the ZeredВҰ82395 brook, \add вүҲonce\add* thatВҰ82382 generationВҰ82404 of \add вүҲwarriors\add* had \add вүҲdied off\add*, just as YahwehВҰ82411 had \add вүҲtold\add* them.\x + \xo 2:14: \xt Num 14:28-35.\x*
\v 15 \add вүҲWhat's more, YahwehВҰ82417 had opposed them, so he'd caused them to die\add*.
\p
\v 16 вҖң\add вүҲAfter\add* all the \add вүҲenlistment-aged\add* menВҰ82432 had diedВҰ82434,
\v 17 YahwehВҰ82440 told me,
\v 18 вҖҳToday you must \add вүҲtravel through the Moav region\add*, \add near\add* ArВҰ82453,
\v 19 andВҰ82455 \add when\add* you approachВҰ82455 the Ammonite \add region\add*, don'tВҰ82459 irritate or fight them because I won'tВҰ82459 giveВҰ82469 you any of \add *their\add* land because I've givenВҰ82480 itВҰ82480 to Lot'sВҰ82479 descendantsВҰ82477 as a possession.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 2:19: \xt Gen 19:38.\x*
\p
\v 20 (Also, it's regardedВҰ82486 as the land of the Refa'ites, who the AmmonitesВҰ82495 call the ZamzummitesВҰ82498, who lived there in the past.
\v 21 \add They were\add* as numerousВҰ82502, and as tall and strong as the Anakites, \add вүҲbut\add* YahwehВҰ82506 destroyedВҰ82505 them \add вүҲin advance\add* of \add @the Anakites\add* who then dispossessedВҰ82508 them and livedВҰ82509 in their placeВҰ82510.
\v 22 He had done \add вүЎthe same thing\add* for Esau'sВҰ82515 descendantsВҰ82514 who live in SeirВҰ82517, when he destroyedВҰ82519 the HoritesВҰ82522 \add вүҲahead of them\add*, and they \add вүҲtook over their land\add* and \add still\add* live there to this dayВҰ82528.
\v 23 \add вүҲAlso\add* the Avvites who lived in villagesВҰ82533 as far \add south\add* as Azzah \add (GazaВҰ82536)\add* were destroyedВҰ82540 by the KaftoritesВҰ82537 who cameВҰ82538 from \add вүҲCrete\add*, andВҰ82531 thenВҰ82531 lived in theirВҰ82542 placeВҰ82542.)
\rem /s1 Defeat of Sihon King of Heshbon
\p
\v 24 вҖң\add Yahweh had told us,\add* вҖҳ\add вүҲGet ready\add* \add now\add* and go through the ArnonВҰ82550 river valley. I'll \add вүҲhelp you defeat\add* the AmoriteВҰ82560 King SihonВҰ82556 from HeshbonВҰ82559. \add вүҲAttack him\add* and beginВҰ82564 to \add вүҲtakeВҰ82565 over\add* his land.
\v 25 \add вүҲBeginning today\add*, I'll \add вүҲmake everyone, everywhere afraid\add* of you. \add вүҲEveryone who hears about you will be terrified and keep their distance from you\add*.вҖҷ
\s1 Defeat of King Sihon
\rem /s1 Victory over Sihon of Heshbon; Israel Defeats King Sihon; Defeat of King Sihon
\r (Num. 21:21-30)
\p
\v 26 вҖңThenВҰ82591 from the KedemotВҰ82594 wildernessВҰ82593, I sentВҰ82591 messengersВҰ82592 to King SihonВҰ82597 at HeshbonВҰ82599 with \add вүҲan offer\add* of peaceВҰ82601,
\v 27 вҖҳ\add вүҲPlease let us travel through your country. We'll stay on the road\add*
\v 28 \add вүҲif you'd be able to just sell us some\add* food and waterВҰ82618, then we could just walk right throughВҰ82625
\v 29 untilВҰ82639 we cross the Yarden river into the land thatВҰ82649 ourВҰ82652 godВҰ82652 YahwehВҰ82651 is giving us. Easu's descendantsВҰ82632 at SeirВҰ82635 \add allowed us through\add*, as did the Moabites at ArВҰ82638.вҖҷ
\p
\v 30 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* Heshbon'sВҰ82660 King SihonВҰ82658 wouldn't let us go through \add his country\add* because your godВҰ82667 YahwehВҰ82666 had hardened his spirit andВҰ82656 \add вүҲmade himВҰ82676 stubbornВҰ82665\add* so that you \add вүҲcould take his land\add*, \add which we still have\add* to this dayВҰ82678.
\p
\v 31 вҖңYahwehВҰ82683 told me, вҖҳListen, I've begunВҰ82686 to give SihonВҰ82691 and his land to you, \add вүҲso enter it and take it\add*.
\v 32 ThenВҰ82702 \add King\add* SihonВҰ82703 andВҰ82706 all his \add вүҲwarriors\add* came out against us at Yahats,
\v 33 \add вүҲbut\add* ourВҰ82714 godВҰ82714 YahwehВҰ82713 \add вүҲhelped us to defeat himВҰ82712, and we killed\add* Sihon and his son, and all his peopleВҰ82726.
\v 34 We capturedВҰ82728 all his citiesВҰ82733 at that time, and completelyВҰ82736 destroyedВҰ82736 men, womenВҰ82743 and childrenВҰ82744 in everyВҰ82739 cityВҰ82741, leaving no survivorsВҰ82747.
\v 35 Only the cattleВҰ82750 were taken as plunderВҰ82751 for ourselves, along with \add the goods\add* in the citiesВҰ82754 we capturedВҰ82756.
\v 36 Our godВҰ82783 YahwehВҰ82782 \add вүҲhelped us to capture\add* \add all their towns\add* from Aroer \add in the south\add* at the edge of the ArnonВҰ82765 River valleyВҰ82768, to the GileadВҰ82771 region \add in the north\add*вҖ”none of their cityВҰ82766 \add walls\add* were too highВҰ82776 for us.
\v 37 \add вүҲHowever,\add* youВҰ82794 didn'tВҰ82793 \add вүҲgo near the Ammonite region\add*, the Yabok river area, the hill countryВҰ82801 townsВҰ82800, or any other place where ourВҰ82807 godВҰ82807 YahwehВҰ82806 told us not to go.
\c 3
\s1 The defeat of Bashan's King Og
\rem /s1 Victory over Og of Bashan; Israel Conquers King Og; Defeat of Og King of Bashan; Defeat of King Og
\r (Num. 21:31-35)
\p
\v 1 вҖңThenВҰ82809 we turnedВҰ82809 andВҰ82809 went towards the BashanВҰ82812 \add вүҲregion\add* \add вүҲbut\add* KingВҰ82817 OgВҰ82814 came out with all his \add вүҲwarriors\add* to battleВҰ82823 against us at EdreiВҰ82824,
\v 2 \add вүҲbut\add* YahwehВҰ82827 told me, вҖҳDon't be afraid of him, because I've givenВҰ82835 him and all his people and his land \add вүҲover to you\add*, and you'll do the same to him that you did to the AmoriteВҰ82851 King SihonВҰ82849 who lived at HeshbonВҰ82854.вҖҷ
\p
\v 3 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ82856\add* our godВҰ82858 YahwehВҰ82857 also \add вүҲhelped us defeat\add* Bashan'sВҰ82866 King OgВҰ82863 and all his people, and we \add вүҲkilled\add* them all leaving no survivorsВҰ82879.
\v 4 We capturedВҰ82881 \add вүҲall\add* sixtyВҰ82897 of King Og'sВҰ82904 citiesВҰ82886 in the Argov regionВҰ82901 of BashanВҰ82905,
\v 5 \add even though\add* they were all fortifiedВҰ82911 with highВҰ82913 walls andВҰ82915 gatesВҰ82914 with bars. In addition, there were many ruralВҰ82918 villagesВҰ82917.
\v 6 We completelyВҰ82922 destroyed them like we'd done to Heshbon'sВҰ82928 King SihonВҰ82926вҖ”men, womenВҰ82934, andВҰ82922 childrenВҰ82935,
\v 7 but weВҰ82942 plunderedВҰ82942 all the cattleВҰ82939 andВҰ82940 the spoilВҰ82940 from the citiesВҰ82941 for ourselves.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ82945\add* at that timeВҰ82946, we tookВҰ82945 the land from twoВҰ82952 of the AmoriteВҰ82954 kingsВҰ82953 \add across on the easternВҰ82956 side\add* of the Yarden, from the ArnonВҰ82959 River \add in the south, up\add* to MtВҰ82962. HermonВҰ82963 \add in the north\add*
\v 9 (called Mt. ShiryonВҰ82968 by the Sidonians, andВҰ82969 Mt. SenirВҰ82973 by the AmoritesВҰ82969).
\v 10 \add вүЎWe captured\add* all the cities on the plain and all of the GileadВҰ82981 region, as well as BashanВҰ82984 as far \add east as\add* Salekah and EdreiВҰ82988 cities, which also belonged to Og'sВҰ82991 kingdomВҰ82990.вҖқ
\v 11 (Bashan'sВҰ82999 King OgВҰ82997 \add вүҲwas the last kingВҰ82998 who was a descendant\add* of the RefaitesВҰ83002. His bed (in RabbahВҰ83009 in the Ammonite region) was made out of iron and was \add вүҲfourВҰ83015 metres\add* long and \add вүҲtwo metres\add* wideВҰ83017.)
\s1 Land division on the eastern side
\rem /s1 The Tribes That Settled East of the Jordan; Land Division East of the Jordan; Division of the Land
\r (Num. 32:1-42)
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ83022\add* weВҰ83026 \add вүҲcaptured\add* that land at that timeВҰ83027вҖ”from AroerВҰ83029 by the ArnonВҰ83035 river, and half of the hill countryВҰ83037 of GileadВҰ83039 including itsВҰ83040 cities. I \add вүҲallocated\add* \add those areas\add* to the \add вүҲtribes of Reuven and Gad\add*.
\v 13 ThenВҰ83046 the rest of GileadВҰ83047 andВҰ83046 all of BashanВҰ83050 which had been Og'sВҰ83052 kingdomВҰ83051, I \add вүҲallocated\add* to half of the tribeВҰ83055 of Menashsheh.вҖқ
\p (That whole area is calledВҰ83064 the land of the RefaitesВҰ83066.
\v 14 Menashsheh's son Yair had \add вүҲcaptured\add* the Argov regionВҰ83077 as far as the bordersВҰ83081 with the GeshuritesВҰ83082 and MaacatitesВҰ83083, \add вүҲrenaming\add* BashanВҰ83091 to Havvot-Yair \add as it's still calledВҰ83084\add* to this dayВҰ83095.)
\p
\v 15 вҖңThenВҰ83098 I \add вүҲallocated\add* GileadВҰ83102 to Makir \add (a clan descended from Menashsheh)\add*,
\v 16 and I gave \add the southern\add* part of GileadВҰ83110 to the \add tribes of\add* Reuven and Gad, \add вүҲextending from\add* the ArnonВҰ83114 river (with the middleВҰ83115 of it being the boundary) to the YabbokВҰ83119 river which borders against the Ammonites.
\v 17 The borderВҰ83127 extends from the plainВҰ83125 along \add the east side of\add* the Yarden valley, from \add Lake\add* Kinneret \add in the north\add* to the Arabah lakeВҰ83130 (the Salt Sea \add or Dead Sea\add*) \add in the south\add* andВҰ83125 to the slopesВҰ83135 of Mt. PisgahВҰ83136 on the east.
\p
\v 18 вҖңThenВҰ83139 at that timeВҰ83141, I commandedВҰ83139 you saying, вҖҳYour godВҰ83145 YahwehВҰ83144 has givenВҰ83146 this land to you to possessВҰ83152 itВҰ83152, \add however\add* \add вүҲyour brave warriors\add* must cross over \add вүҲwith the other IsraeliВҰ83157 tribes\add* \add to help them conquer the western lands\add*.\x + \xo 3:18-20: \xt Josh 1:12-15.\x*
\v 19 \add вүҲLeave\add* your wivesВҰ83167 and childrenВҰ83168 and cattle (yes, I knowВҰ83170 you have many cattle) \add back here\add* in the cities thatВҰ83178 I've givenВҰ83179 you
\v 20 until Yahweh gives \add вүҲpeace\add* to your brotherВҰ83188 tribes like you have \add here\add*. \add вүҲOnce\add* they've taken possessionВҰ83206 of the land that your godВҰ83199 Yahweh is givenВҰ83208 them acrossВҰ83202 the river, then you'll all be able to returnВҰ83204 her to your own inheritance that I've \add вүҲallocated\add* to you.вҖҷ
\rem /s1 Moses Forbidden to Cross the Jordan; Moses Forbidden to Enter the Land
\p
\v 21 вҖңI \add вүҲalso\add* instructedВҰ83214 Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add* at that timeВҰ83215, saying, вҖҳ\add вүҲYou've\add* seenВҰ83219 everything that yourВҰ83218 godВҰ83226 Yahweh has done to those twoВҰ83227 kingsВҰ83228. Yahweh will do \add вүҲsimilar things\add* to all the kingdomsВҰ83236 that you'll be passing through \add over\add* there.
\v 22 Don't be afraid of them, because your godВҰ83249 YahwehВҰ83248 \add will be the one\add* fightingВҰ83251 for you all.
\s1 Mosheh is not permitted to enter Kanaan
\rem /s1 Moses Views Canaan from Pisgah; Moses Is Not Permitted to Enter Canaan
\p
\v 23 вҖңAt that timeВҰ83259, I \add вүҲpleadedВҰ83255\add* with YahwehВҰ83258,
\v 24 вҖҳMy masterВҰ83263 YahwehВҰ83263, you've begunВҰ83266 to show your servantВҰ83270 your greatness and your \add вүҲpower\add*. What \add other\add* godВҰ83281 in heavenВҰ83282 or on earthВҰ83283 is there that does works as \add вүҲgreat and powerful as what you've done\add*?
\v 25 Please let me cross the Yarden river and seeВҰ83293 the good land that's \add on the otherВҰ83299 side\add*вҖ”that good hill countryВҰ83301, and the LebanonВҰ83304 \add region\add*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ83306\add* Yahweh was angryВҰ83306 at me becauseВҰ83309 of \add вүҲwhat your parents had done\add*, andВҰ83306 he wouldn't listenВҰ83311 to me. \add вүҲInstead,\add* Yahweh told me, вҖҳEnough from youвҖ”don'tВҰ83310 talk to me about that againВҰ83324!
\v 27 Go up to the top of Mt. PisgahВҰ83331 and \add вүҲlook out\add* towards the west and the northВҰ83335 and the southВҰ83336 and the east. \add вүҲYes,\add* look with yourВҰ83333 eyes, because you won'tВҰ83342 be crossing this river.
\v 28 Instruct Yehoshua and encourageВҰ83353 him and strengthenВҰ83354 him, because \add вүҲhe's the one who'll lead the\add* peopleВҰ83360 across, and he'll \add вүҲlead\add* them to inheritВҰ83363 the land thatВҰ83368 you'll seeВҰ83369.вҖҷ
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ83371\add* we remainedВҰ83371 in the \add Yarden river\add* valleyВҰ83372 oppositeВҰ83373 Beyt-PeorВҰ83375.
\c 4
\s1 Mosheh encourages Yisrael to obey
\rem /s1 Moses Urges Israel to Obey; Moses Commands Obedience; Obedience Commanded; Moses Urges Israel to Be Obedient
\p
\v 1 вҖңNow YisraelВҰ83379, listenВҰ83380 to the instructions and regulationsВҰ83383 that I'll teachВҰ83389 you so that you'll all goВҰ83394 and possessВҰ83395 the land that YahwehВҰ83400, the godВҰ83401 of your ancestorsВҰ83402, is giving you, and liveВҰ83393 there.
\v 2 Don't add \add вүҲor subtract from what I tell\add* you, \add because you all need to follow\add* the instructions from your godВҰ83423 YahwehВҰ83422 thatВҰ83411 I'm telling you.\x + \xo 4:2: \xt Rev 22:18-19.\x*
\v 3 You've all seenВҰ83430 \add вүҲfor yourselves\add* what yourВҰ83451 godВҰ83450 YahwehВҰ83435 did at Beyt-PeorВҰ83447, when he destroyedВҰ83448 all the men who \add вүҲworshipped\add* \add BaalВҰ83445\add* there.\x + \xo 4:3: \xt Num 25:1-9.\x*
\v 4 \add вүҲHowever,\add* all of you who \add вүҲfaithfully continued to follow\add* your godВҰ83456 Yahweh are aliveВҰ83457 \add here\add* today.
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲListen\add*, I've taughtВҰ83463 you all the instructions and regulationsВҰ83465 that my godВҰ83470 YahwehВҰ83469 commandedВҰ83468 me to, for you all to \add вүҲfollow\add* in the land that you're aboutВҰ83477 to \add вүҲenter and occupy\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲFollow them faithfully\add* because \add вүҲthat will lead to\add* wisdom \add вүҲsuch that peopleВҰ83498 in other countries will notice that\add* this greatВҰ83503 nationВҰ83502 has wisdom andВҰ83481 understanding.
\v 7 What \add other\add* greatВҰ83510 nationВҰ83509 is there thatВҰ83511 has a god near to it like our god Yahweh is whenever we call \add вүҲout to him\add* \add for help\add*?
\v 8 \add вүҲAlso,\add* what other nationВҰ83528 has rules and regulationsВҰ83533 that are as \add вүҲsensible and fair\add* as these instructions that I'm giving to you all today?
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add вүҲBut\add* \add each of you must\add* take care to guard yourselfВҰ83547 and your \add вүҲvalues\add* in case you forgetВҰ83553 that you've seen and \add those past miracles\add* \add вүҲslip from your minds over the years to come\add*. \add Yes,\add* \add вүҲmake sure that you teach them to your children and your grand-children\add*,
\v 10 \add including\add* the dayВҰ83573 when youВҰ83575 stoodВҰ83575 \add вүҲin our godВҰ83578 Yahweh's presence\add* at \add Mt. Sinai\add* (Horev) when \add *he\add* told me, вҖҳAssemble the peopleВҰ83588 for me, and I'll make \add it so they can\add* hearВҰ83589 my wordsВҰ83592, so they'll learnВҰ83594 to \add вүҲhonour and respect for their entireВҰ83597 lifetimes,\add* and then teachВҰ83609 it to their childrenВҰ83608.вҖҷ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ83611\add* you all approached the mountain andВҰ83611 stoodВҰ83612 \add вүҲat its base\add* while it blazed with fireВҰ83617 that wentВҰ83611 up into the \add вүҲatmosphere\add* \add even though\add* the mountain was covered with dark, gloomy cloudsВҰ83623.\x + \xo 4:11-12: \xt Exo 19:16-18; Heb 12:18-19.\x*
\v 12 ThenВҰ83626 YahwehВҰ83627 spokeВҰ83626 to you from the middle of the flamesвҖ”you heard \add вүҲthe voiceВҰ83639 even though you couldn't see anyone\add*,
\v 13 andВҰ83641 he \add вүҲrevealed\add* to you the agreement that he \add вүҲdemands\add* you keep: the tenВҰ83650 commandsВҰ83651 that he wroteВҰ83652 onto twoВҰ83655 stoneВҰ83657 tabletsВҰ83656.\x + \xo 4:13: \xt Exo 31:18; 34:28; Deu 9:10.\x*
\v 14 At that timeВҰ83662, YahwehВҰ83661 told me to teachВҰ83664 you all the instructions and regulationsВҰ83666 so you'd be able to \add вүҲput them into practice\add* in the land that you're \add вүҲaboutВҰ83673 to enter and occupy\add*.\x + \xo 4:14: \xt Exo 21:1.\x*
\s1 Warnings about false gods
\rem /s1 Idolatry Forbidden; A Warning against Idolatry; Warning against Idolatry
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲNow remembering that\add* you didn'tВҰ83681 see any form at \add Mt. Sinai\add* (Horev) when YahwehВҰ83688 spokeВҰ83687 to you all from the middle of the fireВҰ83692,
\v 16 \add вүҲso don't corruptВҰ83696 yourselves\add* by making an idolВҰ83699 \add to be your god\add*вҖ”don't make anything in the likenessВҰ83704 of a man or a woman,\x + \xo 4:16: \xt Exo 20:4; Lev 26:1; Deu 5:8; 27:15.\x*
\v 17 or of any animalВҰ83712 that's on the earthВҰ83714 or bird that fliesВҰ83721 in the sky,\x + \xo 4:17-18a: \xt Rom 1:23.\x*
\v 18 or any \add вүҲreptile\add* thatВҰ83733 creepsВҰ83727 along the groundВҰ83728 or any fishВҰ83732 from the deep \add вүҲoceans\add*.
\v 19 Don't look up to the sky and be \add вүҲtempted\add* to bow down to the sunВҰ83747 or the moonВҰ83750 or the starsВҰ83753 and serve themвҖ”your godВҰ83764 YahwehВҰ83763 made them \add to serve\add* every peopleВҰ83767 group \add вүҲin the world\add*.
\v 20 YahwehВҰ83775 has broughtВҰ83776 you all out of the iron-smelting furnaceВҰ83778 of EgyptВҰ83780 to be a peopleВҰ83783 that would belong to him (as you are today),\x + \xo 4:20: \xt Exo 19:5; Deu 7:6; 14:2; 26:18; Tit 2:14; 1Pe 2:9.\x*
\v 21 \add but\add* thenВҰ83788 YahwehВҰ83788 got angryВҰ83789 at me because of \add вүҲyourВҰ83811 parents\add* andВҰ83788 determined that I would never enter the land that he's giving to all of you.\x + \xo 4:21: \xt Num 20:12.\x*
\v 22 \add вүҲInstead,\add* I'll dieВҰ83818 here in this place. I won'tВҰ83821 cross the Yarden river, but you will, and then you'll all takeВҰ83828 possessionВҰ83828 of that goodВҰ83832 land.
\v 23 Take \add great\add* care that you all don't forgetВҰ83839 the agreement with your god Yahweh. Don't make any idols for yourselves in the form of anythingВҰ83852 that your god Yahweh has ordered you all \add not to\add*,
\v 24 because your god YahwehВҰ83859 is a consumingВҰ83862 fireВҰ83861вҖ”he's a god who gets jealousВҰ83865.\x + \xo 4:24: \xt Heb 12:29.\x*
\p
\v 25 \add Even\add* after you've had children and \add вүҲgrandchildren\add* and then grown old in the land, don't make an idol in the form of anythingВҰ83880, and don't be corruptВҰ83876 or do evil \add things\add* that your god YahwehВҰ83884 \add вүҲdislikes and so which will make him\add* angry.
\v 26 \add If you do\add*, I call the heavensВҰ83894 and the earth as witnessesВҰ83889 against you all today, that you'd die \add over there\add* in the land that you're crossing the river to possessВҰ83912. You wouldn't liveВҰ83915 there very longВҰ83915, but \add instead would end up\add* getting destroyed.
\v 27 ThenВҰ83922 YahwehВҰ83923 would scatterВҰ83922 \add вүҲthe remainder\add* among the nationsВҰ83929 whereВҰ83930 \add ?вүҲyou'd remain as a small minority\add*.\x + \xo 4:27-28: \xt Deu 28:36.\x*
\v 28 There you would \add ?be forced to\add* worship godsВҰ83939 thatВҰ83945 humansВҰ83942 have made out of wood or stoneВҰ83944 andВҰ83936 whichВҰ83945 can'tВҰ83946 seeВҰ83948, hearВҰ83950, smellВҰ83954, or eatВҰ83952.
\v 29 From thereВҰ83957 you'll search for your godВҰ83961 YahwehВҰ83960, and you'll find him when you search for him with \add вүҲdetermination and total sincerity\add*.\x + \xo 4:29: \xt Jer 29:13.\x*
\v 30 \add вүҲIt's in the future when you end up in distressВҰ83972\add* \add there\add* that you'll returnВҰ83980 to your godВҰ83984 YahwehВҰ83983 and listen to \add вүҲwhat he tells\add* \add you\add*,
\v 31 because your god YahwehВҰ83991 is a merciful god. He won't abandonВҰ83994 you or destroyВҰ83996 you, and he won't forgetВҰ83998 what he promised to your ancestorsВҰ84002.
\rem /s1 The Lord Is God; There Is Only One God
\p
\v 32 Now, pleaseВҰ84010, consider past times before you were alive, i.e., from when GodВҰ84022 first createdВҰ84021 people here on the earthВҰ84027. You could search \add вүҲall through humanВҰ84024 history and you wouldn't find anything else as incredible\add* \add as what Yahweh has done for yourВҰ84016 ancestors\add*.
\v 33 \add вүҲHas any other peopleВҰ84043 group\add* heardВҰ84052 GodВҰ84045 talkingВҰ84046 from the middle of a fireВҰ84049 like you have, and then livedВҰ84054 \add to tell about it\add*?
\v 34 Or is their any other nation that GodВҰ84059 has attemptedВҰ84058 to take out from the middle of another nation, using miracles and war, and power and terrifying actions, like your god YahwehВҰ84081 did for you all when you were in EgyptВҰ84083?
\v 35 YouВҰ84092 were shownВҰ84087 \add all that\add* so you'd knowВҰ84088 that YahwehВҰ84090 is \add вүҲthe one and only\add* god.\x + \xo 4:35: \xt Mrk 12:32.\x*
\v 36 He allowed you to hear his voiceВҰ84104 from the skiesВҰ84100 to instruct you, and on earthВҰ84108 you heardВҰ84115 his wordsВҰ84114 from the incredible fire that he \add вүҲshowedВҰ84109\add* you.
\v 37 Because he lovedВҰ84121 your ancestorsВҰ84124, he choseВҰ84125 theirВҰ84126 \add вүҲdescendantsВҰ84126\add* \add as his people\add* and used his \add powerВҰ84130 and strength to lead\add* you out of EgyptВҰ84132
\v 38 \add and then\add* to driveВҰ84134 out nationsВҰ84135 ahead of you that were greaterВҰ84136 and more powerful than youвҖ”bringingВҰ84140 you here today so that you could occupy theirВҰ84146 land as yourВҰ84139 inheritanceВҰ84147.
\v 39 SoВҰ84151 today you should acknowledgeВҰ84151 that YahwehВҰ84158 is god of the heavensВҰ84161 aboveВҰ84162 and the earthВҰ84165 belowВҰ84166, and there'sВҰ84167 no \add вүҲother god\add*.
\v 40 Follow his instructions and \add вүЎobey\add* his regulationsВҰ84173 that I'm \add вүҲgiving\add* you today so that \add вүҲeverything\add* will go well for you and your descendants, and so that you'll live a long time in the land that your godВҰ84197 YahwehВҰ84196 is giving you \add вүҲas a permanent possession\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The refuge cities
\rem /s1 Eastern Cities of Refuge; The Cities of Refuge East of the Jordan; Cities of Refuge; Cities of Refuge East of the Jordan
\p
\v 41 Then MoshehВҰ84207 \add (MosesВҰ84207)\add* selected threeВҰ84208 citiesВҰ84209 on \add вүҲthat easternВҰ84210\add* side of the Yarden\x + \xo 4:41-43: \xt Josh 20:8-9.\x*
\v 42 \add вүҲso that anyoneВҰ84236 who accidentally killedВҰ84217 another person\add* could flee to one of those citiesВҰ84239 and \add вүҲbe safe\add*:
\v 43 BezerВҰ84245 in the wildernessВҰ84246 for the \add вүҲtribe of Reuben\add*, RamotВҰ84253 in GileadВҰ84254 for the \add вүҲtribe of Gad\add*, and GolanВҰ84258 in the BashanВҰ84259 region for the \add вүҲtribe of ManassehВҰ84260\add*.
\s1 Giving the instructions
\rem /s1 Introduction to the Giving of God's Law; Introduction to the Law; Transition to the Second Address
\p
\v 44 TheseВҰ84270 are the instructions thatВҰ84264 MoshehВҰ84267 \add (MosesВҰ84267)\add* gave to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ84269\add*,
\v 45 \add вүҲincluding\add* all the instructions, rules, and regulationsВҰ84274 thatВҰ84276 MoshehВҰ84278 had told them when theyВҰ84283 leftВҰ84283 EgyptВҰ84284,
\v 46 when they were in the valleyВҰ84288 \add east\add* of the Yarden \add River\add*. They were across from the town of Beyt-PeorВҰ84291, in the land that the AmoriteВҰ84295 King SihonВҰ84293 (who lived in HeshbonВҰ84298 \add city\add*) had ruled. (MoshehВҰ84301 and the \add other\add* \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ84303\add* had defeatedВҰ84300 them when they cameВҰ84304 out of EgyptВҰ84305.)
\v 47 They had taken possessionВҰ84307 of his land, as well as the land of Bashan'sВҰ84318 King OgВҰ84315вҖ”the twoВҰ84319 AmoriteВҰ84321 kingsВҰ84320 from the \add вүҲeastern side\add* of the YardenвҖ”
\v 48 from Aroer \add city in the south\add* along the edge of the ArnonВҰ84335 valley, andВҰ84336 as far north as Mt. SionВҰ84339 (\add normally\add* called Mt. HermonВҰ84341)
\v 49 and the entireВҰ84343 plainВҰ84345 east of the Yarden River, \add extending\add* to the Sea of the Arabah \add (the Dead/Salt seaВҰ84350)\add* and \add east to\add* the slopesВҰ84353 of Mt. PisgahВҰ84354.
\c 5
\s1 The ten rules
\rem /s1 The Ten Commandments; Moses' second discourse
\r (Exo. 20:1-17)
\p
\v 1 Then MoshehВҰ84358 \add (MosesВҰ84358)\add* \add вүҲsummoned\add* all Yisrael and told them, вҖңYisrael, listenВҰ84366 to the instructions and the regulationsВҰ84370 thatВҰ84374 I will speakВҰ84376 in your ears today, and then you must learnВҰ84379 them and be carefulВҰ84381 to followВҰ84382 them.
\v 2 Our godВҰ84385 YahwehВҰ84384 made an agreement with us at Horev \add (Mt. Sinai)\add*.
\v 3 \add *He\add* didn't make that agreement with ourВҰ84394 ancestorsВҰ84394, but with us \add ourselves\add*вҖ”those of us here today, \add i.e., with\add* \em living\em* people.
\v 4 YahwehВҰ84414 spokeВҰ84413 to you from the middle of the fireвҖ”face to face with you all on that mountainВҰ84416.
\v 5 \add Well,\add* \add вүҲit was me who\add* stood between all of you and Yahweh at that timeВҰ84426, to reveal Yahweh's messageВҰ84432 to you, because you were afraidВҰ84435 \add вүҲto approach\add* the fireВҰ84437, and you all didn'tВҰ84438 go up the mountainВҰ84441. \add Yahweh\add* said:
\p
\v 6 вҖҳIВҰ84445 am yourВҰ84447 godВҰ84447 YahwehВҰ84446 who broughtВҰ84449 youВҰ84449 all out of EgyptВҰ84451вҖ”from the slave-house \add there\add*.
\li1
\v 7 \add вүҲDon't have any other god, other than me.\add*
\li1
\v 8 Don't \add вүҲcarve\add* any figure for yourselfВҰ84474 \add вүҲthatВҰ84482 looks like\add* anything in the sky or on the ground, or in the waterВҰ84495 below the ground.\x + \xo 5:8-9: \xt Lev 26:1; Deu 4:15-18; 27:15.\x*
\v 9 Don't bow down to them or \add вүҲserveВҰ84509\add* them, because I, your god YahwehВҰ84513, am a jealousВҰ84516 god. I'll \add вүҲpunish the descendants\add* of those who hate me, even for three or four generations,\x + \xo 5:9-10: \xt Exo 34:6-7; Num 14:18; Deu 7:9-10.\x*
\v 10 \add вүҲbut\add* showingВҰ84532 loyalВҰ84534 commitment to thousandsВҰ84536 \add вүЎof generations\add* of those who loveВҰ84538 me andВҰ84539 obey myВҰ84538 instructions.
\li1
\v 11 Don'tВҰ84556 use the name of your godВҰ84551 YahwehВҰ84550 idly, because \add *I\add* won'tВҰ84544 \add вүҲfail to punish people who do that\add*.
\li1
\v 12 Observe the Rest Day \add on Saturday\add* to sanctify itВҰ84578, as yourВҰ84585 godВҰ84585 YahwehВҰ84583 commandedВҰ84581 youВҰ84581.\x + \xo 5:12: \xt Exo 16:23-30; 31:12-14.\x*
\v 13 There's sixВҰ84589 daysВҰ84591 for labouringВҰ84593 andВҰ84595 doing all yourВҰ84600 workВҰ84600,
\v 14 \add вүҲbut\add* the seventhВҰ84604 day is a rest day \add dedicated\add* to your god YahwehВҰ84608. Don't do any work on that day: not you or your children or your slaves, or \add using\add* any of your cattle, nor any foreigner living \add вүҲwith you\add*вҖ”your slaves can rest like you.
\v 15 Remember that you were a slaveВҰ84643 in EgyptВҰ84649, and that your god Yahweh \add вүҲtook action and used my power\add* to take you out of thereВҰ84657. Therefore your god Yahweh commandsВҰ84669 you to keep the Rest Day.
\li1
\v 16 Honour your father and motherВҰ84688 as your god Yahweh has commandedВҰ84690 you, so that \add вүҲyou'll have a long life\add* and \add вүҲso that everything will go well in the country\add* that your god Yahweh is giving you.\x + \xo 5:16: a \xt Deu 27:16; Mat 15:4; 19:19; Mrk 7:10; 10:19; Luk 18:20; Eph 6:2; \xo b \xt Eph 6:3.\x*
\li1
\v 17 Don't murderВҰ84712 \add >anyone\add*.
\li1
\v 18 Don't commitВҰ84718 adulteryВҰ84718.
\li1
\v 19 Don't stealВҰ84724 \add >anything\add*.
\li1
\v 20 Don't \add вүҲtell lies in court about anyone\add*.
\li1
\v 21 Don't covetВҰ84737 your neighbour'sВҰ84752 \add вүҲspouse\add*, or their houseВҰ84743 or land, or their slaves or livestock, or \add вүҲanything else that they own\add*.вҖҷ\x + \xo 5:21: \xt Rom 7:7; 13:9.\x*
\rem /s1 Moses the Mediator of God's Will
\p
\v 22 YahwehВҰ84760 spokeВҰ84759 those wordsВҰ84757 in a \add вүҲbooming\add* voiceВҰ84771 from the middle of the fireВҰ84768, the cloudВҰ84769, and the gloom, to all your assemblyВҰ84765 on the mountainВҰ84766. \add вүҲThat was all he said\add*, and he wroteВҰ84775 \add @those instructions\add* on twoВҰ84778 stoneВҰ84780 tabletsВҰ84779 and gaveВҰ84781 them to me.\x + \xo 5:22-27: \xt Heb 12:18-19.\x*
\s1 The people's fear
\rem /s1 The People's Fear
\r (Exo. 20:18-21)
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ84784 when you heardВҰ84785 the voiceВҰ84788 \add coming out\add* from the darknessВҰ84790 and the mountainВҰ84791 was blazing with fireВҰ84793, thenВҰ84784 all the heads of your tribesВҰ84799 and the eldersВҰ84800 approachedВҰ84794 me
\v 24 and said, вҖңListen, our god YahwehВҰ84805 \add вүҲdemonstrated his greatnessВҰ84812 and power when we heardВҰ84816 him speakВҰ84824\add* from the fireВҰ84818. Today, we've realised that GodВҰ84806 talks to people, and that they can stay alive.
\v 25 \add вүҲHowever,\add* we're \add still\add* afraid that we'll dieвҖ”getting burnt up in that intense fireВҰ84836 if we continue hearing our godВҰ84849 Yahweh's voiceВҰ84847,
\v 26 because \add вүҲwhen has anybody else ever heardВҰ84859 the voiceВҰ84860 of the livingВҰ84862 godВҰ84861 speakВҰ84863 to them from the middle of a blazing fireВҰ84866 andВҰ84868 they\add* \add still\add* livedВҰ84868?
\v 27 You \add Mosheh (Moses),\add* \add вүҲgo\add* and listen to everything that our god YahwehВҰ84878 says, and tell us everything that he tells you, and we'll listen \add to that\add* and obey it.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 YahwehВҰ84896 heard \add вүҲyou all say thatВҰ84913\add* to me, and told me, вҖҳI've heard what they said to you and it's a good idea.
\v 29 \add вүҲIf only they were sincere in saying that they'd honour me and always follow all my instructions so that everything would goВҰ84941 well for them and their descendants forever\add*.
\v 30 Go and tell them to returnВҰ84949 to their tentsВҰ84951,
\v 31 \add вүҲbut\add* thenВҰ84953 come \add вүҲback up\add* here and I'll \add вүҲgiveВҰ84971\add* you all the instructions and rules and regulationsВҰ84963 for you to teachВҰ84966 them, \add вүҲso they can follow them\add* in the land thatВҰ84965 I'm giving them to take possessionВҰ84973 of.вҖҷ
\p
\v 32 Make sure that you do everything that your godВҰ84980 YahwehВҰ84979 has commandedВҰ84978вҖ”don'tВҰ84982 \add вүҲdeviate from any of them\add*.
\v 33 \add вүҲFollow all the instructions from\add* your godВҰ84993 YahwehВҰ84992, and then you'll all liveВҰ84997 and \add вүҲthings will go well\add* and you'll all \add вүҲbe able to occupy thatВҰ84990 land for a long time\add*.
\c 6
\s1 Always honour Yahweh
\rem /s1 A Call for Wholehearted Commitment; Love the Lord Your god; The Great Commandment
\p
\v 1 These are the instructions and rules and regulationsВҰ85008 that your godВҰ85013 YahwehВҰ85012 orderedВҰ85011 me to teachВҰ85014 you all, to do in the land that you're aboutВҰ85020 to enter and occupy.
\v 2 \add *He\add* wants you all to honour him, to follow all his instructions, and to keep his rules that I'm teaching you and your descendants so that your time \add on the land\add* will be prolonged.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ85052,\add* listenВҰ85052 YisraelВҰ85053 and \add вүҲfollow\add* carefullyВҰ85054 so that itВҰ85057 will goВҰ85057 well for you and that you'll \add вүҲincrease in population\add* in that \add вүҲvery fertile\add* land as yourВҰ85066 ancestors' godВҰ85065, YahwehВҰ85064, \add вүҲpromised\add*.
\p
\v 4 ListenВҰ85079 YisraelВҰ85076: YahwehВҰ85077 \add вүҲalone\add* is our god\x + \xo 6:4: \xt Mrk 12:29.\x*
\v 5 and you should loveВҰ85084 your godВҰ85087 YahwehВҰ85086 with \add вүҲyour whole mindВҰ85090, your entireВҰ85088 being\add*, and all your strength.\x + \xo 6:5: \xt Mat 22:37; Mrk 12:30; Luk 10:27.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲAlways be considering\add* theseВҰ85100 instructions thatВҰ85101 I'm \add вүҲgiving\add* youВҰ85103 today,\x + \xo 6:6-9: \xt Deu 11:18-20.\x*
\v 7 and diligentlyВҰ85109 teachВҰ85109 them to your childrenВҰ85110, and talkВҰ85111 about them when you're sitting at home and when you're \add вүҲout walking\add*, when you lie down and when you get up.
\v 8 Your \add вүҲhands should always be applying them\add* andВҰ85120 your \add вүҲminds should always be evaluating them\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲCarve\add* them onto your doorpostsВҰ85133 at home, andВҰ85130 on your \add city\add* gatesВҰ85135.
\s1 Warnings against disobeying
\rem /s1 Warning against Disobedience; Caution against Disobedience
\p
\v 10 Your godВҰ85143 YahwehВҰ85142 promised your ancestorsВҰ85149 AbrahamВҰ85150,\x + \xo 6:10: \xt Gen 12:7.\x* Yitshak,\x + \xo 6:10: \xt Gen 26:3.\x* and Yakov,\x + \xo 6:10: \xt Gen 28:13.\x* that he'd giveВҰ85153 you largeВҰ85156, \add вүҲprosperous\add* citiesВҰ85155 that you didn'tВҰ85159 have to build,
\v 11 housesВҰ85163 full of everyВҰ85165 goodВҰ85167 thingВҰ85167 that you didn't have to collect, wells that you didn't have to dig, and vineyardsВҰ85178 and oliveВҰ85179 grovesВҰ85179 that you didn't have to plantВҰ85183. You'll be able to eatВҰ85184 and be satisfied,
\v 12 \add but\add* be sure to never forgetВҰ85191 that it was YahwehВҰ85194 who rescued you from slaveryВҰ85200 in EgyptВҰ85198.
\v 13 You must honour yourВҰ85205 godВҰ85205 YahwehВҰ85204 and only serveВҰ85208 himВҰ85207 and only make promises using his nameВҰ85209.\x + \xo 6:13: \xt Mat 4:10; Luk 4:8.\x*
\v 14 Don't go \add вүҲtrying to follow\add* otherВҰ85216 godsвҖ”the gods of the surrounding countriesвҖ”
\v 15 because yourВҰ85227 god YahwehВҰ85225 who lives among you is a jealousВҰ85224 god. YouВҰ85233 wouldn't want \add *him\add* to get angry with you and \add вүҲtotally\add* destroyВҰ85236 you.
\p
\v 16 Don't test \add the patience of\add* your godВҰ85247 YahwehВҰ85246 \add again\add* like you all did \add over water\add* at MassahВҰ85250.\x + \xo 6:16: a \xt Mat 4:7; Luk 4:12; \xo b \xt Exo 17:1-7.\x*
\v 17 BeВҰ85257 sure to follow all \add *his\add* instructions and rules and regulationsВҰ85260 thatВҰ85261 he's \add вүҲgiven\add* youВҰ85262.
\v 18 DoВҰ85281 what YahwehВҰ85268 says is rightВҰ85265 and good so that things will go well for you and you'll be able to enter the good land that \add *he\add* promised to your ancestorsВҰ85282 and take possessionВҰ85273 of itвҖ”
\v 19 drivingВҰ85284 out all yourВҰ85289 enemiesВҰ85289 from \add вүҲthat land\add* just as YahwehВҰ85293 has said.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲIn the future\add* when yourВҰ85299 children ask youВҰ85298, вҖҳWhy did our godВҰ85309 YahwehВҰ85308 our godВҰ85309 commandВҰ85307 us to obey all these rules and decreesВҰ85303?вҖҷ
\v 21 thenВҰ85312 you can tell them, вҖҳWe were Far-oh's slavesВҰ85314 in EgyptВҰ85317, \add вүҲbut\add* YahwehВҰ85319 \add вүҲused his incredible power to get us out of there\add*.
\v 22 \add *He\add* \add вүҲdid many kinds of miracles that devastated that Egyptian king andВҰ85324 his whole householdВҰ85335\add*,
\v 23 thenВҰ85338 he took us out of thereВҰ85340, so he could bringВҰ85342 us here to giveВҰ85344 us the land thatВҰ85349 he'd promised to our ancestorsВҰ85351.
\v 24 YahwehВҰ85354 orderedВҰ85353 us to \add вүҲfollow\add* all theseВҰ85361 instructions to \add demonstrate\add* that we honour him so that things will go well for us andВҰ85353 \add вүҲhe'll protect ourВҰ85366 nation as he's doingВҰ85355 now\add*.
\v 25 Our godВҰ85392 YahwehВҰ85391 \add вүҲwill declare us to be innocent of wrong\add* if weВҰ85382 obey everything that he's instructedВҰ85394 us.вҖҷ
\c 7
\s1 Warning Yisrael's descendants
\rem /s1 Driving Out the Nations; The Lord's Own People; The Privilege of Holiness; A Chosen People
\r (Exo. 34:11-16)
\p
\v 1 When yourВҰ85416 godВҰ85400 YahwehВҰ85399 bringsВҰ85398 you into the land which you'reВҰ85406 going to possessВҰ85410, he'll driveВҰ85411 out many people groups \add вүҲahead of you\add*: the HittitesВҰ85417, GirgashitesВҰ85418, AmoritesВҰ85419, Canaanites, PerizzitesВҰ85421, HivitesВҰ85422, and the YevusitesвҖ”sevenВҰ85424 \add вүҲsocieties\add* that are more powerful than yourselves.\x + \xo 7:1: \xt Acts 13:19.\x*
\v 2 When your godВҰ85432 YahwehВҰ85431 \add вүҲenables you to defeatВҰ85434\add* them, you \add вүҲmust killВҰ85435 them all\add*. \add вүҲYou must make no agreement with them\add*, andВҰ85430 you \add вүҲmust not act mercifully toward\add* them.
\v 3 Don't intermarryВҰ85447 with them: don'tВҰ85446 allow your daughters to marry their sons, or your sons to marry \add any of\add* their daughters
\rem /r (Deuteronomy 7.12-24; 28.1-14)
\v 4 because they'd turnВҰ85462 your sonsВҰ85465 away from me, and they'd \add end up\add* serving otherВҰ85469 godsВҰ85468. Then YahwehВҰ85473 \add вүҲwould become very angry\add* with you all and would quicklyВҰ85476 destroyВҰ85475 you.
\v 5 \add вүҲWhat you all should do\add* to \add @those people\add* is to breakВҰ85488 down their altarsВҰ85485 and smash their \add stone\add* pillarsВҰ85487, cut their Asherah polesВҰ85489 to pieces, and burnВҰ85492 up their idolsВҰ85491.\x + \xo 7:5: \xt Deu 12:3.\x*
\v 6 \add YouВҰ85504 must do thatВҰ85512\add* because you're a group of people who \add вүҲbelong only to\add* your god YahwehВҰ85499. \add *He's\add* chosenВҰ85502 you \add вүҲfrom all the people groups in the world to be his own special people\add*.\x + \xo 7:6: \xt Exo 19:5; Deu 4:20; 14:2; 26:18; Tit 2:14; 1Pe 2:9.\x*
\p
\v 7 YahwehВҰ85525 lovedВҰ85524 you andВҰ85527 choseВҰ85527 you all, not becauseВҰ85520 you were the \add вүҲmost populous\add* nation (in fact, you were the smallest of all the nations),
\v 8 but because Yahweh loves you all and because he keptВҰ85541 the promise thatВҰ85548 he'd made to your ancestorsВҰ85550. Yahweh \add вүҲused his power to rescue\add* you all from the slaveryВҰ85558 \add imposed by\add* Egypt'sВҰ85563 King Far-oh.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ85565 remember\add* that your god YahwehВҰ85568 is GodВҰ85569вҖ”the faithfulВҰ85573 god who keepsВҰ85574 agreements and \add displays\add* loyalВҰ85576 commitment toward a thousandВҰ85581 generationsВҰ85582 of those who love him and \add вүҲobey what he's commandedВҰ85579\add*.\x + \xo 7:9-10: \xt Exo 20:5-6; 34:6-7; Num 14:18; Deu 5:9-10.\x*
\v 10 \add вүҲHowever,\add* to those who hateВҰ85585 him, he won'tВҰ85590 hesitate to pay them back with punishment andВҰ85584 destructionВҰ85589.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ85600\add* be sure to obey all the instructions, rules, andВҰ85600 regulationsВҰ85606 thatВҰ85610 I'mВҰ85611 giving youВҰ85612 today.
\s1 Blessings for obedience
\rem /s1 The Blessings of Obedience; Blessings for Obedience
\r (Deu. 28:1-14)
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲIf you pay attention to theseВҰ85623 instructions and always obey them\add*, then your godВҰ85629 YahwehВҰ85628 will keep the agreement thatВҰ85637 he promised to your ancestorsВҰ85639 and \add continue to display his\add* loyalВҰ85636 commitment to you,\x + \xo 7:12-16: \xt Deu 11:13-17.\x*
\v 13 and he will loveВҰ85641 you and bless you. \add вүҲHe'll grant you many children and make your farming productive\add*, \add producing\add* grainВҰ85651 and \add вүҲgrapes for\add* wine, and \add olive\add* oil. Your cattle and sheep and goats will multiplyВҰ85643 on the land that he promised your ancestorsВҰ85664 that he'd giveВҰ85665 you.
\v 14 You'll be blessed \add вүҲmore than any other peopleВҰ85672 group\add*. \add вүҲAll of youВҰ85669 will be able to have children, and all of yourВҰ85679 livestockВҰ85679 will produce offspring\add*.
\v 15 YahwehВҰ85682 will keep sicknessВҰ85686 away from you. All those horrible diseasesВҰ85689 thatВҰ85692 \add @your ancestors\add* saw in EgyptВҰ85690 won'tВҰ85694 affect you, but \add instead\add* he'll give them to those who hateВҰ85700 you.
\v 16 You must destroy all the peoplesВҰ85707 that your godВҰ85710 YahwehВҰ85709 \add вүҲgives you victory over\add*вҖ”\add вүҲdon't allow yourselves\add* to pity them, andВҰ85702 don't serveВҰ85719 theirВҰ85722 godsВҰ85722 because \add вүҲthat would end up trapping you\add*.
\p
\v 17 Don't \add вүҲtell yourselves that because those groups have many more people than you, that you won't be able to drive them out\add*.
\v 18 YouВҰ85752 mustn't be afraidВҰ85742 of them, but rather you should think back to what your godВҰ85751 YahwehВҰ85750 did to Far-oh and to all EgyptВҰ85755.
\v 19 \add Remember\add* the \add вүҲterrible plagues\add* that you saw, and the \add вүҲpowerful miracles that your god YahwehВҰ85771 used\add* to bring you out. That's what \add *he'll\add* do to the peopleВҰ85780 groups that you'reВҰ85783 \add still\add* afraidВҰ85784 of now.
\v 20 What's more, \add after that\add* yourВҰ85793 godВҰ85793 YahwehВҰ85792 will sendВҰ85791 hornetsВҰ85790 against any who are left or in hiding, untilВҰ85795 \add вүҲthey're all destroyed\add*.
\v 21 Don't be afraid of those people, because yourВҰ85809 god YahwehВҰ85807 will be with you. He's a powerful god \add вүҲthat people are in awe of\add*.
\v 22 \add *He'll\add* drive those people groups out bit by bitвҖ”\add вүҲdon'tВҰ85824 try to destroy them all at once or else the wild animalsВҰ85832 would multiply up andВҰ85814 cause problems\add*.
\v 23 Your godВҰ85837 YahwehВҰ85836 will \add вүҲenable you to defeat\add* \add @those people groups\add* andВҰ85839 \add вүҲcause them to panic\add* untilВҰ85842 theyВҰ85843 are destroyedВҰ85843.
\v 24 He'll \add вүҲenable you to defeat\add* their kingsВҰ85846 andВҰ85845 their names \add вүҲwill be forgotten from history\add*. No one will be able to standВҰ85856 against you untilВҰ85859 you \add finally\add* destroyВҰ85860 them.
\v 25 You must burnВҰ85865 theirВҰ85864 idols in a fireВҰ85866вҖ”don'tВҰ85867 \add вүҲbe tempted to takeВҰ85873 any goldВҰ85871 or silverВҰ85870 decorations off them\add* in case you get trapped by it, because your godВҰ85881 YahwehВҰ85880 \add вүҲhates every part of those idols\add*.
\v 26 Don't take any of those disgusting \add idols\add* into your homes or \add вүҲyou too might become a target for destruction\add*. You \add вүҲshould hate andВҰ85884 detest them because they're destined for destruction\add*.
\c 8
\s1 The productive land to be possessed
\rem /s1 A Warning Not to Forget God in Prosperity; A Good Land to Be Possessed; A Call to Remember and Obey; Do Not Forget the Lord
\p
\v 1 You must consistently follow the instructions that I'm givingВҰ85911 you today, so that you all can enter and occupy the land that YahwehВҰ85926 promised to yourВҰ85911 ancestorsВҰ85927, and liveВҰ85916 \add there\add* and multiply.
\v 2 Remember the wayВҰ85934 thatВҰ85935 your godВҰ85938 YahwehВҰ85937 led you these fortyВҰ85940 years in the wildernessВҰ85942 in order to humbleВҰ85944 youвҖ”to test you to knowВҰ85946 whetherВҰ85951 or not \add вүҲyou were sincere about obeying his instructions\add*.
\v 3 He humbledВҰ85958 you \add вүҲby\add* making you hungryВҰ85959 andВҰ85958 feedingВҰ85960 you \add some\add* stuff that neither you nor your ancestorsВҰ85972 had heard of, in order to teach you that people don'tВҰ85967 just need food, but can only \add properly\add* live \add вүҲby following what YahwehВҰ85991 says\add*.\x + \xo 8:3: \xt Mat 4:4; Luk 4:4.\x*
\v 4 For the \add entire\add* fortyВҰ86003 years, your clothes didn't wear out and your feetВҰ85999 didn't swellВҰ86001 up \add from walking in the desert\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲDon't forget\add* that yourВҰ86019 godВҰ86018 YahwehВҰ86017 disciplines youВҰ86019, just like a \add вүҲhuman father\add* disciplines his children.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ86021\add* follow yourВҰ86026 godВҰ86026 Yahweh's instructions. \add вүҲLive how he's told you\add*, andВҰ86029 \add always\add* honour him
\v 7 because \add *he's\add* bringingВҰ86035 youВҰ86035 into a goodВҰ86039 landвҖ”a land with streams and fountains, and springs \add both\add* in the valleysВҰ86046 and in the hillsВҰ86047.
\v 8 \add It's\add* a land with wheatВҰ86050 and barleyВҰ86051, grapevines and figВҰ86053 trees, pomegranatesВҰ86054 and oliveВҰ86057 treesВҰ86053, and honeyВҰ86059вҖ”
\v 9 a land with \add вүҲplenty of food where\add* you won'tВҰ86063 lack anythingВҰ86072. \add вүҲThere's iron in the rocksВҰ86076, and copperВҰ86080 in the hillsВҰ86078\add*.
\v 10 You'll eatВҰ86082 and be full, and you'll \add вүҲthank\add* yourВҰ86088 godВҰ86088 YahwehВҰ86087 for the goodВҰ86092 land thatВҰ86093 he's givenВҰ86094 you.
\s1 Warnings against forgetting Yahweh
\rem /s1 Warnings against Forgetting the Lord
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲBe careful not\add* to forgetВҰ86102 yourВҰ86114 godВҰ86106 YahwehВҰ86105 by failing to follow his instructions and rules and regulationsВҰ86111 thatВҰ86112 I'm telling you today.\x + \xo 8:11-16: \xt Josh 13:5-6.\x*
\v 12 \add Watch out when\add* you eatВҰ86119 and \add вүҲfeel\add* satisfiedВҰ86120, and you've built goodВҰ86122 housesВҰ86121 and are living in them,
\v 13 and your herdsВҰ86126 and flocksВҰ86127 have increased, and you've accumulated goldВҰ86130 and silverВҰ86129, and everything you have has multipliedВҰ86128.
\v 14 \add That's when it would be easy to\add* \add вүҲbecomeВҰ86140 proudВҰ86140\add* andВҰ86140 forgetВҰ86142 yourВҰ86147 godВҰ86146 YahwehВҰ86145 who broughtВҰ86147 youВҰ86147 \add вүҲout of slaveryВҰ86151 in\add* EgyptВҰ86149.
\v 15 He led you through that vast, treacherous wildernessВҰ86154вҖ”\add the home of\add* \add вүҲpoisonous\add* snakesВҰ86158 and scorpionsВҰ86161, and \add вүҲdesert land without\add* water, \add then\add* he \add вүҲmade water flow out of solid\add* rockВҰ86170.
\v 16 He fed you stuff in the wildernessВҰ86175 that yourВҰ86173 ancestorsВҰ86180 had never heard of, so that he could humbleВҰ86182 you \add вүҲyet eventually cause you to prosper\add*
\v 17 without thinking to yourselves that your wealthВҰ86197 came from your own strength andВҰ86188 \add вүҲability\add*.
\v 18 Remember that it's your godВҰ86204 YahwehВҰ86203 who givesВҰ86207 you the strengthВҰ86209 to prosper, so that he can \add вүҲfulfill\add* his agreement that he promised to your ancestorsВҰ86220, as \add he has\add* \add вүҲuntil now\add*.
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if you \add вүҲend up\add* forgetting about your godВҰ86233 YahwehВҰ86232 and \add вүҲstart following\add* otherВҰ86237 godsВҰ86236 and serving them and bowing down to them, I \add вүҲcan assure\add* you that you'll \add вүҲmost definitely be destroyed\add*.
\v 20 IfВҰ86259 you don'tВҰ86256 listen to \add вүҲwhat your godВҰ86260 YahwehВҰ86250 says\add*, then you'll be destroyed just like the other people groups thatВҰ86249 he's destroyed ahead of you all.
\c 9
\s1 The reason for destruction of the land's inhabitants
\rem /s1 The Consequences of Rebelling against God; Victory by God's Grace; Not Because of Israel's Righteousness; The People's Disobedience
\p
\v 1 Listen YisraelВҰ86264: Today you'll cross the Yarden \add river\add* to \add вүҲdrive out peoples\add* that are larger and more powerful than yourselves and who are protected in largeВҰ86278, fortifiedВҰ86279 citiesВҰ86277 \add вүҲwith high walls\add*.
\v 2 The people \add themselves\add* are tall and strong. (Some of these are descendants of the Anakites, and you've heardВҰ86292 people \add ^say that no one\add* can defeat the Anakites.)
\v 3 You \add вүҲneed to be confident\add* that your godВҰ86303 Yahweh will go \add вүҲahead of you like a raging fireВҰ86308\add*вҖ”he'll destroy them and subdueВҰ86313 them ahead of you, thenВҰ86299 you can driveВҰ86315 them out and quicklyВҰ86318 eliminate them as Yahweh has told you \add to do\add*.
\p
\v 4 After your godВҰ86330 Yahweh has drivenВҰ86328 them out ahead of you, don'tВҰ86324 go saying that it was thanks to your \add own\add* \add вүҲgoodness and innocence\add*, because it's because of the wickednessВҰ86343 of those peoples that Yahweh is \add вүҲdoing that\add*.
\v 5 \add Again,\add* it's not because of your \add вүҲobedience or goodness\add* that you'reВҰ86354 going in to occupy theirВҰ86359 land, but it's because of the wickednessВҰ86361 of those peoples that your godВҰ86366 YahwehВҰ86365 will drive them out in front of you, and so that \add *he\add* can \add вүҲfulfill\add* what he promisedВҰ86373 to your ancestorsВҰ86377 AbrahamВҰ86378, Yitshak, and Yakov.
\v 6 \add вүҲActually, you're a very stubborn peopleВҰ86397, so be very clear\add*: it's not because of your \add вүҲgoodness andВҰ86382 obedience\add* that your godВҰ86387 YahwehВҰ86386 is giving you this goodВҰ86393 land.
\s1 The gold calf idol
\rem /s1 Remembering the Gold Calf; The Golden Calf
\p
\v 7 \add ^Never forgetВҰ86407\add* how you provokedВҰ86411 your godВҰ86415 YahwehВҰ86414 to get angry in the wildernessВҰ86416вҖ”you've been rebelliousВҰ86433 towards \add *him\add* \add вүҲthe whole time\add* from when you leftВҰ86422 EgyptВҰ86425 untilВҰ86426 \add вүҲyour arrival here\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲEven\add* at Horev \add (Mt. Sinai)\add* you made YahwehВҰ86443 angry, \add in fact\add* he was angry enough to destroyВҰ86447 you.
\v 9 When I wentВҰ86450 up the mountain to receive the stoneВҰ86454 tablets containing Yahweh's agreement with you, I stayed up on the mountain for forty days and nightsВҰ86467 \add вүҲwithout eating or drinking\add*.\x + \xo 9:9: \xt Exo 24:18.\x*
\v 10 ThenВҰ86475 Yahweh gaveВҰ86475 me the twoВҰ86480 stoneВҰ86482 tabletsВҰ86481 that had been writtenВҰ86483 by God's fingerВҰ86484. They had the wordsВҰ86489 spokenВҰ86491 to you by Yahweh out from the fireВҰ86496 on the mountainВҰ86494 on the dayВҰ86497 of that assemblyВҰ86498.
\v 11 \add вүҲThenВҰ86500 finally\add* at the end of those forty days andВҰ86500 nightsВҰ86505, YahwehВҰ86507 gaveВҰ86506 me those twoВҰ86511 stoneВҰ86513 tablets \add вүҲwith the agreement written on them\add*.
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ86517 \add *he\add* told me, вҖҳ\add вүҲNow hurry andВҰ86517\add* goВҰ86521 down quickly from here, because your peopleВҰ86526 who you broughtВҰ86528 out from EgyptВҰ86529, have become corruptedВҰ86525. They \add вүҲdidn't take at all long to turn away from following my instructions\add*вҖ”they've \add already\add* made a metal \add idol\add* for themselves.вҖҷ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲAdditionally,\add* YahwehВҰ86542 said to me, вҖҳI've \add вүҲnoticed\add* that this \add вүҲgroup of people is very stubborn\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲMove away\add* and I'll destroyВҰ86560 them \add вүҲso they'll never be remembered again\add*, and I'll make \add вүҲyour descendants\add* into a more powerful and more prestigious nationВҰ86569 than they ever were.вҖҷ
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ86575\add* I turnedВҰ86575 andВҰ86575 headed back down the mountain that was still burningВҰ86581 with fireВҰ86582, carrying the two tabletsВҰ86584 with the agreement \add written on them\add*.
\v 16 ThenВҰ86590 I looked, andВҰ86591 wow, you \add certainly\add* had disobeyed your godВҰ86594 Yahweh. You'd cast a metalВҰ86598 calf. You'd turnedВҰ86599 so quicklyВҰ86600 from the instructions thatВҰ86604 Yahweh had given you.
\v 17 I grabbed those two \add stone\add* tabletsВҰ86612 andВҰ86610 threwВҰ86613 them to the groundвҖ”shattering them right in front of your eyesВҰ86618.
\v 18 ThenВҰ86620 I lay on the ground in frontВҰ86621 of Yahweh for forty days andВҰ86620 nightsВҰ86627 without eating or drinking because of how you'd disobeyed YahwehвҖ”doingВҰ86640 evilВҰ86641 things thatВҰ86638 provokedВҰ86644 him into being angry.
\v 19 \add вүҲYes,\add* I was afraidВҰ86647 that \add вүҲin his terrible anger, YahwehВҰ86653 might destroyВҰ86655 you, but\add* \add *he\add* listenedВҰ86657 to me at that time.\x + \xo 9:19: \xt Heb 12:21.\x*
\v 20 YahwehВҰ86666 was angryВҰ86665 enough \add to want\add* to destroyВҰ86668 Aharon, \add вүҲbut\add* I also interceded for himВҰ86668 at that timeВҰ86674.
\v 21 I tookВҰ86688 \add that symbol of\add* your \add вүҲdisobedience\add*вҖ”that calf \add idol\add* that you all had madeвҖ”and \add вүҲthrew it into\add* the fireВҰ86692, then I crushedВҰ86693 it and groundВҰ86695 it into dust, and threw the dust into the mountainВҰ86712 streamВҰ86708.
\p
\v 22 You all also provokedВҰ86718 YahwehВҰ86722 to get angry at Taberah,\x + \xo 9:22: \xt Num 11:3.\x* at MassahВҰ86715,\x + \xo 9:22: \xt Exo 17:7.\x* andВҰ86714 at Kivrot-Hattaavah.\x + \xo 9:22: \xt Num 11:34.\x*
\v 23 \add вүҲAlso\add* when Yahweh sentВҰ86724 you all from Kadesh-Barnea, saying, вҖҳGo in and takeВҰ86731 possessionВҰ86731 of the land thatВҰ86735 I've givenВҰ86736 to you,вҖҷ \add вүҲbut\add* you rebelledВҰ86738 againstВҰ86738 your godВҰ86743 Yahweh's words, and you didn't believeВҰ86745 him and didn't \add вүҲdo what he said\add*.\x + \xo 9:23: a \xt Num 13:17; \xo b \xt Deu 1:21; \xo c \xt Num 13:31; Deu 1:26; Heb 3:16.\x*
\v 24 You've all been rebellious against YahwehВҰ86755 since the dayВҰ86756 I knew you \add back in Egypt\add*.
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ86760\add* I \add вүҲlay on the ground in Yahweh's presence\add* for forty days andВҰ86760 nightsВҰ86769, because \add *he\add* saidВҰ86774 he'd destroyВҰ86776 you all,
\v 26 and I prayedВҰ86779, вҖҳMy masterВҰ86784 YahwehВҰ86784, these people belong to you. Don't destroyВҰ86788 themвҖ”they are people who you rescued and broughtВҰ86796 out of EgyptВҰ86797 by \add using\add* your \add вүҲstrength and power\add*.
\v 27 \add ^Don't forget\add* \add what you promised\add* yourВҰ86802 servantsВҰ86802 AbrahamВҰ86803, Yitshak, and Yakov. \add вүҲOverlook\add* the stubbornnessВҰ86811, wickednessВҰ86816, and disobedience of these peopleВҰ86812
\v 28 so that the people \add of Egypt\add* whereВҰ86825 we were brought out from don'tВҰ86828 say that you weren't able to bringВҰ86831 them to the land that you'd promised to give to them. \add They'll say that\add* you took them into the desert to kill them thereВҰ86827 because you hatedВҰ86839 them.
\v 29 \add вүҲButВҰ86845\add* theyВҰ86845 are your peopleВҰ86846 and your inheritanceВҰ86847, who youВҰ86849 broughtВҰ86849 out \add of Egypt\add* \add вүҲusing your strength and powerВҰ86850\add*.вҖҷ
\c 10
\s1 The replacement stone tablets
\rem /s1 The Second Pair of Tablets; Moses Receives the Commandments Again; Tablets Like the First Ones; New Tablets of Stone
\r (Exo. 34:1-10)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* YahwehВҰ86859 told me, вҖңCarve out twoВҰ86864 stoneВҰ86871 tabletsВҰ86866 like the first ones, and make a wooden chest \add to put them in\add*, then comeВҰ86873 up to me on the mountainВҰ86875.
\v 2 I'll writeВҰ86881 the wordsВҰ86887 onto the tablets that were on the first tablets that you brokeВҰ86895, thenВҰ86881 you can put them into the box.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ86899\add* I made a box from acaciaВҰ86902 wood, and I carved out two stoneВҰ86907 tablets like the first ones, and I wentВҰ86909 up the mountainВҰ86910 \add вүҲcarrying\add* the two tablets
\v 4 andВҰ86915 he wroteВҰ86915 the tenВҰ86922 instructions on the tablets like the first \add вүҲtime\add*вҖ”the same words thatВҰ86924 YahwehВҰ86926 had spokenВҰ86925 to you from the fireВҰ86930 on the mountainВҰ86928 on the dayВҰ86931 of the assemblyВҰ86932. ThenВҰ86915 \add *he\add* gaveВҰ86933 me the tablets
\v 5 and I turnedВҰ86937 and wentВҰ86938 down the mountainВҰ86941. I put the tabletsВҰ86945 into the box thatВҰ86947 I'd made, just like YahwehВҰ86953 had told me to.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ86955 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ86956\add* travelled from BeerotВҰ86958-Bene-Yaakan\f + \fr 10:6 \ft Rather than just transliterating this name as we've done, it would also be possible to translate it as вҖҳthe wells of the sons of YaakanвҖҷ.\f* to Moserah\f + \fr 10:6 \ft The document known as вҖҳNumbersвҖҷ tells us that Aharon died on Mt. Hor, so presumably Moserah is in that same region.\f* where Aharon died. He was buriedВҰ86966 \add there\add*, andВҰ86955 his son EleazarВҰ86969 replaced himВҰ86971 as \add chief\add* priestВҰ86968.\x + \xo 10:6: \xt Num 20:28; 33:38.\x*
\v 7 From there theyВҰ86974 moved on to GudgodahВҰ86975, then from \add *there\add* onto YotbatahвҖ”an area with many streams.
\v 8 At that timeВҰ86987, Yahweh \add вүҲchose\add* the tribeВҰ86993 of LeviВҰ86994 to carryВҰ86995 the box \add вүҲcontaining\add* Yahweh's agreement, and to standВҰ87002 \add вүҲin Yahweh's presence\add* to serveВҰ87005 and \add вүҲworship\add* himВҰ87005, untilВҰ87008 this dayВҰ87009.\x + \xo 10:8: \xt Num 3:5-8.\x*
\v 9 That's why \add вүҲthe Levites didn'tВҰ87015 receive land in the same way as the other tribes\add* \add as\add* YahwehВҰ87024 told them that \add *he\add* is their inheritance.
\v 10 I myself stayed up on the mountainВҰ87035 for forty days and nightsВҰ87041 just like the firstВҰ87037 time. YahwehВҰ87043 listenedВҰ87042 to me that time as well, and \add said\add* that he wouldn't destroyВҰ87052 you.\x + \xo 10:10: \xt Exo 34:28.\x*
\v 11 ThenВҰ87054 YahwehВҰ87055 told me, вҖң\add вүҲContinue your journeyВҰ87059 leading\add* the peopleВҰ87061 to enter andВҰ87054 occupy the land that I promised theirВҰ87070 ancestorsВҰ87070 that I'd giveВҰ87071 them.
\s1 The call to obedience
\rem /s1 Fear the Lord; A Call to Love and Obedience; The Essence of the Law; What God Demands
\p
\v 12 Now YisraelВҰ87076, your god YahwehВҰ87078 expects you \add вүҲhonour\add* \add *him\add* and to \add вүҲfollow his instructions\add* and to love him, and to serveВҰ87096 \add *him\add* with \add вүҲsincerity and with energy\add*вҖ”
\v 13 \add вүҲobeying\add* \add *his\add* rules andВҰ87113 regulationsВҰ87115 thatВҰ87116 I'm giving youВҰ87118 today for the benefit of \add @the country\add*.
\v 14 Listen, the highest heavensВҰ87127 belong to yourВҰ87125 godВҰ87125 YahwehВҰ87124, as well as the earthВҰ87129 and everything on itВҰ87134,
\v 15 \add вүҲyet\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲdecided to show loveВҰ87140\add* to your ancestorsВҰ87137, and as theirВҰ87143 \add вүҲdescendantsВҰ87143\add*, he choseВҰ87142 you all out from all the peoplesВҰ87148 as \add you know\add* to this dayВҰ87149.
\v 16 You all must \add вүҲeradicate your rebelliousness\add* and \add вүҲstop being stubborn\add*,
\v 17 because your god YahwehВҰ87168 is god of gods and master of mastersвҖ”the very powerful and awesomeВҰ87173 one who \add вүҲdoesn't judge by looks\add* and doesn't accept bribesВҰ87181.\x + \xo 10:17: \xt 1Tim 6:15; Rev 17:14; 19:16; Acts 10:34; Rom 2:11; Gal 2:6; Eph 6:9.\x*
\v 18 He \add вүҲdelivers\add* \add fair\add* judgementsВҰ87184 for the fatherlessВҰ87185 and for widowsВҰ87186, and \add вүҲshows love\add* towards foreignersвҖ”givingВҰ87189 them food and clothingВҰ87192,
\v 19 \add вүҲso\add* you all must \add вүҲshow loveВҰ87194\add* to foreigners \add too\add* because you all were foreigners when you were in EgyptВҰ87203.
\v 20 You must \add вүҲhonour\add* your godВҰ87208 YahwehВҰ87207 and serveВҰ87211 him. \add вүҲRely on\add* him and \add only\add* make promises \add вүҲwith his authority\add*.
\v 21 He's the one you should praiseВҰ87218. He's your godВҰ87220 who's done \add вүҲpowerful miracles on your behalf\add* whichВҰ87232 you saw with your own eyesВҰ87234.
\v 22 When your ancestorsВҰ87239 wentВҰ87238 down to EgyptВҰ87240, there was only seventyВҰ87236 of them, but now your godВҰ87247 YahwehВҰ87246 \add вүҲhas increasedВҰ87250 your population\add* like the starsВҰ87248 in numberВҰ87250.\x + \xo 10:22: a \xt Gen 46:27; \xo b \xt Gen 15:5; 22:17.\x*
\c 11
\s1 Remembering the miracles
\rem /s1 Rewards for Obedience; Love and Obey the Lord; The Lord's Greatness
\p
\v 1 You must loveВҰ87252 yourВҰ87255 godВҰ87255 YahwehВҰ87254 and follow his instructions, rules, regulationsВҰ87258, and commandsВҰ87260 \add вүҲfrom now on\add*.
\v 2 \add Of course thatВҰ87277 was you all and your parents\add* who \add вүҲexperienced\add* your godВҰ87285 Yahweh's discipline and who saw his power and strength and \add вүҲthe amazing miracles done on your behalf\add*вҖ”not your childrenВҰ87272.
\v 3 \add вүЎThey didn't see\add* his actions and the miracles done to King Far-oh and all his people right there in EgyptВҰ87305,\x + \xo 11:3: \xt Exo 7:8вҖ“12:13.\x*
\v 4 or what he did to the Egyptian army with its horsesВҰ87318 and chariotsВҰ87319 when he causedВҰ87321 the Red Sea to flow over \add вүҲthe top of them\add* as they chased you, and how YahwehВҰ87334 destroyedВҰ87333 them and \add ^they've never recovered\add* to this dayВҰ87336,\x + \xo 11:4: \xt Exo 14:28.\x*
\v 5 or \add вүҲhow he helped\add* you all in the wildernessВҰ87342 untilВҰ87343 you reached this placeВҰ87348.
\v 6 \add вүЎYour children didn't see\add* what \add @Yahweh\add* did to Eliav's sonsВҰ87355 DatanВҰ87353 and Aviram (from the tribe of Reuven) when the ground openedВҰ87361 \add вүҲup\add* and swallowedВҰ87366 them, alongВҰ87378 with their housesВҰ87369 and tentsВҰ87372 and \add вүҲall their families and animals\add* \add вүҲright in the middle of the encampment\add*\x + \xo 11:6: \xt Num 16:31-32.\x*
\v 7 because you all are the ones who \add actually\add* saw the amazing miracles thatВҰ87394 YahwehВҰ87392 did.
\s1 The promises and warnings
\rem /s1 The Blessings of Obedience; The Blessings of the Promised Land
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ87397 thenВҰ87397,\add* follow all the instructions that I'mВҰ87404 \add вүҲgiving\add* you all today so that you'll all be strongВҰ87408 to enter andВҰ87397 take possession of the land \add вүҲonce you cross the river\add*
\v 9 and so that you all might live \add вүҲfor a long time\add* in that land whichВҰ87426 YahwehВҰ87428 promised to giveВҰ87430 them and theirВҰ87432 descendantsВҰ87432вҖ”a land flowingВҰ87434 with milk and honeyВҰ87436
\v 10 because \add *it's\add* not like EgyptВҰ87449 where \add @your ancestors\add* cameВҰ87452 out from, where you planted seed and had to water \add the fields\add* \add вүҲby hand\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ87464\add* the land that you're all aboutВҰ87467 to enter over \add the river\add* has a terrain of hills andВҰ87464 valleysВҰ87472, \add i.e.,\add* it drinksВҰ87475 in the rain waterВҰ87477.
\v 12 It'sВҰ87488 a land thatВҰ87480 your god YahwehВҰ87482 \add вүҲcares about\add*вҖ”\add вүҲwatching over\add* it from the beginningВҰ87491 of each year to the end.
\p
\v 13 If you all listen to the instructions thatВҰ87506 I'm \add вүҲgiving\add* you today, loving your godВҰ87515 YahwehВҰ87514 and serving himВҰ87516 with \add вүҲsincerity and with energy\add*,\x + \xo 11:13-17: \xt Lev 26:3-5; Deu 7:12-16; 28:1-14.\x*
\v 14 thenВҰ87524 \add he says that he'll\add* giveВҰ87524 the land \add вүҲthe seasonalВҰ87528 early and late rains\add* \add вүҲso that you'll be able to produce\add* grainВҰ87532, and new wine, and \add olive\add* oil.
\v 15 \add вүҲHe'll\add* provide grassВҰ87537 in the countryside for your livestockВҰ87539, and you'll eatВҰ87540 and be satisfied.
\v 16 Guard yourselves to make sure that you're not deceivedВҰ87546 and \add end up\add* turning around to serveВҰ87549 otherВҰ87551 вҖҳgodsВҰ87550вҖҷ and bow down to them,
\v 17 \add because\add* thenВҰ87555 YahwehВҰ87558 \add вүҲwould become angry at\add* you and \add вүҲclose\add* the skiesВҰ87563 so that there'd be no rain, and the land would \add вүҲstop producingВҰ87573\add*, and you'd all \add вүҲsoon die\add* from off the goodВҰ87578 land that \add *he's\add* aboutВҰ87581 to giveВҰ87581 you.
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲMemorise\add* theseВҰ87588 wordsВҰ87587 of mine and \add вүҲconstantly think about them\add*. Your \add вүҲhands should always be applying them\add* and your \add вүҲminds should always be evaluating them\add*.\x + \xo 11:18-20: \xt Deu 6:6-9.\x*
\v 19 Teach them \add repeatedly\add* to your childrenВҰ87610: when you're sitting at home, when you're walking down the roadВҰ87616, when you go to lie down, andВҰ87606 when you get up.
\v 20 \add вүҲCarve\add* them on the doorpostsВҰ87623 of your homes andВҰ87620 on your \add city\add* gatesВҰ87625,
\v 21 so that your own lifetimes, and the lifetimes of your childrenВҰ87631 will be extended in the land that YahwehВҰ87636 promised to giveВҰ87638 to your ancestorsВҰ87637 \add to have\add* as \add вүҲlong as the sky remains\add* over the earthВҰ87644.
\p
\v 22 If you all follow these instructions thatВҰ87658 I'm telling you to do, to loveВҰ87663 your godВҰ87667 YahwehВҰ87666 and \add вүҲlive how he wants you to, and stay faithful\add* to him,
\v 23 thenВҰ87676 \add *he'll\add* driveВҰ87676 all those peoples out \add вүҲahead of\add* you all, and you'll dispossessВҰ87685 groups that are larger and more powerful than yourselves.
\v 24 EveryВҰ87691 placeВҰ87693 thatВҰ87694 your feet step on will become yours: from the \add southern\add* desert to LebanonВҰ87705 \add in the north\add*, and from the EuphratesВҰ87711 \add in the east\add* to the Mediterranean Sea \add in the west\add*.\x + \xo 11:24-25: \xt Josh 1:3-5.\x*
\v 25 No one \add вүҲwill be able to resist\add* you all. Your godВҰ87728 YahwehВҰ87727 \add вүҲwill make those peoples in thatВҰ87735 land terrified\add* of you, just as he promised he would.
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲNow listen,\add* today I'm \add вүҲgiving you all the option\add* of a blessingВҰ87749 or a curseВҰ87750:
\v 27 the blessingВҰ87754 is if you all \add decide to\add* obeyВҰ87756 your godВҰ87761 Yahweh's instructions thatВҰ87762 I'm giving you today,
\v 28 \add вүҲbut\add* the curseВҰ87768 is if you all don'tВҰ87771 \add вүҲtake any notice\add* of \add *his\add* instructions, or if you turnВҰ87778 away from what I'm commandingВҰ87775 you all today to goВҰ87787 afterВҰ87788 otherВҰ87790 godsВҰ87789 thatВҰ87782 you \add вүҲpreviously had nothing to do with\add*.
\v 29 Whenever your godВҰ87801 YahwehВҰ87800 brings you into the land that you'reВҰ87807 entering to take possessionВҰ87811 of, you must \add вүҲpronounce\add* the blessingВҰ87815 from Mt. GerizimВҰ87819, and the curseВҰ87822 from Mt. Eyval.\x + \xo 11:29: \xt Deu 27:11-14; Josh 8:33-35.\x*
\v 30 (Those two mountains are acrossВҰ87831 the Yarden \add river\add*, west of the river plainВҰ87840 where the CanaanitesВҰ87838 liveВҰ87839, near the Oak of MorehВҰ87845 oppositeВҰ87841 GilgalВҰ87842.)
\v 31 You'll all \add soon\add* be crossing the Yarden to goВҰ87853 in and occupy the land thatВҰ87858 your godВҰ87861 YahwehВҰ87860 is giving you. \add вүҲAs\add* you all \add вүҲtakeВҰ87854 it over\add* and \add start to\add* liveВҰ87866 there,
\v 32 \add вүҲmake sure that\add* you follow all the instructions andВҰ87876 rules that I'mВҰ87880 giving to you all today.
\c 12
\s1 One place for future worship
\rem /s1 The Lord's Chosen Place for Worship; The One Place of Worship; Laws delivered by Moses; The One Place for Worship; Pagan Shrines to Be Destroyed
\p
\v 1 In the land that yourВҰ87896 godВҰ87895 YahwehВҰ87894 has givenВҰ87893 you to own, these are the rules andВҰ87887 regulationsВҰ87886 that you must keep obeying as long as you're aliveВҰ87905.
\v 2 When you drive those peoples out, you all must completely destroy all the placesВҰ87916 on the mountainsВҰ87931 and hillsВҰ87935, and underВҰ87936 the large trees whereВҰ87917 theyВҰ87918 servedВҰ87918 theirВҰ87928 godsВҰ87928.
\v 3 You all must tear down their altarsВҰ87946, shatter their stone pillarsВҰ87951, and set fireВҰ87954 to their Asherah polesВҰ87952. You must chop down their carved idolsВҰ87955 so they won't be remembered in that placeВҰ87964 any more.\x + \xo 12:3: \xt Deu 7:5.\x*
\p
\v 4 Don't worship your godВҰ87972 YahwehВҰ87971 \add вүҲthe same way they worship their gods\add*,
\v 5 because you all must go to the \add single\add* placeВҰ87979 that Yahweh'sВҰ87983 going to chooseВҰ87982 out of all your tribesВҰ87987, that he'll attach his nameВҰ87991 to, so if you want find his residence, you'll have to go there.
\v 6 That will \add also\add* be where you'll all have to take your animal sacrifices and offerings, as well as the tenth of your \add вүҲproduce and animals\add*, \add вүҲspecial contributionsВҰ88005\add*, sacrifices for promises, free-will sacrifices, and the firstbornВҰ88009 animals from your herdsВҰ88010 and flocksВҰ88011.
\v 7 You'llВҰ88027 all be able to take your families thereВҰ88015 in frontВҰ88016 of your god YahwehВҰ88017 to cheerfully eat \add вүҲwhat you've produced as a result of his blessingВҰ88026\add*.
\p
\v 8 We won't be able to continue like weВҰ88034 are at present, with each person \add вүҲworshipping however they feel is rightВҰ88041\add*
\v 9 because untilВҰ88048 now, you haven't reached the inheritanceВҰ88056 andВҰ88054 the \add вүҲpeaceful life\add* thatВҰ88057 yourВҰ88060 godВҰ88060 YahwehВҰ88059 is giving to you.
\v 10 \add вүҲAfter\add* you all crossВҰ88064 the Yarden and live in the land that your godВҰ88073 YahwehВҰ88072 is givingВҰ88074 you as an inheritanceВҰ88074, it's thenВҰ88064 that he'll give you \add вүҲpeace\add* from all your surrounding enemiesВҰ88080, and \add so\add* you'll all live safely.
\v 11 ThenВҰ88086 your godВҰ88092 Yahweh will chooseВҰ88090 one placeВҰ88087 to \add вүҲattach his nameВҰ88095 to\add*, and that's where you'll all bringВҰ88098 everything that I tell you to: your animal sacrifices and offeringsВҰ88106, as well as the tenth of your \add вүҲproduce and animals\add*, \add вүҲspecial contributionsВҰ88109\add*, and sacrifices for promises made to Yahweh.
\v 12 You'll all celebrate thereВҰ88131 in frontВҰ88119 of YahwehВҰ88120: you and your children and your servants, along with any LevitesВҰ88127 \add вүҲwho live in your townsВҰ88129\add* (because they don'tВҰ88131 \add вүҲpersonally inheritВҰ88134 any land of their own\add*).
\rem /s1 A Prescribed Place of Worship
\v 13 \add вүҲMake sure\add* that you don't offerВҰ88141 burntВҰ88142 sacrifices at any placeВҰ88145 that you \add вүҲjust decide is good\add*вҖ”
\v 14 only at the placeВҰ88152 that YahwehВҰ88156 will chooseВҰ88155 from one of your tribesВҰ88158. That's where you'll offerВҰ88160 your sacrifices, and do everything else that I tell you.
\p
\v 15 However, you may kill and eat your animals \add вүҲwherever you live as much as you want\add*. Those animals are blessingsВҰ88178 from your godВҰ88180 YahwehВҰ88179. You can eat thatВҰ88181 meat \add вүҲwhether or not you're ceremonially вҖҳcleanВҰ88189вҖҷ\add*, just like you'd eat a \add wild\add* gazelleВҰ88191 or deer.
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever,\add* don'tВҰ88196 eatВҰ88197 the bloodВҰ88195вҖ”itВҰ88201 must be poured out on the ground like waterВҰ88202.\x + \xo 12:16: \xt Gen 9:4; Lev 7:26-27; 17:10-14; 19:6; Deu 15:23.\x*
\v 17 In your townsВҰ88208, don't eatВҰ88207 the tenth of your \add вүҲproduce\add* or the firstbornsВҰ88213 from your herd or flockВҰ88215, or at the celebration of a vow, or any free-will offeringВҰ88221 or contributionВҰ88222 \add вүҲthatВҰ88219 you've made\add*.
\v 18 You can only eat those in Yahweh's presence in the placeВҰ88232 thatВҰ88233 \add *he'll\add* chooseВҰ88234. \add вүҲThe same applies to\add* your children, your servants, and any LevitesВҰ88243 who live \add вүҲin your townsВҰ88245\add*. \add вүҲThe celebration for what you've produced must be done in front of\add* your god Yahweh.
\v 19 \add вүҲMake sure\add* that you don't neglectВҰ88258 the LevitesВҰ88261 as long as you live in yourВҰ88264 land.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲInВҰ88283 the future, when\add* your godВҰ88274 YahwehВҰ88273 widens your territoryВҰ88277 like he's said he would, if you want to eat meat there, then \add вүҲgo ahead and do it\add*.
\v 21 If the placeВҰ88302 thatВҰ88313 \add *he\add* choosesВҰ88304 \add вүҲto attach his nameВҰ88308 to\add* is too far away, then \add вүҲit's permissible\add* to sacrifice like I've instructedВҰ88318 you from yourВҰ88323 herd or flockВҰ88312, and you can eatВҰ88319 it \add вүҲwhereВҰ88303 you live whenever you want\add*.
\v 22 You can eat it \add вүҲwhether or not you're ceremonially вҖҳcleanВҰ88337вҖҷ\add*, just like you'd eat a \add wild\add* gazelleВҰ88330 or deer.
\v 23 \add вүҲHowever,\add* don'tВҰ88343 eat the blood of any animal, because the blood is the life and you mustn't eat the life with the meat.\x + \xo 12:23-24: \xt Lev 17:10-14.\x*
\v 24 Don't eatВҰ88359 \add @the blood\add*вҖ”it must be poured out on the ground like waterВҰ88364.
\v 25 Don't eatВҰ88367 it so that things will goВҰ88369 well for you and your childrenВҰ88371 afterВҰ88372 you, when you do what YahwehВҰ88378 \add вүҲsays is rightВҰ88376\add*.
\v 26 \add вүҲHowever, youВҰ88387 still must takeВҰ88387\add* your sacredВҰ88381 thingsВҰ88381 and offerings for vows to the placeВҰ88391 thatВҰ88382 YahwehВҰ88395 will chooseВҰ88394.
\v 27 The meat and blood from burntВҰ88398 offeringsВҰ88398 must only be placed on your god Yahweh's \add future\add* altar, and the blood of your \add other\add* sacrificesВҰ88408 must be pouredВҰ88409 on the altar, \add вүҲbut\add* you can eat the meat.
\v 28 \add вүҲMake sure to follow\add* all theseВҰ88424 instructions that I'm giving you so that everything will goВҰ88429 well for you and for your descendants into the future, when you do what your godВҰ88442 YahwehВҰ88441 has said is goodВҰ88438 and rightВҰ88439.
\s1 Warnings about false gods
\rem /s1 Warning against Idolatry
\p
\v 29 When you enter the land that you will occupy, yourВҰ88460 godВҰ88449 YahwehВҰ88448 \add вүҲwill destroy the people groups that liveВҰ88463 there as you advance\add*.
\v 30 WatchВҰ88492 out afterВҰ88472 they've been destroyedВҰ88473, that you don'tВҰ88475 get trapped \add вүҲby curiosity aboutВҰ88478 how they servedВҰ88481 their gods, and then you end up doing the same\add*.
\v 31 Don'tВҰ88504 do thatВҰ88505 to your god YahwehВҰ88498, because \add *he\add* hatesВҰ88506 the disgusting things they've done for their godsвҖ”even burning their own sons and daughtersВҰ88516 \add on altars\add* for their gods.
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲMake sure that\add* you obey all those instructionsвҖ”don't add anything to them, or remove anything from them.\x + \xo 12:32: \xt Deu 4:2; Rev 22:18-19.\x*
\c 13
\s1 Warnings about false prophets
\rem /s1 A Warning against Idolatry; Worshipping Other Gods
\p
\v 1 IfВҰ88527 someone among you \add claims\add* to be a prophet or interpreter of dreams, or \add вүҲable to do miracles\add*,
\v 2 \add вүҲand it seems true, but they use those things to convince you to go after other вҖҳnewвҖҷ\add* gods and worship them,
\v 3 then don'tВҰ88571 listen to thatВҰ88561 person, because your god Yahweh is testing you to know whether you love \add *him\add* with \add вүҲsincerity and with your energy\add*.
\v 4 You must \add вүҲconduct your lives as your god YahwehВҰ88592 wants you to\add*. Honour him, and listenВҰ88578 to his voice and follow his instructions, and serve him and \add вүҲremain loyal\add* to him.
\v 5 \add вүҲBut\add* that prophet or interpreter of dreams must be executed because they've incited rebellion against your godВҰ88612 Yahweh who brought you all out from slavery in Egypt. Those \add kinds of\add* people want to drive you away from @Yahweh's instructions, hence why you must remove that evil from among you.
\p
\v 6 YourВҰ88648 brother, son, daughter, \add вүҲbeloved\add* wife, or \add вүҲsome close\add* friend might privately urge you to worship other gods thatВҰ88655 you and yourВҰ88648 ancestors hadn't heard about before.
\v 7 \add вүҲThat might be\add* the godsВҰ88690 of the surrounding peoples, either nearby or \add вүҲright across the world\add*.
\v 8 Don't give in to them, or take notice of them. Don't even \add вүҲfeel sympathy for them or cover up for them\add*,
\v 9 because \add вүҲyou'll definitely need to execute them\add*. \add вүҲYou yourself must be the first to take action, followed by the rest of the community\add*.
\v 10 You must \add вүҲexecute peopleВҰ88749 like that by throwing rocks at them\add*, because they try to drive you away from yourВҰ88740 god Yahweh who brought you out of \add вүҲslavery\add* in Egypt.
\v 11 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* all Yisrael will hear and \add вүҲbecome afraid of doing such wicked things in the future\add*.
\p
\v 12 If \add in the future\add*, you hearВҰ88772 that in one of the cities that yourВҰ88781 god Yahweh will give you to live in,
\v 13 some wicked people have enticed those in the city to go and serve other вҖҳnewвҖҷ gods,
\v 14 then you must thoroughly investigate the matter. If it's actually true that that disgusting thing had been done amongВҰ88805 you,
\v 15 then all the people in that place must be executed by the sword, along with all their livestock.
\v 16 Gather all the people's possessions and pile them up in the cityВҰ88842 plaza, then burn the place and everything in it like a вҖҳburnt offeringвҖҷ to Yahweh. Leave the place as an abandoned heapвҖ”it should never be rebuilt again.
\v 17 Don't \add be tempted\add* to \add вүҲpick anything valuable out\add* from the \add вүҲpile headed for destruction\add*, \add but obey carefully\add* so that Yahweh's \add вүҲanger will subside\add*. Then he'll show compassion to you and mercy, and make you increase like he promised to your ancestors
\v 18 when you listen to \add вүҲwhat he says\add*вҖ”following all his instructions and doing what \add *he\add* says is the right thing to do.
\c 14
\s1 Prohibitions during mourning
\rem /s1 Clean and Unclean Food; Pagan Practices Forbidden; A Forbidden Mourning Practice; Ceremonially Clean and Unclean Animals
\p
\v 1 You're all childrenВҰ88942 of your godВҰ88945 YahwehВҰ88944 \add so\add* don'tВҰ88946 cut yourselvesВҰ88947 or shave the front of your heads for \add the sake of\add* the deadВҰ88954,\x + \xo 14:1: \xt Lev 19:28; 21:5.\x*
\v 2 because you're a nation that's set apart for your godВҰ88961 YahwehВҰ88960, and \add *he's\add* chosenВҰ88963 you out of all the other peoples in the world to be his own people.\x + \xo 14:2: \xt Exo 19:5-6; Deu 4:20; 7:6; 26:18; Tit 2:14; 1Pe 2:9.\x*
\s1 вҖҳCleanвҖҷ and вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ foods
\rem /s1 Clean and Unclean Foods; Clean and Unclean Animals
\r (Lev. 11:1-47)
\p
\v 3 Don't eatВҰ88979 anything \add вүҲthat Yahweh detests\add*.
\v 4 These are the animalsВҰ88989 thatВҰ88986 you all can eatВҰ88987: cattleВҰ88985, sheep, goatsВҰ88992,
\v 5 \add вүҲall kinds of\add* deer, gazellesВҰ88995, wild goats, and mountainВҰ89000 sheepВҰ89000,
\v 6 \add i.e.,\add* you can eatВҰ89015 any of the animalsВҰ89004 that have split hoovesВҰ89010 andВҰ89007 that also chew the cud.
\v 7 But there are other animals that chew the cud that you mustn't eat: camelsВҰ89030, \add вүҲrabbits and hares\add*, and rock badgers. They chew the cud, but don'tВҰ89021 have splitВҰ89025 hooves so they are \add вүҲunacceptable\add* for you to eat.
\v 8 Don't eat pigsвҖ”they're unacceptable for you to eat. They have split hooves, but they don't chew the cud. Don't eat the meat of those animals andВҰ89049 don't even touchВҰ89067 their dead bodies.
\p
\v 9 You all can eat anything that \add lives\add* in waterВҰ89076 that has \add both\add* fins and scalesВҰ89082,
\v 10 but anything \add in the water\add* that doesn't have \add *both\add* is \add вүҲunacceptable\add* for you to eatВҰ89093.
\p
\v 11 You all can eatВҰ89103 any cleanВҰ89102 bird,
\v 12 \add вүҲbut\add* not these: eaglesВҰ89111, vultures, ospreys,
\v 13 buzzards, kites, falcons,
\v 14 any kind of ravensВҰ89125 or crows,
\v 15 ostriches, owls, seagulls, any kind of hawk,
\v 16 \add вүҲany kinds of\add* owls,
\v 17 pelicans, carrionВҰ89153 vulturesВҰ89153, cormorantsВҰ89156,
\v 18 storksВҰ89158, any kind of heronВҰ89159, hoopoesВҰ89161, or bats.
\v 19 You mustn't eat any insect with wings andВҰ89164 which swarmВҰ89165вҖ”they're unacceptable \add to Yahweh\add* for you to eat,
\v 20 \add вүҲbut other insectsВҰ89175 with wings are acceptable to\add* eatВҰ89177.
\p
\v 21 Don't eat any creature that's died \add вүҲnaturally\add*. You may allow foreigners who live among you to eat those things. You may also sell them to other foreigners. But you are a peopleВҰ89194 group that belongs to your godВҰ89198 YahwehВҰ89197.
\p You mustn't cook a young sheep or goat in its motherвҖҷs milk.\x + \xo 14:21: \xt Exo 23:19; 34:26.\x*
\rem /s1 The Law of the Tithe; Regulations concerning Tithes; The Giving of Tithes; Tithes
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲMake sure\add* you set aside a tenth of all the \add вүҲcrops that you harvest from your fieldsВҰ89215\add*.\x + \xo 14:22-29: \xt Lev 27:30-33; Num 18:21.\x*
\v 23 You must eat it \add вүҲin the presence of\add* your god Yahweh, in the placeВҰ89224 that he'll chooseВҰ89227 and \add вүҲattach his name to\add*. That's whereВҰ89225 you must eat the tenth of your grainВҰ89232, wine, \add olive\add* oil, and the firstbornВҰ89235 \add male animals\add* from your herd and your flockВҰ89237, so that you'll learnВҰ89239 to always honour your god Yahweh.
\v 24 When \add *he\add* blessesВҰ89272 you \add with produce\add*, if the placeВҰ89263 he choosesВҰ89265 to attach his nameВҰ89269 to is too far for you to be able to carryВҰ89258 it to,
\v 25 thenВҰ89276 you can \add вүҲgiveВҰ89276 the equivalent in cash\add*, andВҰ89276 \add вүҲcarefully takeВҰ89278 the cash with you all the way\add* to the placeВҰ89284 thatВҰ89285 \add *he\add* choosesВҰ89286.
\v 26 \add When you get there\add*, \add вүҲuse the moneyВҰ89292 to purchase any kinds of meat or drinkВҰ89301 that you want\add*, and consume itВҰ89296 there \add вүҲin frontВҰ89308 of\add* your godВҰ89310 YahwehВҰ89309, and celebrate along with your householdВҰ89313.
\p
\v 27 \add Be sure\add* not to neglectВҰ89320 any Levites that live in yourВҰ89318 town, because \add вүҲthey weren't given ancestral land for agriculture like youВҰ89326 were\add*.
\v 28 At the end of every third year, bringВҰ89333 the tenth of all your produceВҰ89339 for that year and storeВҰ89342 it in your town
\v 29 for the LevitesВҰ89346 (because they didn'tВҰ89348 get land), and for any foreigners, orphans, and widowsВҰ89356 who live in your townsВҰ89358. They can comeВҰ89345 and \add вүҲget what they need\add* so that your godВҰ89364 YahwehВҰ89363 can blessВҰ89362 you in everything that you do.
\c 15
\s1 The 7-year economic reset
\rem /s1 Release for Debtors; Laws concerning the Sabbatical Year; The Seventh Year; The Year for Cancelling Debts
\r (Lev. 25:1-7)
\p
\v 1 At the end of \add every\add* sevenВҰ89374 yearsВҰ89376, youВҰ89377 must \add вүҲcancel all debts\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲHandle it like\add* this: Everyone who's loaned money to their \add вүҲIsraeli\add* neighbour \add вүҲmust cancel that debt, i.e.,\add* they must not insist that it's paid back, because YahwehВҰ89405 has announced a cancellation.
\v 3 You can pressureВҰ89410 a foreignerВҰ89409 to repay, but you must cancel any debt from a fellow Israeli.
\p
\v 4 HoweverВҰ89434, there shouldn'tВҰ89422 be any poor among you, because your godВҰ89435 YahwehВҰ89431 will bless you in the land thatВҰ89433 \add *he's\add* giving you to own as an inheritanceВҰ89439,
\v 5 as long as you listen to \add вүҲwhat he says\add* and keep following theseВҰ89457 instructions thatВҰ89458 I'm telling you today.
\v 6 Because your godВҰ89466 YahwehВҰ89465 will blessВҰ89467 you (like he promised he would), you'll lend to many nations rather than borrowingВҰ89477 from them, and you'll rule over many nations rather than them ruling you.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲIn the townsВҰ89494\add* that your godВҰ89499 YahwehВҰ89498 is giving you, if it so happens that any of your fellow Israelis are poor, then don'tВҰ89502 \add вүҲjust ignore them and refuse to help them,\add*\x + \xo 15:7-8: \xt Lev 25:35.\x*
\v 8 but instead, open yourВҰ89521 \add вүҲwallet\add* and lend them however much they need.
\v 9 \add вүҲBe careful not to quietly think to yourselfВҰ89532 that the seventh-year reset\add* is close \add so they won'tВҰ89552 have to pay it back.\add* It would be wrong not to help a fellow Israeli, and if you did and he called out to YahwehВҰ89559 for help, then it would be \add вүҲcounted againstВҰ89556 you as disobedience\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲGive generously to the poor without getting resentful inside\add*, because then your godВҰ89580 YahwehВҰ89579 can blessВҰ89578 you in all your workВҰ89583 and \add вүҲall your investments\add*.
\v 11 \add ^There'll always be poor people in your country\add*, so I commandВҰ89599 you to give generouslyВҰ89601 to the poor and needy and your fellow Israelis.\x + \xo 15:11: \xt Mat 26:11; Mrk 14:7; Yhn 12:8.\x*
\s1 Freeing slaves
\rem /s1 The Treatment of Slaves; Freeing Servants; Release for Hebrew Slaves
\r (Exo. 21:1-11)
\p
\v 12 If a \add вүҲfellow Israeli\add* is sold to you\f + \fr 15:12 \ft Often to pay off their debt.\f* and servesВҰ89620 you for sixВҰ89621 yearsВҰ89622, then you must free them in the seventhВҰ89624 yearВҰ89623.\x + \xo 15:12-18: \xt Lev 25:39-46.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ89629\add* when youВҰ89633 free them, don'tВҰ89634 sendВҰ89635 them off \add вүҲempty-handed\add*
\v 14 \add but instead,\add* give to them generously from your flockВҰ89641 and from your \add вүҲbarn\add* and from your wine. \add вүҲIn whatever ways\add* your godВҰ89647 YahwehВҰ89646 has blessedВҰ89645 you, you should give to them.
\v 15 \add Always\add* rememberВҰ89652 that you were a slaveВҰ89654 in EgyptВҰ89657 andВҰ89652 yourВҰ89665 godВҰ89660 YahwehВҰ89659 redeemedВҰ89658 you \add out of there\add*, so that's why I'm commanding you to do that.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ89678,\add* if any slave says that they don'tВҰ89677 want to leave you, because they \add вүҲappreciate\add* you and your household, and so they're better off to stay with you,
\v 17 then get an awl and \add вүҲstand them against the doorpost\add* and pierce one of their earlobes with the awl, then that person (male or femaleВҰ89703) will be your slave forever.
\v 18 \add вүҲDon't complain\add* when you have to release your slaves, because they've servedВҰ89720 you \add up to\add* sixВҰ89721 yearsВҰ89722 and \add вүҲbeen doubleВҰ89717 the value\add* of a \add regular\add* hiredВҰ89719 worker, plus your godВҰ89725 YahwehВҰ89724 will blessВҰ89723 you in whatever you do.
\s1 The firstborn animals
\rem /s1 The First-Born Cattle and Sheep; The Firstborn Animals; Sacrificing Firstborn Male Animals; The Firstborn of Livestock
\p
\v 19 You must set apart for your godВҰ89741 YahwehВҰ89740, all the firstborn maleВҰ89738 animals from your herds and your flocks. You mustn't use the cattle for working, and mustn't shearВҰ89747 the sheep or goats.\x + \xo 15:19: \xt Exo 13:12.\x*
\v 20 EachВҰ89761 year, you and your householdВҰ89763 must \add take them\add* to the placeВҰ89757 thatВҰ89758 YahwehВҰ89752 will chooseВҰ89760, and eat them there in frontВҰ89751 of \add *him\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* any animals that have defects (e.g., lame or blindВҰ89772, or with a severe blemish) mustn't be sacrificedВҰ89777 to yourВҰ89779 godВҰ89779 YahwehВҰ89778.
\v 22 \add Instead,\add* you can eat those \add вүҲat home\add* \add вүҲwhether or not you're ceremonially вҖҳcleanВҰ89784вҖҷ\add*, just like you'd eat a \add wild\add* gazelleВҰ89786 or deer.
\v 23 \add вүҲHowever,\add* don'tВҰ89793 eatВҰ89794 the bloodВҰ89792вҖ”itВҰ89798 must be poured out on the ground like waterВҰ89799.\x + \xo 15:23: \xt Gen 9:4; Lev 7:26-27; 17:10-14; 19:26; Deu 12:16-23.\x*
\c 16
\s1 The messenger's вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ celebration
\rem /s1 The Passover; Passover; The Passover Reviewed; Passover and the Festival of Unleavened Bread
\r (Exo. 12:1-20)
\p
\v 1 \add Each year, honour\add* your god YahwehВҰ89809 \add вүҲin the early spring\add* by celebratingВҰ89807 the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ, because it was one nightВҰ89818 \add вүҲin the early spring\add* that \add *he\add* broughtВҰ89814 you out of Egpyt \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.\x + \xo 16:1-8: \xt Exo 12:1-20; Lev 23:5-8; Num 28:16-25.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲInВҰ89830 order to celebrate, go to\add* the placeВҰ89826 that your godВҰ89823 YahwehВҰ89822 will chooseВҰ89829 \add вүҲto attach his nameВҰ89832 to\add*, andВҰ89820 thereВҰ89833 sacrificeВҰ89820 to \add *him\add* one \add young\add* animal from your flockВҰ89824 or herd.
\v 3 Don't eat any leavenedВҰ89839 bread with it. For sevenВҰ89840 days, you must eat flat bread (the bread of suffering) because you came out of Egypt in a rush. That's how you should rememberВҰ89854 the day of your exit from Egypt for the rest of your life.
\v 4 \add In fact,\add* for sevenВҰ89876 daysВҰ89877 youВҰ89885 shouldn'tВҰ89868 even have any rising agent within yourВҰ89875 borders, andВҰ89878 none of the meat from the sacrificeВҰ89885 on thatВҰ89884 firstВҰ89888 eveningВҰ89886 is allowed to be left untilВҰ89889 the morningВҰ89889.
\p
\v 5 You mustn't sacrificeВҰ89893 the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add animal\add* within any of your townsВҰ89898 thatВҰ89899 your godВҰ89902 YahwehВҰ89901 is giving to youВҰ89892вҖ”
\v 6 only at the placeВҰ89911 thatВҰ89912 your godВҰ89916 YahwehВҰ89915 will chooseВҰ89914 to \add вүҲattach his nameВҰ89918 to\add*. That's where you must sacrificeВҰ89920 the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ \add animal\add* at sunset, whichВҰ89912 was the timeВҰ89927 when \add вүҲyour ancestors\add* started leaving EgyptВҰ89929.
\v 7 You must cook the meat andВҰ89931 eatВҰ89932 it at the placeВҰ89933 thatВҰ89934 YahwehВҰ89936 will chooseВҰ89935, thenВҰ89931 in the morningВҰ89940 you can \add start\add* returningВҰ89941 to your \add вүҲhomes\add*.
\v 8 Then for six daysВҰ89945 you must only eat flat breadВҰ89947, and the seventhВҰ89949 day is a special celebration for your god YahwehВҰ89951вҖ”don'tВҰ89953 do any work on that day.
\s1 The harvest celebration
\rem /s1 The Festival of Weeks Reviewed; Feast of Weeks; The Festival of Harvest; The Harvest Festival
\r (Exo. 34:22; Lev. 23:15-21)
\p
\v 9 You must count off seven weeks \add вүҲstarting from when the very firstВҰ89963 harvesting of grainВҰ89965 beginsВҰ89966\add*.\x + \xo 16:9-12: \xt Lev 23:15-21; Num 28:26-31.\x*
\v 10 ThenВҰ89971 celebrateВҰ89971 the вҖҳFestival of WeeksвҖҷ\f + \fr 16:10 \ft Also known as the вҖҳHarvest FestivalвҖҷ or вҖҳPentecostвҖҷ (relating to the fifty days = seven weeks plus one day).\f* \add to honour\add* your god YahwehВҰ89974 by contributing a freewillВҰ89977 offeringВҰ89977 \add acknowledging\add* however much \add *he\add* has blessedВҰ89982 you.
\v 11 You should celebrate in Yahweh's presence, along with your children and your servants, and any LevitesВҰ89996 living in your town, and the foreigners, orphans, and widowsВҰ90001 living among you. Take your offerings to the placeВҰ90004 that your god Yahweh will chooseВҰ90006 \add вүҲto attach his name to\add*.
\v 12 \add Always\add* rememberВҰ90013 that youВҰ90017 were a slaveВҰ90016 in EgyptВҰ90018, \add вүҲso carefullyВҰ90019 follow those instructions\add*.
\s1 The celebration in temporary huts
\rem /s1 The Festival of Shelters; The Festival of Booths Reviewed; Feast of Tabernacles
\r (Lev. 23:33-43)
\p
\v 13 \add After\add* you've brought in the grain harvest and pressed out the grape juice, you must celebrate the вҖҳFestival of SheltersвҖҷ for sevenВҰ90031 daysВҰ90032.\x + \xo 16:13-15: \xt Lev 23:33-36,39-43; Num 29:12-38.\x*
\v 14 You should celebrate along with your children and your servants, as well as any LevitesВҰ90044 and foreigners and orphans and widowsВҰ90047 who live in your town.
\v 15 \add Honour\add* your god YahwehВҰ90054 at the placeВҰ90056 \add *he'll\add* chooseВҰ90059, by celebratingВҰ90053 for seven daysВҰ90052 because \add *he's\add* blessedВҰ90062 your harvest and \add вүҲall your other work\add*.
\p
\v 16 \add In summary,\add* all your men must travel three timesВҰ90075 each yearВҰ90077 to the placeВҰ90088 thatВҰ90089 your godВҰ90087 YahwehВҰ90086 will chooseВҰ90090: at the Flat Bread Celebration, at the Festival of Weeks, and at the Festival of Shelters. \add вүҲNo man should come empty-handed\add*,
\v 17 \add but rather,\add* each man \add вүҲmust give in proportion\add* to the blessingsВҰ90108 that yourВҰ90110 godВҰ90110 YahwehВҰ90109 has givenВҰ90112 you \add during that year\add*.
\s1 Strive for justice
\rem /s1 Municipal Judges and Officers; Justice for the People; Judges; The Administration of Justice
\p
\v 18 You must appointВҰ90119 judgesВҰ90117 and other officialsВҰ90118 throughout your tribesВҰ90130, in all the townsВҰ90124 thatВҰ90125 your godВҰ90127 YahwehВҰ90126 is giving to youВҰ90119. They must judgeВҰ90131 the peopleВҰ90134 \add вүҲfairly and correctly\add*.
\v 19 You mustn't \add вүҲpervert justiceВҰ90142 or give favours\add*. Don't accept bribes because a bribe causes \add an otherwise\add* wise person to \add вүҲignore evil\add* and \add вүҲmisrepresents what innocent people say\add*.\x + \xo 16:19: \xt Exo 23:6-8; Lev 19:15.\x*
\v 20 \add вүҲTrue justice is what you should aim for\add*, so that you'll occupy and liveВҰ90163 in the land that your godВҰ90171 YahwehВҰ90170 is giving you.
\s1 Prohibitions in worship and justice
\rem /s1 Forbidden Forms of Worship; Worshipping Other Gods
\p
\v 21 Never put an AsherahВҰ90180 pole near the altarВҰ90185 to yourВҰ90187 godВҰ90187 YahwehВҰ90186 thatВҰ90188 you'll build for yourselfВҰ90179,\x + \xo 16:21: \xt Exo 34:13.\x*
\v 22 andВҰ90194 don'tВҰ90194 erect any stone pillarsВҰ90198 thatВҰ90199 yourВҰ90202 godВҰ90202 YahwehВҰ90201 hatesВҰ90200.\x + \xo 16:22: \xt Lev 26:1.\x*
\c 17
\p
\v 1 Don'tВҰ90221 sacrificeВҰ90207 any \add вүҲanimal\add* to your god YahwehВҰ90208 that has any blemishВҰ90215 or defect, because \add *he\add* detests that.
\p
\v 2 InВҰ90248 any of the townsВҰ90231 that yourВҰ90229 god YahwehВҰ90234 is giving you, if you discover any man or womanВҰ90241 who does evil by disobeying the agreement that \add *he's\add* made with you
\v 3 andВҰ90254 \add вүҲworshippedВҰ90258\add* otherВҰ90257 godsВҰ90256, or the sunВҰ90260, moonВҰ90263, or starsвҖ”all of whichВҰ90269 I'veВҰ90272 prohibited you from doing,\x + \xo 17:3: \xt Exo 22:20.\x*
\v 4 and it it's reported to you, and you listenВҰ90277 and investigateВҰ90278 it thoroughlyВҰ90279, and it's true that this detestableВҰ90285 thingВҰ90285 was done in YisraelВҰ90287,
\v 5 you must bringВҰ90289 that man or woman out to the \add town\add* gatesВҰ90308, andВҰ90289 \add вүҲexecute them by throwing rocksВҰ90317 at them\add*.
\v 6 \add Note that\add* that person can only be executed if there's at least two witnesses \add as evidence\add*вҖ”no one can be put to death on the testimony of just one witness.\x + \xo 17:6: \xt Num 35:30; Deu 19:15; Mat 18:16; 2Cor 13:1; 1Tim 5:19; Heb 10:28.\x*
\v 7 \add вүҲThe witnessesВҰ90340 must be the ones to throw the firstВҰ90344 rocks\add* then all the other peopleВҰ90349 after that, and that's how you'll remove evilВҰ90352 \add вүҲfrom yourВҰ90353 society\add*.\x + \xo 17:7: \xt 1Cor 5:13.\x*
\rem /s1 Law Courts; Legal Decisions by Priests and Judges
\p
\v 8 If a case is too difficultВҰ90357 for you yourselves to judge \add вүҲ(e.g., two parties claimingВҰ90371 bloodshed, or lawsuits, or assaultsВҰ90374, or other disputesВҰ90370 within your townsВҰ90377)\add*, you must leave town and goВҰ90379 to the placeВҰ90382 thatВҰ90383 your godВҰ90386 YahwehВҰ90385 is going to chooseВҰ90384.
\v 9 You should goВҰ90389 to the \add вүҲLeviticalВҰ90393 priestsВҰ90392\add* and to the judgeВҰ90396 \add вүҲon duty there\add* and they will \add вүҲproduce\add* a judgement.
\v 10 Whatever the decisionВҰ90412 is that's made at the placeВҰ90418 YahwehВҰ90422 will chooseВҰ90421, \add вүҲthat's the verdict that must be applied to the case\add*вҖ”
\v 11 accept their judgement and do what they sayВҰ90440 without making any adjustments to their decisionВҰ90437.
\v 12 Anyone who \add вүҲshows\add* contemptВҰ90459 for \add the decision of\add* the judgeВҰ90475 or the priestВҰ90464 who's standingВҰ90465 thereВҰ90467 serving yourВҰ90471 godВҰ90471 YahwehВҰ90470, thenВҰ90455 that person must be executed \add вүҲto\add* remove that evilВҰ90480 from YisraelВҰ90481,
\v 13 thenВҰ90483 all the peopleВҰ90485 will hearВҰ90486 \add about it\add* and be afraidВҰ90487, and \add вүҲit'll stamp out such arrogance\add*.
\s1 Expectations for a king
\rem /s1 Limitations of Royal Authority; The King; Guidelines for a King; Instructions concerning a King
\p
\v 14 When you enter the land that your godВҰ90501 YahwehВҰ90500 is aboutВҰ90502 to giveВҰ90502 you, then occupy and live in it, and you sayВҰ90507 that you need a kingВҰ90510 over you like all the surrounding countriesВҰ90513 have,\x + \xo 17:14: \xt 1Sam 8:5.\x*
\v 15 you can appoint the king over you that YahwehВҰ90523 choosesВҰ90522. Your king must be \add вүҲan Israeli\add*вҖ”\add вүҲnever allow a foreignerВҰ90536 to become your king\add*.
\v 16 However, he mustn't acquire a large number of horses for himself, and he should never send peopleВҰ90555 to EgyptВҰ90556 to buy horses, because YahwehВҰ90560 has told you all to never go back that way againВҰ90568.\x + \xo 17:16: \xt 1Ki 10:28; 2Ch 1:16; 9:28.\x*
\v 17 He mustn't \add вүҲtake a lot of wivesВҰ90574 for himself\add* \add вүҲor else he might stop\add* \add worshipping Yahweh\add*. Nor should he \add вүҲaccumulate too much\add* goldВҰ90579 andВҰ90570 silverВҰ90578.\x + \xo 17:17: a \xt 1Ki 11:1-8; \xo b \xt 1Ki 10:14-22,27; 2Ch 1:15; 9:27.\x*
\p
\v 18 Once he's sitting on his \add вүҲroyal\add* throneВҰ90589, he must copy for himself the instructions on the scrollВҰ90600 \add вүҲthat's in the custody of\add* the LeviticalВҰ90603 priestsВҰ90602,
\v 19 thenВҰ90605 he must keep it with him and read \add some of\add* it every day so that he learnsВҰ90614 to honour his godВҰ90619 YahwehВҰ90618вҖ”being careful to follow all the instructions and regulationsВҰ90630 written in it
\v 20 so that he won'tВҰ90634 \add вүҲthink he's more valued than his fellow citizens\add*, and so that he doesn't \add вүҲignore those instructions even slightly\add*. \add вүҲAs a result, him and his descendantsВҰ90653 will rule as kings in YisraelВҰ90655 for many years\add*.
\c 18
\s1 Portions for Levites
\rem /s1 Offerings for Priests and Levites; Privileges of Priests and Levites; Gifts for the Priests and Levites; The Share of the Priests
\p
\v 1 None of the LevitesВҰ90662 (including the priestsВҰ90661) will receive \add any land as\add* an inheritance like the \add вүҲother Israelis\add*. \add вүҲInstead, the people's offeringsВҰ90672 to YahwehВҰ90673 will be theirВҰ90674 inheritance to sustain them\add*.
\v 2 \add Yes,\add* unlike \add вүҲfellow Israelis\add*, they won'tВҰ90678 have any inherited \add land\add*вҖ”YahwehВҰ90685 is their inheritance like he told them.\x + \xo 18:2: \xt Num 18:20.\x*
\p
\v 3 This is the requirement that the peopleВҰ90699 do for the priests: whenever they bring a bullВҰ90705 or a sheepВҰ90708 as a sacrifice, they must give the shoulderВҰ90711, the cheeks, and the stomachВҰ90713 to the priestВҰ90710.
\v 4 Also youВҰ90722 must giveВҰ90722 \add @the Levites\add* the firstfruits of your grainВҰ90716, your grape juice, your \add olive\add* oil, and the wool shorn from your sheepВҰ90721,
\v 5 because your godВҰ90730 YahwehВҰ90729 choseВҰ90728 them out of all your tribesВҰ90733 for them and their descendants permanently to serve \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 6 If a LeviteВҰ90749 chooses to move \add his family\add* from their town in any part of YisraelВҰ90754 and sincerely wants to go to the placeВҰ90767 thatВҰ90768 YahwehВҰ90771 will chooseВҰ90770,
\v 7 thenВҰ90773 he can join the other LevitesВҰ90780 thereВҰ90782 to serve his godВҰ90776 YahwehВҰ90775
\v 8 \add вүҲand must be given a portionВҰ90786 like all the others\add*. (\add вүҲHe can keep anything he got from the sale of their familyВҰ90793 home\add*.)
\s1 Warnings against divination and magic
\rem /s1 Detestable Practices; A Call to Holy Living; Child-Sacrifice, Divination, and Magic Prohibited; Warning against Pagan Practices
\p
\v 9 When you enter the land thatВҰ90802 your godВҰ90805 YahwehВҰ90804 is aboutВҰ90806 to giveВҰ90806 you, don'tВҰ90808 \add вүҲimitate the disgusting habits\add* of thoseВҰ90814 peoples.
\v 10 There mustn't be anyoneВҰ90820 among you who passes their son or daughterВҰ90823 through fireВҰ90824, or who uses divinationВҰ90825 or omensВҰ90828 \add to try to tell the future\add*, or who practices sorceryВҰ90829,\x + \xo 18:10: a \xt Lev 19:26; \xo b \xt Exo 22:18.\x*
\v 11 \add вүҲor who puts spellsВҰ90832 on people, or who tries to talk to spiritsВҰ90835 of deceased people\add*,
\v 12 because anyoneВҰ90847 who does those things is abhorrent to Yahweh. It's because of those kinds of things that yourВҰ90856 godВҰ90853 Yahweh will drive \add @those other peoples\add* \add вүҲaway ahead of you\add*.
\v 13 You must be a blameless \add nation in the eyes\add* of yourВҰ90862 godВҰ90862 YahwehВҰ90861,\x + \xo 18:13: \xt Mat 5:48.\x*
\v 14 because the groups that you'll \add вүҲexpel from the land\add* \add вүҲrely on\add* fortune-tellers and divinersВҰ90878, but yourВҰ90889 godВҰ90889 YahwehВҰ90888 won'tВҰ90881 allow you to do that.
\s1 Yahweh promises to send prophets
\rem /s1 The Prophet; The Promise to Send a Prophet; True and False Prophets; A New Prophet Like Moses
\p
\v 15 YourВҰ90892 godВҰ90898 YahwehВҰ90897 will \add вүҲselect a man from amongВҰ90892 youВҰ90892 and send him as\add* a prophetВҰ90891 like me. You must \add вүҲtake notice of\add* him,\x + \xo 18:15: \xt Acts 3:22; 7:37.\x*
\v 16 since you \add вүҲbegged\add* your god Yahweh from \add the bottom of Mt.\add* Horev when you said, вҖң\add вүҲWe can'tВҰ90913 handle directly hearing\add* the voiceВҰ90918 of our god Yahweh and \add вүҲlooking at this terrible\add* fireВҰ90923. \add Let us go home\add* so we won'tВҰ90913 die \add here\add*.вҖқ
\v 17 ThenВҰ90933 YahwehВҰ90934 told me, вҖң\add вүҲThey're right in what they're saying\add*.
\v 18 I'll \add вүҲchoose a prophetВҰ90940 from amongВҰ90943 them and see him\add*. I'll \add вүҲtell him what to say, and he can pass it on\add* to them,
\v 19 andВҰ90957 if anyone doesn't listenВҰ90962 to what he says \add вүҲwith my authority\add*, I'll \add вүҲpunish thatВҰ90966 person\add* \add as if they ignored me\add*.\x + \xo 18:19: \xt Acts 3:23.\x*
\v 20 However, if the prophet \add вүҲsays things that I didn'tВҰ90982 tell him to say but claims they came from me\add*, or if he speaks in the name of otherВҰ90990 godsВҰ90989, then that prophet must die.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Now if youВҰ90996 ask yourselves, вҖңHow can weВҰ90999 \add вүҲrecognise a messageВҰ91002 thatВҰ91003 didn'tВҰ91004 come from\add* YahwehВҰ91007?вҖқ
\v 22 then when the prophet speaksВҰ91010 in Yahweh's nameВҰ91012 but that thingВҰ91017 doesn't happenВҰ91016, then you'll know that it didn'tВҰ91014 comeВҰ91019 from Yahweh. The prophet spoke it \add вүҲassuming that I'd want that\add*, but you don'tВҰ91014 need to be afraidВҰ91031 of him.
\c 19
\s1 The refuge cities
\rem /s1 Cities of Refuge; Laws concerning the Cities of Refuge; The Cities of Refuge
\r (Num. 35:9-28; Josh. 20:1-9)
\p
\v 1 WhenВҰ91044 your god YahwehВҰ91038 destroys those peoples where \add *he's\add* giving you the land, and you occupy the land and live in their cities and housesВҰ91054,
\v 2 you must select three citiesВҰ91057\x + \xo 19:1-13: \xt Josh 20:1-9.\x* \add вүҲspread across\add* the land thatВҰ91062 YahwehВҰ91063 is giving you.
\v 3 You must \add вүҲdefine\add* threeВҰ91072 borders and \add вүҲbuild roadsВҰ91071\add* in the land thatВҰ91077 your godВҰ91080 YahwehВҰ91079 is giving youВҰ91078 to inherit. \add вүҲAnyone who kills another person\add* can then flee to \add @one of those cities\add*.
\v 4 This is the rule for someone who's killed another person and flees to liveВҰ91095 thereВҰ91094: if \add вүҲthey've accidentally killed another person\add* and \add вүҲhad no hate for that person from past events\add*,
\v 5 (for example, if two men went into the forestВҰ91117 to chop wood and an axeВҰ91122 head flew off its handle and killed the other man) thenВҰ91112 \add @that accidental killer\add* can flee to one of those citiesВҰ91140 and liveВҰ91143 there.
\v 6 \add вүҲOtherwise a friend or relative of the dead person might chase the killer in a sudden rage\add* and overtakeВҰ91156 and kill \add @the accidental killer\add* if \add вүҲthe city was too far away\add*. \add вүҲHowever, the killer doesn't deserve deathВҰ91167\add* if they hadn't hated that person \add вүҲfrom past events\add*вҖ”
\v 7 that's why I'mВҰ91179 ordering you to select threeВҰ91182 citiesВҰ91183 \add вүҲfor this\add*.
\p
\v 8 \add Then in the future,\add* if your godВҰ91192 YahwehВҰ91191 extends your \add вүҲterritoryВҰ91195\add* as he promised your ancestorsВҰ91209 that he would do, and gives you all the land that he told \add *them\add* about,
\v 9 and if you're \add still\add* followingВҰ91220 all theseВҰ91244 instructions thatВҰ91221 I'mВҰ91222 giving you today (lovingВҰ91225 your godВҰ91229 YahwehВҰ91228 and \add always\add* \add вүҲobeying what he's said\add*), then you'll \add need to\add* add three more \add refuge\add* citiesВҰ91241 for your \add вүҲcountry\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲThat's so\add* innocentВҰ91249 \add вүҲpeople won't be killed\add* in the land that your godВҰ91254 YahwehВҰ91253 is giving you, andВҰ91246 \add вүЎso that\add* you \add вүҲwon't be found guilty of the murder of that accidental killer\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever, if someone hates another person and then ambushes them and kills them\add*, and then fleesВҰ91276 to one of those citiesВҰ91280,
\v 12 thenВҰ91283 the eldersВҰ91284 from their home town \add вүҲshould go and get that person\add* from the \add @refuge cityВҰ91285\add* and handВҰ91291 \add @that killer\add* over to \add вүҲthe relatives handling the case\add*, and \add @the murderer\add* must be executed.
\v 13 YouВҰ91305 must \add вүҲshow no mercy to murderers\add* \add but they must be executed\add* \add вүҲso that the country isn't responsible for the bloodВҰ91302 of innocentВҰ91304 people\add*, and then things will go well for you.
\s1 Respecting boundaries
\rem /s1 Property Boundaries; Ancient Property Lines; Concern for Justice
\p
\v 14 \add Once you're\add* in the land thatВҰ91314 your godВҰ91323 YahwehВҰ91322 is giving you to occupy, you mustn't move the boundaryВҰ91312 markers which were set \add вүҲbetween you and your neighbourВҰ91313\add*.\x + \xo 19:14: \xt Deu 27:17.\x*
\s1 Concerning witnesses in court
\rem /s1 Witnesses; Law concerning Witnesses; Concerning Witnesses
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲA single witness must not be used to condemn anyoneВҰ91333\add*вҖ”a matterВҰ91360 \add вүҲmust only be considered proven if there's at least\add* twoВҰ91350 or threeВҰ91356 witnesses.\x + \xo 19:15: \xt Num 35:30; Deu 17:6; Mat 18:16; Yhn 8:17; 2Cor 13:1; 1Tim 5:19; Heb 10:28.\x*
\v 16 \add Suppose\add* that a вҖҳwitnessВҰ91365вҖҷ \add вүҲbrought a false allegation\add* against a man,
\v 17 thenВҰ91373 \add вүҲboth parties\add* must go and standВҰ91373 \add вүҲin front of\add* YahwehВҰ91382вҖ”\add вүҲin front of the priestsВҰ91384 and judgesВҰ91385 on duty at that time\add*.
\v 18 The judgesВҰ91392 must investigate \add the case\add* thoroughlyВҰ91393, and if the witness is \add вүҲproved to be lying\add* (\add вүҲand so falsely accusing a fellow citizen\add*),
\v 19 you must \add вүҲgive the false witness the punishment\add* that was plannedВҰ91406 for \add вүҲthe person falsely accused\add*, andВҰ91403 that's how you can remove the evilВҰ91410 from among yourВҰ91411 \add nation\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ91413 the \add вүҲrest of the people\add* will hearВҰ91414 \add about that\add* andВҰ91413 be afraidВҰ91415 \add вүҲto do that kind of evilВҰ91422 thingВҰ91421 in yourВҰ91424 country\add*.
\v 21 Don't pity \add violent people\add*: it's a life for a life, an eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth, a hand for a hand, andВҰ91426 a foot for a foot.\x + \xo 19:21: \xt Exo 21:23-25; Lev 24:19-20; Mat 5:38.\x*
\c 20
\s1 Rules of battle
\rem /s1 Concerning War; Going to War; Regulations concerning War; Rules of Warfare
\p
\v 1 When you goВҰ91443 out to battle against your enemiesВҰ91447, and seeВҰ91448 \add many\add* horsesВҰ91449 and chariotsВҰ91450 \add вүҲand a bigger army than yoursВҰ91453\add*, don'tВҰ91454 be afraidВҰ91455 of them, because your godВҰ91460 YahwehВҰ91459 who \add вүҲhelped you out of\add* EgyptВҰ91464 is with you.
\v 2 As you approach the \add place of\add* battleВҰ91470, the \add high\add* priestВҰ91472 must go andВҰ91466 stand in front of the \add вүҲwarriors\add*,
\v 3 and tell them, вҖңListen, YisraelВҰ91481, you're about to battleВҰ91485 against your enemiesВҰ91488. Don't \add вүҲbe nervous\add* or afraidВҰ91495, and don'tВҰ91489 tremble or be terrifiedВҰ91501 of them,
\v 4 because your godВҰ91506 YahwehВҰ91505 will go with you to fightВҰ91509 for you against your enemiesВҰ91513. \add He'll\add* \add вүҲgiveВҰ91514 you victoryВҰ91514\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ91517 the \add вүҲofficersВҰ91518 must ask\add* the people, вҖңIs there anyone here who's just builtВҰ91527 a new house and hasn't dedicated it yet? If so, he can go home in case he dies in battleВҰ91539 and \add вүҲsomeone else gets to\add* dedicate his house.
\v 6 Is there anyone who's plantedВҰ91549 a vineyardВҰ91550 and not \add вүҲbenefitted from it yet\add*? If so, he can goВҰ91553 home in case he dies in battleВҰ91559 and \add вүҲsomeone else enjoysВҰ91552 the grape harvest\add*.
\v 7 Is there anyone who's gotten engaged, but not yet married? If so, he can goВҰ91573 home in case he died in battleВҰ91579 andВҰ91564 \add вүҲsomeone else marries\add* her.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ91584 those officersВҰ91585 should also ask, вҖңIs there anyone who's scared or \add вүҲfearful\add*? If so, he should goВҰ91597 home \add вүҲso his fear doesn't spread to others\add*.вҖқ
\v 9 Once they've finishedВҰ91609 speakingВҰ91611 with the \add вүҲfighting men\add*, they must appointВҰ91615 commandersВҰ91616 over \add *them\add*.
\p
\v 10 When youВҰ91624 approach a cityВҰ91627 \add вүҲready to attack it\add*, \add first\add* call out to offerВҰ91630 peaceВҰ91632 \add for surrender\add*,
\v 11 and if they \add вүҲagree to surrender\add* and open the city gates, thenВҰ91634 they'll all be forcedВҰ91650 to work for youВҰ91651.
\v 12 \add вүҲButВҰ91653\add* if they \add вүҲrefuse your terms\add* andВҰ91653 decide to fight againstВҰ91659 you, thenВҰ91653 you should besiege that city.
\v 13 Then when your godВҰ91669 YahwehВҰ91668 \add вүҲhelps you to capture itВҰ91667\add*, you must \add вүҲkill\add* everyВҰ91674 male in that city.
\v 14 \add вүҲHowever,\add* you can take the womenВҰ91682 and childrenВҰ91683 and cattle and everything \add else\add* in the cityВҰ91688 as plunderВҰ91692 for yourself. You can enjoy your enemies' possessions thatВҰ91699 YahwehВҰ91701 has givenВҰ91700 to you.
\v 15 That's \add вүҲhow you should treat\add* the cities located far from youвҖ”it doesn't apply to the cities of nearby peoples.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲIn contrast,\add* the citiesВҰ91723 of those peoplesВҰ91724 thatВҰ91726 your godВҰ91728 YahwehВҰ91727 is giving you as an inheritanceВҰ91731, \add вүҲyou mustn't leave a single living thingВҰ91736 alive\add*
\v 17 because you must complete eliminate the Hittes, the AmoritesВҰ91743, the CanaanitesВҰ91744, the PerizzitesВҰ91745, the HivitesВҰ91746, and the Yevusites. Do that just as your godВҰ91751 YahwehВҰ91750 commandedВҰ91749 you
\v 18 so that they don'tВҰ91755 teachВҰ91757 you to sinВҰ91765 against YahwehВҰ91766 by doingВҰ91759 any of their abhorrent activities that they do for their godsВҰ91764.
\p
\v 19 When you besiege a cityВҰ91775 \add вүҲfor a lengthy period\add*, battling against it to captureВҰ91780 it, you mustn't use yourВҰ91801 axes to destroyВҰ91783 its trees, because you can eat \add вүҲtheir fruit\add*. Don't cut them down because the trees in the countrysideВҰ91799 \add вүҲaren'tВҰ91781 likely to turn around and attack you\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲHowever, the trees that aren'tВҰ91811 fruit trees\add* can be cut down and make \add вүҲladders and towers to enable you to go over the walls and capture the cityВҰ91823 that is resisting\add* you.
\c 21
\s1 Handling an unseen murder
\rem /s1 Law concerning Murder by Persons Unknown; Atonement for an Unsolved Murder; Concerning Unsolved Murders; Cleansing for Unsolved Murder
\p
\v 1 If a \add вүҲdead body\add* is foundВҰ91836 in the land that your godВҰ91841 YahwehВҰ91840 is aboutВҰ91842 to giveВҰ91842 you, and \add it appears that\add* \add @that person\add* had been killedВҰ91850 out in the countrysideВҰ91846 \add вүҲby some unknown person\add*,
\v 2 thenВҰ91852 your eldersВҰ91853 and your judgesВҰ91854 must goВҰ91852 out and \add вүҲwork out the distance to each of the towns close to thatВҰ91859 victim\add*.
\v 3 ThenВҰ91863 the eldersВҰ91870 from that closest town must select a heiferВҰ91873 from their herd that's \add вүҲnever been yoked or had to pull anything\add*,
\v 4 andВҰ91886 take it down into a valleyВҰ91910 thatВҰ91897 has a stream \add but the ground\add* has never been ploughed or planted. They must breakВҰ91904 its neck thereВҰ91906
\v 5 and the Levitical priestsВҰ91913 must approach itВҰ91928 because yourВҰ91920 godВҰ91920 Yahweh has chosenВҰ91918 them to serve himВҰ91921 and \add вүҲpronounceВҰ91922 blessingsВҰ91922 on Yahweh's behalf\add*, and to \add вүҲgive rulings\add* on disputesВҰ91931 and assaults.
\v 6 ThenВҰ91936 all the eldersВҰ91937 from that closest town must wash theirВҰ91947 handsВҰ91947 over the heiferВҰ91950 whose neck was brokenВҰ91951 in the valleyВҰ91952,
\v 7 andВҰ91954 sayВҰ91955, вҖңWe didn'tВҰ91957 murder this person, nor did we see who did it.
\v 8 YahwehВҰ91976, forgive your \add вүҲIsraeli\add* people who you rescued \add from Egypt\add*. Don't count us as guilty for murdering an innocentВҰ91981 person.вҖқ
\m \add When they do that,\add* \add вүҲYisraelВҰ91972 will be forgiven for that murder\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲThat's how\add* \add @your country\add* will removeВҰ91990 from yourselves the guiltВҰ91991 of shedding innocentВҰ91992 bloodВҰ91991, when you do what's rightВҰ91997 in Yahweh's eyesВҰ91998.
\s1 Handling captured women
\rem /s1 Female Captives; Marriage to a Captive Woman; Concerning Women Prisoners of War; Marrying a Captive Woman
\p
\v 10 When you goВҰ92004 out to battle against your enemiesВҰ92008 and your godВҰ92011 YahwehВҰ92010 \add вүҲhelps you defeat them\add*, and you \add вүҲcapture some of theirВҰ92014 people\add*
\v 11 andВҰ92016 \add вүҲyou notice an attractive\add* woman that you'd like to take as a wife,
\v 12 thenВҰ92028 you must \add publicly\add* take her to your houseВҰ92032. There you must shaveВҰ92033 off her hair andВҰ92028 trim her nailsВҰ92040,
\v 13 and \add вүҲdiscard the clothesВҰ92045 she was wearing when she was captured\add*. She must stay in that houseВҰ92049, and be allowed an \add entire\add* monthВҰ92057 to mournВҰ92050 for \add herВҰ92046 parents\add* before she's taken to be your wife.
\v 14 If you're not happy with her, thenВҰ92068 you can'tВҰ92071 sell herвҖ”you must release her to goВҰ92074 wherever sheВҰ92075 wantsВҰ92075 becauseВҰ92085 you've already humiliated her.
\s1 The oldest son's inheritance
\rem /s1 The Right of the Firstborn; Rights of the Firstborn; Concerning the First Son's Inheritance
\p
\v 15 If a manВҰ92093 has twoВҰ92094 wivesВҰ92095 \add вүҲand loves one more than the otherВҰ92098\add*, \add вүҲbut\add* they've both given birthВҰ92100 to sonsВҰ92103 for him \add вүҲbut the oldest son is from the wife he dislikes\add*,
\v 16 thenВҰ92111 \add вүҲwhen he assigns his inheritance to his sonsВҰ92116, he mustn't favour the son of the favourite wife over thatВҰ92118 eldest son\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲInstead,\add* he must acknowledgeВҰ92145 the son of the wife he dislikes, and given him double of everything, because \add @that son\add* is the beginningВҰ92158 of his strengthВҰ92159, and the largest share belongs to him.
\s1 The rebellious child
\rem /s1 A Rebellious Son; Concerning a Disobedient Son; Rebellious Children; Dealing with a Rebellious Son
\p
\v 18 If a person has a stubbornВҰ92170, rebelliousВҰ92171 son who won't listen to the voice of his parents, and they \add вүҲtell him off\add*, but he \add still\add* won't listen to them,
\v 19 thenВҰ92187 his parents must \add вүҲphysically\add* bringВҰ92191 him to the eldersВҰ92195 at the gateВҰ92199 of his \add вүҲhometown\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ92202 they must tell \add *those\add* eldersВҰ92205, вҖңOurВҰ92213 son is stubbornВҰ92209 and rebelliousВҰ92210 and pays no attention to what we sayВҰ92202вҖ”he's a gluttonВҰ92214 and a drunkardВҰ92215.вҖқ
\v 21 Then all the menВҰ92220 from that place must \add вүҲexecute him by throwing rocksВҰ92222 at\add* him, \add вүҲthus\add* removing that evilВҰ92225 from among you. Then everyone in YisraelВҰ92229 will hearВҰ92230 about it andВҰ92217 be afraid \add вүҲto imitate him\add*.
\s1 Miscellaneous rules
\rem /s1 Various Regulations; Miscellaneous Laws; Various Laws
\p
\v 22 If someone has committed a \add вүҲcrime\add* worthy of death, and \add @that person\add* is executed and you hang their body on a tree,
\v 23 then the corpseВҰ92252 mustn't remainВҰ92251 overnightВҰ92251 on the treeвҖ”it must be buried that same dayВҰ92260, because anyoneВҰ92266 who's hangedВҰ92266 is cursedВҰ92264 by GodВҰ92265 and you mustn't defile your country that your god YahwehВҰ92273 is aboutВҰ92275 to give you as an inheritanceВҰ92277. \x + \xo 21:23: \xt Gal 3:13.\x*
\c 22
\p
\v 1 If you see \add вүҲsomeone else's\add* cowВҰ92285 or sheepВҰ92290 that \add вүҲhas strayed away\add*, don'tВҰ92280 \add вүҲact as though you didn'tВҰ92280 see it\add*. Take it back to \add вүҲits owner\add*.\x + \xo 22:1-4: \xt Exo 23:4-5.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the owner doesn't \add live\add* near you, or if you don'tВҰ92300 knowВҰ92305 who it is, then take the animal to your houseВҰ92310. It can stay with you untilВҰ92313 the owner comes looking for it, then you must give it to them.
\v 3 \add вүҲSimilarly\add* if it's a donkeyВҰ92322 or clothing or anything else that someone's lost, \add вүҲdon'tВҰ92337 pretend that you never saw it\add*.
\p
\v 4 If you see \add вүҲsomeone else's\add* donkeyВҰ92347 or cowВҰ92350 that's fallen beside the roadВҰ92352, don'tВҰ92342 \add вүҲact as though you didn'tВҰ92342 see it\add*. You must try to help \add @the owner\add* to get the animal up.
\p
\v 5 Women mustn't \add вүҲwear\add* men's clothes, andВҰ92369 men mustn't \add вүҲwear\add* women's clothes. Your godВҰ92378 YahwehВҰ92377 \add вүҲhates\add* \add вүҲpeople who do things like\add* that.
\p
\v 6 If \add вүҲyou happen to find\add* a bird's nest in a tree or on the ground, and the mother bird is sitting in the nest on itsВҰ92387 eggs or with the baby birds, don'tВҰ92413 take \add вүҲboth the mother bird and the babies\add*.
\v 7 You may take the \add вүҲeggs or the baby birds\add*, but you must \add вүҲallow the motherВҰ92425 bird to fly away\add*. Do that so that things will go well for you and so that you'll live \add in the land\add* for a long time.
\p
\v 8 When you buildВҰ92440 a new house, be sure to include a railing around your \add flat\add* roof, so you won'tВҰ92446 \add вүҲbe guilty of having caused someone's death\add* if a person falls off it \add and dies\add*.
\p
\v 9 Don't \add вүҲplant a crop\add* in yourВҰ92461 vineyard, because then the harvestВҰ92466 of the crop andВҰ92470 the fruit from the vineyard will \add both\add* \add ?вүҲbe defiled\add*.\f + \fr 22:9 \ft Or possibly, become sacred.\f*\x + \xo 22:9-11: \xt Lev 19:19.\x*
\p
\v 10 Don't plough with a cowВҰ92477 andВҰ92479 a donkeyВҰ92479 \add harnessed\add* togetherВҰ92480.
\p
\v 11 Don't wear \add clothes\add* with a mix of wool andВҰ92487 linenВҰ92487.
\p
\v 12 \add Twist threads together to\add* make tasselsВҰ92491 and \add sew them\add* onto the fourВҰ92497 cornersВҰ92498 of yourВҰ92499 cloakВҰ92499.\x + \xo 22:12: \xt Num 15:37-41.\x*
\s1 Rules about marriage and rape
\rem /s1 Laws concerning Sexual Relations; Marriage Violations; Regulations for Sexual Purity; Laws concerning Sexual Purity
\p
\v 13 If a manВҰ92509 takes a wifeВҰ92510 and \add вүҲsleeps with\add* her, then hates her
\v 14 and accuses her of shameful things, \add вүҲdestroying her reputation\add* and \add вүҲclaiming that she hadn't been\add* a virginВҰ92535,
\v 15 thenВҰ92537 the young woman'sВҰ92539 parents must show the evidence of herВҰ92541 virginityВҰ92545\f + \fr 22:15 \ft Presumably, the blood-stained sheet.\f* to the eldersВҰ92550 at the cityВҰ92551 gateВҰ92552.
\v 16 TheВҰ92567 youngВҰ92556 woman's fatherВҰ92555 must tell the eldersВҰ92563 how he gave his daughterВҰ92566 to the man as a wife, but now he's rejected her
\v 17 and made shameful accusations about her not being a virgin. ThenВҰ92582 the parents must spreadВҰ92588 out that clothВҰ92589 and show it to the cityВҰ92592 eldersВҰ92591.
\v 18 ThenВҰ92594 the cityВҰ92596 eldersВҰ92595 must punishВҰ92602 that manВҰ92601
\v 19 and fine him a hundredВҰ92607 silverВҰ92608 \add coins\add* to be paid to the youngВҰ92611 woman'sВҰ92611 fatherВҰ92610 for defaming an IsraeliВҰ92618 virginВҰ92617. ThenВҰ92605 she'll remain as his wife and he'll be prohibited from \add ever\add* \add вүҲdivorcingВҰ92626\add* her.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add @the accusation\add* was true andВҰ92635 the youngВҰ92645 womanВҰ92645 \add вүҲhadn't been a virginВҰ92644\add*,
\v 21 thenВҰ92648 they must take \add *her\add* to the doorway of her father's house. ThenВҰ92648 the men from that cityВҰ92661 must \add вүҲexecute her by throwing rocksВҰ92662 at her\add*, because she's done a disgracefulВҰ92667 thing in YisraelВҰ92668вҖ”committing fornication \add вүҲwhile she still lived in\add* her father's house. That's how you'll remove evil from \add вүҲyourВҰ92674 country\add*.
\p
\v 22 If a man is discovered sleeping with another man's wife, then both of them must \add вүҲbe executed\add*. That's how you'll remove evil from YisraelВҰ92701.
\p
\v 23 If a youngВҰ92706 womanВҰ92706 is engaged to a man, and \add another\add* man sleeps with her,
\v 24 thenВҰ92717 you must execute both of them at the cityВҰ92725 gateВҰ92723 by throwing rocksВҰ92729 at themвҖ”the youngВҰ92733 womanВҰ92733 because she didn'tВҰ92739 scream, andВҰ92717 the man for defiling another man's \add вүҲfiancГ©e\add*.
\p
\v 25 If the man found the young womanВҰ92768 \add out\add* in the countrysideВҰ92763 and \add вүҲoverpowers\add* her and \add вүҲrapes\add* her, then the man \add вүҲmust be executed\add*
\v 26 but don'tВҰ92789 do anythingВҰ92792 to that woman because she's not worthy of deathВҰ92797. (This is similar to the case of a man murderingВҰ92805 another man \add out in the countryside\add*.)
\v 27 When that man foundВҰ92813 her \add out\add* in the countrysideВҰ92812, then sheВҰ92814 would have criedВҰ92814 out \add for helpВҰ92814\add*, but no \add вүҲone was thereВҰ92818 to save\add* her.
\p
\v 28 If a man \add вүҲoverpowers\add* a youngВҰ92827 womanВҰ92827 who's not engaged, and \add вүҲrapes\add* her, and it's discoveredВҰ92837,\x + \xo 22:28-29: \xt Exo 22:16-17.\x*
\v 29 that man must pay her fatherВҰ92843 fiftyВҰ92846 silverВҰ92847 coins, andВҰ92839 she'll become his wife becauseВҰ92852 he's violatedВҰ92854 her. He'll thenВҰ92839 be prohibited from \add ever\add* \add вүҲdivorcingВҰ92858\add* her.
\p
\v 30 A man must never \add вүҲsleep with\add* any of his father's wives \add ?вүҲbecause that would expose his father's nakedness\add*.\x + \xo 22:30: \xt Lev 18:8; 20:11; Deu 27:20.\x*
\c 23
\s1 Excluded people
\rem /s1 Exclusion From the Assembly; Regulations concerning Worship; Those Excluded from the Assembly; Exclusion from the Lord's People
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNo manВҰ92871 with crushed testicles\add* or \add вүҲa severed penis\add* is allowed to enter into Yahweh's assembly.
\p
\v 2 No \add ?вүҲillegitimate child\add*\f + \fr 23:2 \ft Or possibly, child from mixed parentage.\f* is allowed to enter into Yahweh's assemblyВҰ92891, even down to the tenth generation.
\p
\v 3 No Ammonite or Moabite is allowed to enter into Yahweh's assembly, even down past the tenthВҰ92904 generationВҰ92903\x + \xo 23:3-5: \xt Neh 13:1-2.\x*
\v 4 since they wouldn't \add even sell\add* you bread andВҰ92918 water when the people were travelling from Egypt \add to Canaan\add*. \add вүҲWhat's more,\add* they hired Beor's son Bil'am \add (Balaam)\add* (from Petor in Aram-Naharayim) to curse you
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever,\add* your god Yahweh \add вүҲtook no notice of\add* Bil'am and turned the curseВҰ92960 into a blessing because \add *he\add* loves you,\x + \xo 23:5: \xt Num 23:7вҖ“24:9.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲso\add* you must \add вүҲnever\add* strive for peace or prosperity for \add @the Ammonites or the Moabites\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add In contrast,\add* don't despise the Edomites because they're your \add вүҲcousins\add* \add (descendants of your ancestor Yitshak)\add*. And don't despise the Egyptians, because you \add вүҲlived there\add* as foreigners.
\v 8 The third generation \add (grandchildren)\add* of any of \add @Edomites or Egyptians\add* that live among you, may enter Yahweh's assembly.
\s1 Purity when at war
\rem /s1 Miscellaneous Regulations; Keeping the Military Camp Clean; Uncleanness in the Camp; Sanitary, Ritual, and Humanitarian Precepts
\p
\v 9 WhenВҰ93027 \add @your warriors\add* are out besieging your enemies, theyВҰ93020 you must avoid \add вүҲceremonial impurity\add*.
\v 10 If something happens at night to make a man вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ, then he must stay outside the camp \add the next day\add* \add вүҲandВҰ93038 not join the others\add*.
\v 11 That evening, he must wash himself in water, then once the sun has set, he may reenter the camp.
\p
\v 12 You must have a place outside your camp where you can go to \add relieve yourself\add*.
\v 13 You must have a spade among your equipment so that when you goВҰ93091 to relieve yourselfВҰ93088, you can dig a hole and then cover itВҰ93087 up afterwards,
\v 14 because your god Yahweh walks in your camp to give you victory \add вүҲto defeat\add* your enemies, so your camp must be sacred so he won't see anything вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ and turnВҰ93107 away from you.
\s1 Various regulations
\rem /s1 Miscellaneous Laws; Various Laws
\p
\v 15 YouВҰ93115 mustn't \add вүҲreturn\add* any slaves to their master if they escaped and got to you.
\v 16 \add вүҲAllow them to stay\add* \add вүҲin your town\add* and don'tВҰ93139 \add вүҲmistreat\add* them.
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲDon't allow any Israeli man or woman to become a religious\add*\f + \fr 23:17 \ft Or, cultic.\f* prostitute.\x + \xo 23:17: \xt Lev 19:29.\x*
\v 18 \add вүҲDon't allow anyone womanВҰ93174 or man to bring any part of their wages\add* as a \add secular\add* prostitute into your god Yahweh's temple, because both \add @female and male prostitution\add* is abhorrent to \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 19 You mustn't charge interest to your fellow Israeli, whether it's money or food or anything else \add вүҲthat's borrowed\add*.\x + \xo 23:19-20: \xt Exo 22:25; Lev 25:36-37; Deu 15:7-11.\x*
\v 20 You can chargeВҰ93209 foreigners interest, but not \add fellow\add* Israelis so that your god Yahweh will bless \add @your society\add* in everything you do in the land that you're about to occupy.
\s1 Making promises to God
\p
\v 21 When you make a vow to your godВҰ93231 YahwehВҰ93230, don'tВҰ93226 put off fulfilling it, because \add *he\add* will \add вүҲhold you accountable\add* and \add not doing it\add* would \add count as\add* \add вүҲdisobeying him\add*.
\v 22 However \add of course\add*, \add вүҲif you don'tВҰ93254 make any vows, then you won'tВҰ93254 be guilty\add*,
\v 23 \add вүҲbut\add* if \add вүҲyou've spoken your promise out loud\add* to your god Yahweh, then you're \add вүҲobligated to keep itВҰ93274\add*.
\p
\v 24 IfВҰ93285 you're walking through \add вүҲsomeone else's\add* vineyard, you can eat as many grapes as \add вүҲyou like\add*, but you mustn't pick any to \add takeВҰ93281 away\add* in a container.
\v 25 \add вүҲSimilarly,\add* if you're going through \add вүҲsomeone else's\add* field of grain, you can \add crunch\add* \add вүҲa few kernels, but\add* you mustn't \add вүҲcut off any of the stalks\add*.
\c 24
\s1 Divorce and remarriage
\rem /s1 Divorce and Remarriage; Laws concerning Marriage and Divorce
\p
\v 1 When a man marriesВҰ93330 a womanВҰ93329, then \add вүҲfurther on he decides he doesn't want her because of something he foundВҰ93341 out about\add* her, then he must writeВҰ93345 a divorceВҰ93348 notice and give it to her, and send her out of hisВҰ93338 houseВҰ93352.\x + \xo 24:1: \xt Mat 5:31; 19:7; Mrk 10:4.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲAfter she leavesВҰ93354 that marriage\add*, \add вүҲanotherВҰ93360 manВҰ93358 is allowed to marry her\add*.
\v 3 If that \add вүҲsecond\add* husband \add also\add* \add вүҲdecides to divorce her by sending her away with a divorce notice\add*, or if he were to dieВҰ93375,
\v 4 then the firstВҰ93388 husbandВҰ93387 isn'tВҰ93406 allow to takeВҰ93393 herВҰ93387 back as his wife. \add That's\add* because she's been defiled and it would be abhorrent to Yahweh, and you mustn't defile the land thatВҰ93411 your godВҰ93413 Yahweh is giving you.
\rem /s1 Miscellaneous Laws; Various Laws
\p
\v 5 When a man \add вүҲis newly married\add*, he mustn't \add вүҲbe called for\add* the army \add вүҲor be given any other responsibilities\add*. He must be free for one year \add вүҲto establish his house\add* and \add вүҲto satisfy his new\add* wife.
\p
\v 6 \add If someone borrows money,\add* \add @the lender\add* mustn't takeВҰ93451 their millstone \add for grindingВҰ93453 grain\add* as a pledge, because \add вүҲthey need itВҰ93457 to stay alive\add*.
\s1 Abduction
\p
\v 7 If someone is foundВҰ93463 to have abducted a fellow IsraeliВҰ93469 to make them into a slaveВҰ93470 or to sell them, then that abductor must \add вүҲbe executed\add* in order to purgeВҰ93477 such evils from \add вүҲyourВҰ93479 countryВҰ93467\add*.\x + \xo 24:7: \xt Exo 21:16.\x*
\s1 Skin diseases
\p
\v 8 Stay on guardВҰ93485 against a plague of skin diseaseВҰ93484. Always follow what the priestsВҰ93493 andВҰ93487 LevitesВҰ93494 tell you all to do, as I've instructedВҰ93491 them.\x + \xo 24:8: \xt Lev 13:1вҖ“14:54.\x*
\v 9 Remember what yourВҰ93507 godВҰ93507 YahwehВҰ93506 did to Miryam on the way out of EgyptВҰ93511 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.\x + \xo 24:9: \xt Num 12:9-10.\x*
\p
\v 10 If you've lent anythingВҰ93520 to a neighbourВҰ93517, don'tВҰ93521 goВҰ93523 into their houseВҰ93526 to collectВҰ93527 their pledge.
\v 11 \add Just\add* \add вүҲwait\add* outsideВҰ93530, then the \add вүҲperson\add* you've lent something to will bringВҰ93537 the \add вүҲitem\add* out to you.
\v 12 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add вүҲthat personВҰ93546\add* is poor \add andВҰ93544 gives clothing or a blanket as security\add*, don'tВҰ93549 \add вүҲkeep it overnight\add*.
\v 13 Take it back to them when the sunВҰ93560 goes down so they'll \add be warm\add* when they sleepВҰ93561. Then they'll blessВҰ93563 you and your godВҰ93569 YahwehВҰ93568 \add вүҲwill be pleased with\add* you.
\p
\v 14 Don't oppressВҰ93574 any poor or needyВҰ93577 hiredВҰ93575 workers, whether they're fellow Israelis or foreigners who live in your townsВҰ93583.\x + \xo 24:14-15: \xt Lev 19:13.\x*
\v 15 At the end of each dayВҰ93585, pay them before sunset, because they need it to live on. Then they won'tВҰ93588 cry out to YahwehВҰ93608 againstВҰ93605 you and have him \add вүҲhold you accountable\add*.
\p
\v 16 Parents mustn't be executed for what their children have done, and children mustn't be executed for what their parents have done. Any person must only be executed for what they themselves have done.\x + \xo 24:16: \xt 2Ki 14:6; 2Ch 25:4; Eze 18:20.\x*
\p
\v 17 Don't pervert justiceВҰ93638 if it involves foreigners or orphans, andВҰ93641 don'tВҰ93636 takeВҰ93642 a widow'sВҰ93644 cloak as security \add for a loan\add*.\x + \xo 24:17-18: \xt Exo 23:9; Lev 19:33-34; Deu 27:19.\x*
\v 18 Remember that you were a slaveВҰ93648 in EgyptВҰ93650 andВҰ93646 yourВҰ93659 godВҰ93653 YahwehВҰ93652 \add вүҲrescued\add* you from thereВҰ93654. \add вүҲThat's why\add* I'm commandingВҰ93659 you to do those thingsвҖ”\add вүҲto be considerate about helping other people who are in need\add*.
\p
\v 19 When you \add вүҲharvest your crops\add*, if you forgetВҰ93671 a tied bundle in your field, don'tВҰ93674 go back to get itвҖ”it'll be for a \add resident\add* foreigner or an orphanВҰ93678 or widowВҰ93679 \add to pick up\add*, so that your god YahwehВҰ93683 can blessВҰ93682 everything \add вүҲthat you do\add*.\x + \xo 24:19-21: \xt Lev 19:9-10; 23:22.\x*
\v 20 When you beat your oliveВҰ93691 tree \add to make the fruit fall\add*, don'tВҰ93692 goВҰ93693 back over itВҰ93698 to pick the ones still on the tree. Those will be for the foreigner, or the orphanВҰ93696 or widowВҰ93697.
\v 21 \add Similarly,\add* when you \add вүҲpick your grapesВҰ93702\add* in the vineyardВҰ93703, don'tВҰ93704 \add вүҲgo back over the vines a second time\add*. Those will be for the foreigner, or the orphanВҰ93708 or widowВҰ93709.
\v 22 \add ^Don't forget\add* that you were a slaveВҰ93715 in EgyptВҰ93718вҖ”that's why I'mВҰ93722 instructing you to do those thingsВҰ93727.
\c 25
\s1 Whipping for criminals
\p
\v 1 If \add вүҲtwo parties have a disputeВҰ93734, they can request a judgement and the judges will decideВҰ93741 who's right and wrong\add*.
\v 2 If \add вүҲthe guiltyВҰ93756 person is deserving of punishment\add*, the judge will order him to lie on the ground \add вүҲwhere he'll be whipped in front of the judge as the crime deserves\add*.
\v 3 He may not \add вүҲreceive more than forty lashesВҰ93766\add* because that would be \add вүҲtoo degradingВҰ93778\add*.
\p
\v 4 Don't \add вүҲcover your cow's mouth when it's pulling the grain threshing sledge\add*.\x + \xo 25:4: \xt 1Cor 9:9; 1Tim 5:18.\x*
\s1 Continuing the family name
\rem /s1 Levirate Marriage; Duty to a Dead Brother
\p
\v 5 If some brothersВҰ93793 live \add вүҲon the same property\add* and one of them diesВҰ93795 without leaving a son, then the widow mustn't marry outside \add вүҲof the family\add*. HerВҰ93811 brother-in-law must takeВҰ93814 herВҰ93811 as a wifeВҰ93805 for himself and \add вүҲperformВҰ93817 the duty of\add* a brother-in-law.\x + \xo 25:5-6: \xt Mat 22:24; Mrk 12:19; Luk 20:28.\x*
\v 6 If she gives birth to a son \add in due course\add*, he'll be considered as the son of the brother who died, so that his \add family\add* name won'tВҰ93829 disappear from YisraelВҰ93833.
\v 7 \add вүҲButВҰ93835 if the dead man's brother doesn't want to marry the widow\add*, she must go to the eldersВҰ93849 at the city gate andВҰ93835 \add вүҲexplain that her brother-in-law is refusingВҰ93851 to do his duty to preserve\add* the dead brother's \add family\add* name in YisraelВҰ93856.\x + \xo 25:7-10: \xt Rut 4:7-8.\x*
\v 8 ThenВҰ93861 those eldersВҰ93864 must summonВҰ93861 \add @the brother\add* andВҰ93861 talk to him. \add вүҲHoweverВҰ93872,\add* if he \add вүҲreally\add* doesn't want to marryВҰ93873 herВҰ93873,
\v 9 thenВҰ93875 his \add late\add* brother's wife must go up to him in front of those eldersВҰ93879, and take his sandalВҰ93881 off his footВҰ93883 and spit in his faceВҰ93885. ThenВҰ93875 she must say, вҖҳThat's what happens to a man who won'tВҰ93892 \add вүҲstrengthen his brother's family\add*.вҖҷ
\v 10 \add After that,\add* the brother will be known in YisraelВҰ93904 as the man who had his sandalВҰ93907 taken off.
\s1 Being fair and honest
\rem /s1 Various Commands; Other Laws
\p
\v 11 If two menВҰ93913 are fighting each other, and one man's wifeВҰ93918 comesВҰ93917 to help herВҰ93927 husbandВҰ93923, and reaches out and grabs the other man's private parts,
\v 12 thenВҰ93931 you must cut her handВҰ93934 off. Don't pity her.
\s1 Don't all cheat
\p
\v 13 Don't keep two stone \add weights\add* in yourВҰ93944 bagвҖ”a \add вүҲlighter one\add* and a \add вүҲheavier one\add* \add for when you're buying and selling\add*.\x + \xo 25:13-16: \xt Lev 19:35-36.\x*
\v 14 Don't keep \add вүҲtwo measuring containers\add* in yourВҰ93955 houseВҰ93955вҖ”a smallerВҰ93959 \add one\add* and a largerВҰ93958 \add one\add*.
\v 15 You must use exact stone \add weightsВҰ93961\add* and \add вүҲmeasuringВҰ93967 containers\add* so that your godВҰ93981 YahwehВҰ93980 will prolong your time in the \add вүҲcountry\add* that he's giving youвҖ”
\v 16 \add *he\add* \add вүҲcan't stand people who cheat others\add*.
\s1 Eliminating the Amalekites
\rem /s1 The Command to Kill the Amalekites
\p
\v 17 \add ^Don't forget\add* what \add вүҲthe AmalekitesВҰ94004\add* did to you \add people\add* when you cameВҰ94006 out of EgyptВҰ94007.\x + \xo 25:17-19: \xt Exo 17:8-14; 1Sam 15:2-9.\x*
\v 18 They met you on the road, then attackedВҰ94012 you from behindВҰ94017вҖ”\add getting\add* the stragglers who were weak and exhaustedВҰ94020. They had no fear of GodВҰ94024.
\v 19 \add вүҲAt some point in the future when\add* your god YahwehВҰ94028 has givenВҰ94027 you the land to occupy as an inheritanceВҰ94043, andВҰ94026 \add вүҲyou're no longer being attacked by your\add* enemiesВҰ94034, you must \add вүҲeliminate the Amalekites so they won'tВҰ94052 be rememberedВҰ94048 anymore\add*. Don't forgetВҰ94053 \add to do thatВҰ94037\add*.
\c 26
\s1 Offerings for the beginning of the harvest
\rem /s1 Firstfruits and Tithes; Harvest Offerings and Tithes; Harvest Offerings; First Fruits and Tithes
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAfter\add* you've entered the land thatВҰ94063 your godВҰ94065 YahwehВҰ94064 is giving you as an inheritanceВҰ94068, and you occupy it and liveВҰ94070 there,
\v 2 \add each of\add* you should take the firstВҰ94074 part of your harvest in that place andВҰ94073 put it in a basketВҰ94089. ThenВҰ94073 take it to the place that your god YahwehВҰ94084 is going to chooseВҰ94095 to attach his name to.\x + \xo 26:2: \xt Exo 23:19.\x*
\v 3 Go to the \add high\add* priestВҰ94105 \add вүҲin office\add* at that time, andВҰ94102 tell him, вҖңI declareВҰ94112 today to yourВҰ94115 godВҰ94115 YahwehВҰ94114 that I've entered the land that \add *he\add* promised to our ancestorsВҰ94125 to giveВҰ94126 us.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 The priestВҰ94130 will takeВҰ94129 that basketВҰ94131 of food andВҰ94129 place it in frontВҰ94134 of your godВҰ94137 Yahweh's altarВҰ94135.
\v 5 ThenВҰ94139 in Yahweh's presence you should respond, вҖңMy ancestor was a wanderingВҰ94146 ArameanВҰ94145, and he went down to EgyptВҰ94149 with his \add вүҲsmallish family\add*, and livedВҰ94150 there and \add eventually\add* became a large and powerful peopleВҰ94152.
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ94162\add* the EgyptiansВҰ94164 treatedВҰ94162 us badly andВҰ94162 oppressedВҰ94165 usвҖ”forcing us into hard labourВҰ94168.
\v 7 WeВҰ94178 criedВҰ94171 out to our ancestors' godВҰ94175 YahwehВҰ94174 \add to help us\add*, and he heard our cry and sawВҰ94182 our suffering and oppressionВҰ94191 and the \add hard\add* labour.
\v 8 ThenВҰ94193 \add вүҲusing your greatВҰ94201 power\add* and \add вүҲdoing many miracles and other terrifying things\add*, you broughtВҰ94193 us out from EgyptВҰ94195
\v 9 andВҰ94205 broughtВҰ94205 us to this \add вүҲvery fertile\add* land
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ94222 now\add*, Yahweh, I've broughtВҰ94224 the firstВҰ94227 part of the harvest from that land that you've givenВҰ94232 me.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ94222 \add вүҲas\add* the basket is placedВҰ94235 in front of Yahweh, you must bow down in front of \add *him\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ94244 you can celebrate \add by eating\add* all the goodВҰ94247 things thatВҰ94248 your godВҰ94253 YahwehВҰ94252 has givenВҰ94249 to you and your householdВҰ94254, and it's \add also\add* for the LevitesВҰ94256 and the foreigners who live among you.
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲEvery thirdВҰ94272 year,\add* take a tenth of your harvest to the LevitesВҰ94276, the foreigners, and the orphansВҰ94278 and widowsВҰ94279 \add вүҲin your town\add* for them to eat and be content.\x + \xo 26:12: \xt Deu 14:28-29.\x*
\v 13 ThenВҰ94284 you must explain in frontВҰ94285 of your godВҰ94287 YahwehВҰ94286, вҖңI've taken the sacredВҰ94289 \add tenth\add* from my houseВҰ94292 and givenВҰ94294 itВҰ94294 to the LevitesВҰ94295, the foreigners, the orphansВҰ94297 and widowsВҰ94298, \add вүҲthus following all of your instructions\add*. I've not disobeyed or forgottenВҰ94309 your regulations.
\v 14 I never used any of it at a funeral, or took it \add вүҲin disobedience\add*, or offered it to the deadВҰ94325. I've listenВҰ94326 to the voiceВҰ94327 of my godВҰ94329 YahwehВҰ94328 and \add вүҲfollowed all your instructions\add*,
\v 15 \add вүҲso\add* look down from your sacredВҰ94337 home in the heavensВҰ94340 and blessВҰ94341 your peopleВҰ94344 YisraelВҰ94347 and the land that you've givenВҰ94351 us \add вүҲthat's so fertile\add*, as you had promised our ancestorsВҰ94355.
\rem /s1 Follow the Lord's Commands; The Lord's Own People; Concluding Exhortation; A Call to Obey the Lord's Commands
\p
\v 16 Today yourВҰ94366 godВҰ94365 YahwehВҰ94364 is commandingВҰ94366 youВҰ94366 to follow all theseВҰ94371 instructions and regulationsВҰ94370, so follow them \add вүҲsincerely and enthusiastically\add*.
\v 17 You have declaredВҰ94388 today that YahwehВҰ94387 is your godВҰ94392, and that you'll follow all his instructions and keepВҰ94395 his regulationsВҰ94396 and commandsВҰ94397 and rules, and listen to his voiceВҰ94400.
\v 18 \add вүҲAlso\add* today, YahwehВҰ94402 has declaredВҰ94403 that you are his peopleВҰ94407, like a \add prized\add* possessionВҰ94408, like he told you that you would be. You must follow all his instructions\x + \xo 26:18: \xt Exo 19:5; Deu 4:20; 7:6; 14:2; Tit 2:14; 1Pe 2:9.\x*
\v 19 and thenВҰ94418 he'll make \add вүҲyour country\add* greater than all the others thatВҰ94424 he's \add вүҲestablished\add*. You'll be praisedВҰ94426 for your reputation and beauty, and you'll be different from the othersвҖ”being a sacredВҰ94432 peopleВҰ94430 for your godВҰ94434 YahwehВҰ94433, just like he's said.
\c 27
\s1 The warnings of not still entering of Kanaan
\rem /s1 Moses' closing discourse; God's Laws Written on Stones; The Altar on Mount Ebal; The Inscribed Stones and Altar on Mount Ebal
\p
\v 1 Then MoshehВҰ94440 \add (Moses)\add* and the IsraeliВҰ94441 eldersВҰ94441 commandedВҰ94439 the peopleВҰ94445, вҖңFollow all the \add вүҲinstructions\add* thatВҰ94453 I'm \add вүҲgiving\add* you today.
\v 2 When you cross the Yarden \add river\add* to enter the land thatВҰ94469 yourВҰ94472 godВҰ94472 YahwehВҰ94471 is giving you, thenВҰ94459 you must \add вүҲstand up some tall pieces of rock\add* andВҰ94459 coverВҰ94479 them with plasterВҰ94481.\x + \xo 27:2-8: \xt Josh 8:30-32.\x*
\v 3 ThenВҰ94483 writeВҰ94483 all these instructions onto them as soon as you've crossedВҰ94492 the river, so that you can enter the \add вүҲvery fertile\add* land that your god YahwehВҰ94501 is giving you, as he had \add вүҲpromised\add* your ancestorsВҰ94515.
\v 4 ThenВҰ94518 after you've \add вүҲgone further in\add*, \add вүҲstand some tall pieces of rock up on end\add* on Mt. EbalВҰ94534 like I've told you, andВҰ94535 coverВҰ94535 them with plasterВҰ94537,
\v 5 andВҰ94539 buildВҰ94539 a stone altar thereВҰ94540 \add to offer sacrifices\add* to yourВҰ94543 godВҰ94543 YahwehВҰ94542. Don't use any iron tools \add вүҲto shape\add* the stonesВҰ94545.\x + \xo 27:5-6: \xt Exo 20:25.\x*
\v 6 You must built Yahweh's altarВҰ94557 with uncut stones. Then you can offerВҰ94560 burntВҰ94562 sacrifices to your god Yahweh on it.
\v 7 \add вүҲAlso,\add* you can sacrificeВҰ94566 peaceВҰ94567 offeringsВҰ94567 andВҰ94566 cheerfully eatВҰ94568 them thereВҰ94569 in frontВҰ94571 of yourВҰ94573 godВҰ94573 YahwehВҰ94572.
\v 8 When you write these instructions on those stonesВҰ94578, you must write them very clearlyВҰ94586.
\rem /s1 Curses From Mount Ebal
\p
\v 9 Then Mosheh \add (Mosheh)\add* along with the priestsВҰ94592 and the LevitesВҰ94593, spokeВҰ94590 to all Yisrael, вҖңBe silentВҰ94599 and listenВҰ94601, Yisrael. Today youВҰ94605 have becomeВҰ94605 the peopleВҰ94606 of yourВҰ94608 godВҰ94608 YahwehВҰ94607.
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ94610\add* \add from now on\add*, you must \add вүҲlisten to what he says\add* and followВҰ94614 all the instructions and rules thatВҰ94623 I'm giving you today.вҖқ
\s1 Curses for disobedience
\rem /s1 The Curses on Disobedience; Curses from Mount Ebal; Twelve Curses
\p
\v 11 That \add same\add* dayВҰ94634, MoshehВҰ94630 told the peopleВҰ94633,
\v 12 вҖңAfter you've all crossedВҰ94648 the Yarden \add river\add*, the tribesВҰ94638 of SimeonВҰ94652, LeviВҰ94653, Yehudah, Yissakar, YosefВҰ94656, and BenyaminВҰ94657 must standВҰ94639 on MtВҰ94646. GerizimВҰ94647 and blessВҰ94640 the peopleВҰ94643.\x + \xo 27:12: \xt Deu 11:29; Josh 8:33-35.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the tribes of Reuven, GadВҰ94667, AsherВҰ94668, Zevulun, DanВҰ94670, andВҰ94659 NaftaliВҰ94671 must standВҰ94660 on Mt. EbalВҰ94665 \add to hear\add* the curseВҰ94663.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ94673 the LevitesВҰ94674 will call out loudly to tell \add вүҲeveryВҰ94678\add* IsraeliВҰ94681:
\p
\v 15 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyone\add* who makes a figure, whether carved \add from wood\add* or cast \add from metal\add*, and secretlyВҰ94698 sets it up \add to worship\add* will be cursedВҰ94686 \add because\add* YahwehВҰ94693 abhors it.вҖҷ\x + \xo 27:15: \xt Exo 20:4; 34:17; Lev 19:4; 26:1; Deu 4:15-18; 5:8.\x*
\p Then the peopleВҰ94702 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 16 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94708\add* who dishonoursВҰ94708 their fatherВҰ94709 or motherВҰ94710 will be cursedВҰ94707.вҖҷ
\p Then the peopleВҰ94714 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 17 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94719\add* who moves their boundaryВҰ94720 marker \add back into\add* their neighbour'sВҰ94721 \add property\add* will be cursedВҰ94718.вҖҷ
\p Then the peopleВҰ94725 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 18 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94730\add* who leadsВҰ94730 a blindВҰ94731 person down the wrong pathВҰ94732 will be cursedВҰ94729.вҖҷ
\p Then the peopleВҰ94736 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 19 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94741\add* who perverts justiceВҰ94742 for a foreigner or orphan or widowВҰ94746 will be cursedВҰ94740.вҖҷ\x + \xo 27:19: \xt Exo 22:21; 23:9; Lev 19:33-34; Deu 24:17-18.\x*
\p Then the peopleВҰ94750 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 20 вҖҳ\add вүҲAny man\add* who sleeps with a wife of his father will be cursedВҰ94754 because \add вүҲhe's exposed his father's nakedness\add*.вҖҷ
