\v 23 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94805\add* who sleeps with his mother-in-law will be cursedВҰ94804.вҖҷ
\p Then the peopleВҰ94812 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 24 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94817\add* who secretlyВҰ94819 \add вүҲmurders\add* his neighbourВҰ94818 will be cursedВҰ94816.вҖҷ
\p Then the peopleВҰ94823 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 25 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyoneВҰ94828\add* who \add вүҲtakesВҰ94828 payment to murder\add* an innocentВҰ94833 personВҰ94831 will be cursedВҰ94827.вҖҷ
\p Then the peopleВҰ94837 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\p
\v 26 вҖҳ\add вүҲAnyone\add* who doesn't \add вүҲfollow all these instructions\add* will be cursedВҰ94841.вҖҷ\x + \xo 27:26: \xt Gal 3:10.\x*
\p Then the peopleВҰ94857 must reply, вҖҳLet it be so.вҖҷ
\c 28
\s1 Blessings for obedience
\rem /s1 The Blessings of Obedience; Blessings for Obedience
\r (Lev. 26:3-13; Deu. 7:12-24)
\p
\v 1 If you, \add Yisrael,\add* listen to \add вүҲwhat god YahwehВҰ94867 says\add* and follow all his instructions thatВҰ94876 I'm giving you today, then \add *he\add* will make you the greatest of all the nationsВҰ94887 \add вүҲin the world\add*,\x + \xo 28:1-14: \xt Deu 11:13-17.\x*
\v 2 andВҰ94890 all theseВҰ94895 blessingsВҰ94894 will comeВҰ94890 to you if you listenВҰ94898 to \add his\add* voiceВҰ94899:
\p
\v 3 You'll be blessed in the cityВҰ94905, andВҰ94906 blessed in the countrysideВҰ94908.
\p
\v 4 Your \add вүҲchildren\add*, your \add вүҲharvestsВҰ94911\add*, and your \add вүҲcalves, and lambs and kids\add* will \add all\add* be blessedВҰ94910.
\p
\v 5 Your basketВҰ94924 and your kneadingВҰ94925 bowl will be blessedВҰ94923.
\p
\v 6 You'll be blessed when you're coming in andВҰ94930 when you're going out.
\p
\v 7 YahwehВҰ94935 \add вүҲwill enable you to defeatВҰ94941\add* your enemiesВҰ94938 who comeВҰ94945 to attack youвҖ”they'll \add вүҲmarch in all orderly, but\add* will flee from you in \add вүҲall\add* directionsВҰ94948.
\p
\v 8 YahwehВҰ94953 will decree a blessing on your barnsВҰ94958 and on all \add вүҲthe work you do\add*, and he'll bless you in the land thatВҰ94964 \add *he's\add* giving to you.
\p
\v 9 If you follow your GodВҰ94988 Yahweh's instructions and \add вүҲdo what he wants\add*, \add *heВҰ94974\add* will establish you as his sacredВҰ94977 peopleВҰ94976 just like he promised.
\v 10 ThenВҰ94992 all the peoplesВҰ94995 \add вүҲaround the world\add* will realise that Yahweh'sВҰ94999 nameВҰ94998 is \add вүҲattached to\add* you, andВҰ94992 they'll be afraidВҰ95002 of you.
\v 11 YahwehВҰ95006 will help you to really prosperВҰ95007 through your children, your animals, andВҰ95005 your harvestsВҰ95008 in the land that \add *he\add* promised to your ancestorsВҰ95019 that he'd giveВҰ95020 to you.
\v 12 YahwehВҰ95024 will open his treasure \add house\add* in the sky and send goodВҰ95030 rain \add вүҲwhen it's needed\add* and blessВҰ95039 \add вүҲeverything you do\add*, \add вүҲso that\add* you'll lend \add money\add* to many nationsВҰ95046 instead of needing to borrowВҰ95050 it.
\v 13 Yahweh will make you the head, not the tail. You'll be above, not beneath, if you listenВҰ95065 to yourВҰ95074 godВҰ95071 Yahweh's instructions thatВҰ95072 I'm giving you today, andВҰ95052 \add вүҲfollowВҰ95077 them\add*
\v 14 \add MakeВҰ95085 sure youВҰ95080\add* don'tВҰ95079 turnВҰ95080 away from those instructions, andВҰ95079 never \add вүҲworship\add* otherВҰ95094 godsВҰ95093.
\s1 Curses for disobedience
\rem /s1 Warnings against Disobedience; Curses for Disobedience; The Consequences of Disobedience
\r (Lev. 26:14-46)
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲOn the other hand,\add* if you don'tВҰ95101 listenВҰ95102 to yourВҰ95116 godВҰ95105 Yahweh's voiceВҰ95103 and keep following his instructions and obeying his rules thatВҰ95114 I'm giving you today, then all theseВҰ95123 cursesВҰ95122 will \add вүҲcatch up to you and hit\add* you:
\p
\v 16 You'll be cursed in the cityВҰ95128 andВҰ95129 cursed in the countrysideВҰ95131.
\p
\v 17 Your basketВҰ95134 and your kneadingВҰ95135 bowl will be cursedВҰ95133.
\p
\v 18 Your \add вүҲchildren\add*, your \add вүҲharvestsВҰ95138\add*, and your \add вүҲcalves, and lambs and kids\add* will \add all\add* be cursedВҰ95137.
\p
\v 19 You'll be cursed when you're coming in andВҰ95151 when you're going out.
\s1 The curses of repentance from God
\p
\v 20 YahwehВҰ95156 will sendВҰ95155 cursesВҰ95161 against you, and confusionВҰ95164 and opposition in \add вүҲeverything your country does\add* untilВҰ95174 you're destroyedВҰ95175 and quicklyВҰ95179 \add вүҲeliminated\add* because of your evil activities that \add demonstrate that\add* you've abandonedВҰ95184 me.
\v 21 YahwehВҰ95187 will make the plague clingВҰ95186 to you untilВҰ95192 he's finished you from off the land that you'reВҰ95199 aboutВҰ95200 to enter and \add вүҲtake ownership of\add*.
\v 22 YahwehВҰ95206 will send \add вүҲcancer\add* and feverВҰ95208 and inflammationВҰ95209. There'll be fieryВҰ95210 heat and droughtВҰ95211, and blightВҰ95212 and mildewВҰ95213, and will chase you untilВҰ95215 you \add вүҲdie\add*.
\v 23 The overhead skyВҰ95219 \add will be locked up\add* like bronzeВҰ95224, andВҰ95225 \add the dryness will make\add* the land like iron.
\v 24 \add вүҲInstead of\add* rain on your land, YahwehВҰ95232 will send powdered dust that will cover you untilВҰ95244 \add @your country\add* is destroyedВҰ95245.
\p
\v 25 YahwehВҰ95249 \add вүҲwill allow your enemiesВҰ95253 to destroy you\add*вҖ”your army will \add вүҲmarch in all orderly, but\add* will flee from you in \add вүҲall\add* directionsВҰ95259, and all \add вүҲthe other countries in the world will be horrified at what happens to\add* you.
\v 26 Your corpsesВҰ95269 will become food for birds and wild animals, and there'll be no one \add left\add* to \add вүҲscare them away\add*.
\v 27 YahwehВҰ95281 will afflict you with boilsВҰ95282 \add вүҲlike he sent to the EgyptianВҰ95283 people\add*, along with ulcers, rashes, and itching whichВҰ95288 \add вүҲthere's no cure for\add*.
\v 28 YahwehВҰ95295 will strike youВҰ95294 with madnessВҰ95296 and blindnessВҰ95297, and with \add вүҲconfusedВҰ95298 minds\add*.
\v 29 \add вүҲEven in the middle of the day,\add* you'll be gropingВҰ95302 around like blindВҰ95306 people, and yourВҰ95312 projects won'tВҰ95308 be successfulВҰ95309. You'll be oppressedВҰ95315 and robbedВҰ95316 continually, and there'll be no one to rescue you.
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲA man\add* will be engaged to a young womanВҰ95323, but someone else will rape her. You'll buildВҰ95330 a houseВҰ95329, but never get to live in it, and you'll plantВҰ95336 a vineyardВҰ95335, \add вүҲbut not get to produce any wine\add*.
\v 31 Your cowВҰ95343 will be slaughteredВҰ95344 right in front of your eyesВҰ95345, but you won'tВҰ95346 get to eatВҰ95347 any of it. You donkeyВҰ95349 will be stolen \add вүҲright in front of you\add*, but will \add never\add* be returnedВҰ95353. Your sheepВҰ95355 will be givenВҰ95356 to your enemiesВҰ95357, but no one will help you rescue them.
\v 32 YourВҰ95376 sons and daughtersВҰ95363 will be handed over to anotherВҰ95366 country, and you'll strainВҰ95369 yourВҰ95376 eyesВҰ95367 all dayВҰ95373 lookingВҰ95368 for them, but you won't be able to do anything about it.
\v 33 People from a country you've never heard of will harvest your crops and \add вүҲenjoy the results of\add* your work, but you'll just be oppressedВҰ95391 and crushedВҰ95392.
\v 34 \add вүҲAll the things you witness will driveВҰ95398 you to insanity\add*.
\v 35 YahwehВҰ95405 will strike your \add people\add* with badВҰ95407 boilsВҰ95406 on your kneesВҰ95410 and legs thatВҰ95414 will never heal upвҖ”from the bottom of your soles right up to the tops of your heads.
\p
\v 36 YahwehВҰ95425 will lead you and the kingВҰ95429 that you'll place over you, to a countryВҰ95435 that you and your ancestorsВҰ95441 have never been to, and you'll \add end up\add* serving otherВҰ95445 godsВҰ95444 thereВҰ95443 made of wood or stoneВҰ95447.
\v 37 Those peopleВҰ95454 in the countries that YahwehВҰ95458 will push you into will be horrified about you, and create sayings and jokes about you.
\p
\v 38 You'll \add вүҲplant a lot of seed in your fieldsВҰ95464, but\add* only gatherВҰ95466 a smallВҰ95465 \add harvest\add* because locustsВҰ95469 will eat the crops.
\v 39 You'll plantВҰ95472 vineyards and cultivateВҰ95473 them, but you won'tВҰ95475 harvest the grapes or drinkВҰ95477 the wine, because worms will eatВҰ95481 them.
\v 40 You'll have olive trees across your territoryВҰ95489, but you won'tВҰ95491 have any oil to \add вүҲrub on your skin\add*, because the \add unripe\add* olives will drop off \add the trees\add*.
\v 41 You'll have sons and daughtersВҰ95498, \add вүҲbut youВҰ95499 won'tВҰ95500 be able to keep them\add* because they'll be \add вүҲtaken away as captivesВҰ95506\add*.
\v 42 \add Swarms of\add* cricketsВҰ95514 will takeВҰ95513 over your treesВҰ95510 and \add вүҲplants\add*.
\p
\v 43 The foreigners who live among you will become \add вүҲmore and more powerful\add* and you'll become \add вүҲless and less powerful\add*.
\v 44 They'll lend to you, not you lending to them. The foreigner will be the head and you'll be the tail.
\p
\v 45 All those cursesВҰ95544 will comeВҰ95540 on you and chase and overtakeВҰ95547 you untilВҰ95548 you're destroyedВҰ95549 because \add @your country\add* didn'tВҰ95552 listenВҰ95553 to the voiceВҰ95554 of your godВҰ95556 YahwehВҰ95555, or follow his instructions, or obey the rules thatВҰ95560 he \add вүҲgave\add* you.
\v 46 \add @Those curses\add* will afflict you andВҰ95563 yourВҰ95567 descendantsВҰ95567 forever as signs
\v 47 because you didn'tВҰ95574 serveВҰ95576 your godВҰ95580 YahwehВҰ95579 with cheerfulness \add resulting\add* from the abundanceВҰ95584 \add that you took for granted\add*.
\v 48 \add вүҲSoВҰ95587 thenВҰ95587,\add* Yahweh will sendВҰ95592 enemiesВҰ95590 against you and you'll serveВҰ95587 them in hungerВҰ95595 and thirstВҰ95596, and in nakednessВҰ95597 and lacking everythingВҰ95599. \add @Yahweh\add* will put an iron yoke on your neck \add used for pulling heavy loads with,\add* untilВҰ95606 heВҰ95607 destroysВҰ95607 you.
\v 49 YahwehВҰ95611 will send a very distant nation againstВҰ95612 you. They'll \add swoopВҰ95618 in\add* like an eagleВҰ95619вҖ”speaking a languageВҰ95625 thatВҰ95621 you won'tВҰ95622 understandВҰ95624.
\v 50 They'll be fierceВҰ95628 \add вүҲlooking\add* andВҰ95636 with \add вүҲno mercy\add* for either the elderly or the youngВҰ95636.
\v 51 They'll eatВҰ95640 \add the meat of\add* your animals andВҰ95640 the harvestsВҰ95641 from your crops until you're destroyedВҰ95647. They won'tВҰ95649 leaveВҰ95651 any grainВҰ95653 or new wine, or calves, lambs, or kidsвҖ”you'll all \add вүҲdie\add* \add of hunger\add*.
\v 52 They'll surround all your cities untilВҰ95669 your highВҰ95672, fortifiedВҰ95673 wallsВҰ95671 thatВҰ95674 you trustedВҰ95676 in comeВҰ95670 down all over your country. \add Yes,\add* you'll be \add contained\add* inside your cities throughout the land the your godВҰ95692 YahwehВҰ95691 has givenВҰ95690 you.
\p
\v 53 Due to that siegeВҰ95708 and the distress that you experience from the oppression of your enemies, you'll \add end up\add* eating the fleshВҰ95699 of the sonsВҰ95700 and daughtersВҰ95701 that your godВҰ95707 YahwehВҰ95706 has givenВҰ95703 you.
\v 54 Even the most sensitiveВҰ95719, kind-hearted manВҰ95716 among you will \add вүҲbe selfish\add* towards his brotherВҰ95723, towards the wifeВҰ95724 \add вүҲthatВҰ95728 he loves\add*, and towards his own remainingВҰ95729 childrenВҰ95727вҖ”
\v 55 withholding from them, the fleshВҰ95735 of his childrenВҰ95736 that he'll eatВҰ95738, in his distress as he has nothing else left due to that siegeВҰ95744 and the oppression from your enemies that have surrounded your cities.
\v 56 Even the most delicateВҰ95768, tender woman among you \add вүҲwho never once stepped outside the house in her bare feet\add*, will \add вүҲbe selfish\add* towards the husbandВҰ95772 \add вүҲthat she loves\add* and to her own son and her own daughterВҰ95775вҖ”\x + \xo 28:57: \xt 2Ki 6:28-29; Lam 4:10.\x*
\v 57 eating \add both\add* her new baby and the placenta, in her distress as sheВҰ95784 has nothing else left due to that siegeВҰ95792 and the oppression from your enemies that have surrounded your cities.
\p
\v 58 If youВҰ95803 don'tВҰ95802 keep following all the instructions that are writtenВҰ95812 in this book, i.e., not \add вүҲhonouring andВҰ95820 showing respect\add* to yourВҰ95824 incredible godВҰ95824 YahwehВҰ95823,
\v 59 thenВҰ95826 \add *he'll\add* punish you by sending terrible plagues to you andВҰ95826 yourВҰ95830 descendantsВҰ95833, along with long-lasting illnesses.
\v 60 All the plagues thatВҰ95848 he sent onto the Egyptians and whichВҰ95848 terrified you, he'll send them onto you \add now\add* and they'll clingВҰ95851 to you.
\v 61 Every kind of sicknessВҰ95857 and disease thatВҰ95861 isn'tВҰ95862 \add even\add* writtenВҰ95863 in this book, YahwehВҰ95868 will send them \add all\add* onto you untilВҰ95870 you're destroyedВҰ95871.
\v 62 Even though you all had been as numerous as the starsВҰ95879 in the sky, \add @your country\add* will be left underpopulated because you didn'tВҰ95884 listenВҰ95885 to your godВҰ95888 Yahweh's voiceВҰ95886.
\v 63 JustВҰ95902 as YahwehВҰ95894 was happy to do good things for you and multiplyВҰ95898 you all, he would thenВҰ95890 be happy to to bringВҰ95904 you all to ruin and destructionВҰ95906. ThenВҰ95890 you'll be torn away from the land that you'reВҰ95913 going in to \add вүҲtake ownership of\add*.
\p
\v 64 YahwehВҰ95920 will scatterВҰ95919 you among all the peoplesВҰ95923 \add вүҲright around the world\add* where you'll serveВҰ95930 godsВҰ95932 made out of wood or stoneВҰ95941 thatВҰ95934 neither you nor your ancestorsВҰ95939 \add вүҲhad heard of\add*.
\v 65 You won'tВҰ95945 have any peace among thoseВҰ95944 nationsВҰ95943, and \add вүҲyou'll never be able to relax\add*, but rather YahwehВҰ95955 will give you tremblingВҰ95959 heartsВҰ95958, sore eyesВҰ95961, and \add вүҲminds full of despair\add*.
\v 66 \add вүҲTime will go very slowly for you\add*, and you'll be scared both nightВҰ95971 and dayВҰ95972, \add вүҲwithout any certainty in your life\add*.
\v 67 In the morning you'll say, вҖҳIf only it was evening,вҖҷ and in the evening you'll say, вҖҳIf only it was morning,вҖҷ because of the continual tightness in your stomach and because of the sightsВҰ95993 \add вүҲyou'll have to witness\add*.
\v 68 YahwehВҰ96000 will send \add some of\add* you back to EgyptВҰ96002 by ship, even though I'dВҰ96006 told you that you'll never see that country againВҰ96011. ThenВҰ95998 you'll be offeredВҰ96013 there for sale as slaves, but no one will \add want to\add* buy you.
\c 29
\rem /s1 The Lord's Covenant with Israel in the Land of Moab; Renewal of the Covenant
\p
\v 1 Those are the words of the agreement that YahwehВҰ96066 commanded MoshehВҰ96051 to \add вүҲmake\add* with the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ96054\add* there in Moav, on top of the agreement that he'd \add вүҲmade\add* with them at Horeb \add (Mt. Sinai)\add*.
\s1 Overview of the agreement
\rem /s1 Moses Reviews the Covenant; The Covenant Renewed in Moab
\p
\v 2 Then Mosheh \add (Moses)\add* called all Yisrael together and told them, вҖңYou've all seen everything thatВҰ96081 Yahweh did to Far-oh and all his servants in Egypt and \add вүЎwhat he did\add* to all his country \add вүҲright in front of\add* your eyesВҰ96083вҖ”
\v 3 the sufferings \add of the people there\add* that you saw for yourselves, along with the incredible miracles,
\v 4 \add вүҲyet up until now\add*, Yahweh hasn't enabled you all to understandВҰ96121 the meaning of everything that you saw and heard.
\v 5 ForВҰ96135 forty years, \add вүҲYahwehВҰ96136\add* led you all in the wilderness, \add but\add* your clothes didn'tВҰ96126 wear through, and the sandals on your feet never wore out.
\v 6 You all \add survived without\add* bread to eat or any wine or alcohol to drink so that you'd realise that I am your god Yahweh.
\v 7 Then when we arrived here, King Sihon from Heshbon and King Og from Bashan came out \add вүҲto battle\add* against us, \add вүҲbut we defeated them\add*.\x + \xo 29:7: a \xt Num 21:21-30; \xo b \xt Num 21:31-35.\x*
\v 8 We took their land and gave it to the tribes of Reuven and Gad, and the half-tribe of Menashsheh to become their inheritance.\x + \xo 29:8: \xt Num 32:33.\x*
\v 9 \add вүҲSo\add* follow all the instructions in this agreement andВҰ96200 obey the rules so that you'll all prosper in everythingВҰ96201 you do.
\p
\v 10 All of you stand \add here\add* today \add вүҲin front\add* of your god Yahweh: your chiefs, your tribes, your elders, and your officers, all the Israeli men
\v 11 along with your wives and children, and the foreigners \add вүҲliving\add* among you (who cut wood and fetch water for you),
\v 12 to enter into an agreement with your godВҰ96244 Yahweh, and to \add accept\add* the promise thatВҰ96249 \add вүҲhe's made to\add* you today.
\v 13 That will establish \add @your country\add* as his people, and he will be your god as he told you he would, having promised \add >it\add* to your ancestors Abraham, Yitshak, and Yakov.
\v 14 ThisВҰ96282 agreement isn'tВҰ96286 just with all of you here today,
\v 15 the ones standing here, \add вүҲbut also\add* with those who aren't here with you today.
\p
\v 16 You all know how we lived in Egypt, and then travelled through other \add вүҲkingdoms\add* on our way \add here\add*,
\v 17 and you've all seen their disgusting practices and the idols that they had, made of wood and stone, gold and silver.
\v 18 If there happens to be a man or woman, or clan or tribe, whose \add вүҲloyalty\add* is turning away today from your god Yahweh and to go and serve those gods in those other nations, i.e., if there's a \add вүҲbitter or poisonous root\add* among you all,\x + \xo 29:18: \xt Heb 12:15.\x*
\v 19 and if they hear the words of this curseВҰ96408, then they'll think to themselves, вҖҳWe'll have peace, even though \add вүҲour minds are fixed on where we're going\add*,вҖҷ so that the \add ?вүҲgood and the bad are carried along together\add*,
\v 20 Yahweh won't be willing to forgive them. \add No,\add* his jealousy and anger will rage against them, and all the curses writtenВҰ96430 in this book will land on them, and Yahweh will wipe out their name \add вүҲnever to be remembered again\add*.
\v 21 Then YahwehВҰ96460 will single out that person \add or group\add* from all of Yisrael's tribe, to be marked out for disaster as per all the curses that are written in this book of instructions.
\p
\v 22 Then a future generation (your descendants who'll be born in the future, plus the foreigner who comesВҰ96476 from a distant land), when they see the plagues \add that hit\add* that land and the diseases that YahwehВҰ96489 \add sent to\add* make it sick, will say,
\v 23 вҖҳAll that land is sulfur and burning salt. No one plants anything and nothing sprouts, and not even grass grows in it, like the overthrow of Sodom and Amorah \add (Gomorrah)\add*, Admah and Tsevoim, which YahwehВҰ96502 destroyed in his rage and angerВҰ96508,вҖҷ\x + \xo 29:23: \xt Gen 19:24-25.\x*
\v 24 and all the nations will \add вүҲask\add*, вҖҳWhy did YahwehВҰ96520 do that to that country? What's \add вүҲhe so angry about\add*?вҖҷ
\v 25 Then \add вүҲothersВҰ96535 will reply\add*, вҖҳBecause they neglected their agreement with Yahweh, the god of their ancestors, thatВҰ96540 he \add вүҲmade\add* with them when he brought them out from Egypt,
\v 26 and they went and served other gods and bowed down to themвҖ”gods that they hadn't \add вүҲheard of before or had anything to do with\add*.
\v 27 That's why YahwehВҰ96568 was angry at that country and brought all the curses written in this book onto itвҖ”
\v 28 tearing them away from their land \add вүҲin his raging anger\add*, and threw them into another land as \add we can see\add* today.вҖҷ
\p
\v 29 Our god Yahweh \add вүҲhas his secrets\add*, \add вүҲbut what he's revealed\add* is for us and our children forever, so that we can follow all his instructions.
\c 30
\s1 Opportunity for restoration
\rem /s1 Prosperity After Turning to the Lord; Conditions for Restoration and Blessing; A Call to Return to the Lord; God's Fidelity Assured
\p
